re struggling with heavily researched medical issues be supported.</li>\r\n	<li>We will not support organizations which participate heavily in political donations, activity, or lobbying. If there is a cause that needs representation at state and federal levels then let us know and we will work together on how to address that.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe bottom line: we want our donations to get to people who need it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Here are some numbers on how we can impact our communities:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>First off let\'s assume our app is awesome, and it gains great market acceptance and we grow like crazy. But let\'s just start at that 1% (1.5 million) of the market. Good, now that we have that out of the way.</li>\r\n	<li>We would love to have all of our users donate their entire $15 max, then we match that, which equals $30 total. But to be realistic that group might make up around 10% (150,000) of our total active users, giving us a potential total of $4.5 million a month from these users.</li>\r\n	<li>If the rest of the 1.35 million users donate $1, and we match that, then it equals $2. We get monthly donation funds of... $2.7 million plus the users\' donations from point number 2, then we get <strong>$7.2 million a month.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.ggpht.com/DLDifF6R6ETGoHBPAfEDcwbRnZiTvty074hd0WQuRJug7RbfR7ihrkZXgt5zACKejbL6=h900\"><img class=\"alignright\" src=\"https://lh3.ggpht.com/DLDifF6R6ETGoHBPAfEDcwbRnZiTvty074hd0WQuRJug7RbfR7ihrkZXgt5zACKejbL6=h900\" alt=\"\" width=\"461\" height=\"288\" /></a>Sounds crazy right... Well Candy Crush Saga, yes we just referenced that game, has over 100 million active users!\r\n\r\nIt makes over $600,000 a day, and over $230 million a year <strong>AND</strong> our app has the potential to blow that away!\r\n\r\nIf we can donate $7.2 million a month, here is just a glimpse at some of the things we can do with that:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>@ $200 per child = 36,000 kids <strong>clothing &amp; school supplies</strong> for a year</li>\r\n	<li>@ $3.50 per meal = over 2.0 million <strong>meals</strong></li>\r\n	<li>@ $100 per procedure = 72,000<strong> dental procedures</strong> for underprivileged families</li>\r\n	<li>@ $100 per month = 72,000 <strong>Public Transit passes</strong> for a month to un/under employed</li>\r\n	<li>@$2,000 per month = 3,600 families <strong>sheltered and given job training</strong> per month</li>\r\n	<li>@ $5,000 per semester = 1440 <strong>scholarships</strong> to under-funded college students</li>\r\n	<li>@ $25,000 per child = 288 families <strong>supported during life threatening medical issues</strong></li>\r\n	<li>@ $100,000 per unit = We can deliver a self-sustaining water solution to 72 locations, and <strong>provide clean water</strong> where thousands die every year from unclean water...</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf we donated all but a fraction of our revenues to efforts like this we would find joy and satisfaction in our existence and our app. But we can have both an amazing impact through our donations <strong>and</strong> have a healthy profit margin; this is a \"win/win\" opportunity.\r\n\r\nWe also want to help small businesses by providing them with free help when it comes to learning how to advertise and how to get results.\r\n\r\nWe want to give large brands the reach and impact they are looking for every day.\r\n\r\nWe want to provide an amazing return for our investors so they can go out and invest more in companies that do good.\r\n\r\nWe want to talk to you.\r\n<h3>If you want to become part of our team, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://lscapp.com/contact/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></h3>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-04-30 15:55:26','2014-04-30 15:55:26','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(79,1,'2014-04-30 15:56:38','2014-04-30 15:56:38','<a href=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-252 alignright\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" /></a>Many could use a little help.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">Many more people would love to help.</p>\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have an app in development to make all of this easier. The focus of the app is to deliver ads to users, to pay those users up to $15 a month for letting us deliver ads to them, then ask those users to donate at least $1 per month of their earnings. <strong>We then match these donations, dollar for dollar. </strong><em>\r\n</em></span>\r\n\r\nOur app will be attractive to those who want to save a buck or 15, but what about those who do not care about the cost of their cell phone plan?\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Crowd.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-96\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Crowd.jpg\" alt=\"Crowd\" width=\"388\" height=\"255\" /></a>This is where we really push the fact that we are willing to match their full potential of $15 per month, dollar for dollar. Just to make it easy on everyone--<em>that is up to $30 per cell phone</em> user donated to charity. We know that $30 per month is nothing to get too excited about, but if you multiply that by thousands of people every month we could be donating $30,000 - $300,000 or even $3,000,000<em> per month</em> to a charity of our users\' choice.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">It is simple: the advertising pays for charity work.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">By partnering with strategic organizations, charities, carriers, and other large companies, we can hit our first goal of 1% of the 150 million smartphone user market by the middle of 2015. Yes that is 1.5 million users, and yes we know that is crazy user engagement in a short time. This will help us donate up to 3 million dollars <strong>per month</strong> to charities that we vet. If you want to find out more about our marketing plan, <a href=\"info@lscapp.com\">email us</a>. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Our requirements for the charities before getting money from us will be:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 24px;\">No less than 85% of all funds donated must go directly to the key activities of the cause, now this does not mean that no more than 15% can go to \'overhead\' only that it must be an activity that can benefit the cause. We want to work with these charities and make sure that most of their efforts are productive. Fundraising can be productive, getting great talent can be productive, marketing can be productive, tech investments can be productive yet these are all considered traditionally overhead in the non-profit world.</span></li>\r\n	<li>Legal work using donated funds will be heavily scrutinized. We love the legal system but we would rather feed children than pay lawyers.</li>\r\n	<li>Organizations run by religious groups will be heavily scrutinized. We want to make sure everyone is served; not just individuals who share a faith or ideology.</li>\r\n	<li>Medical research will be vetted heavily to make sure funds are going to research that is making strides not spinning wheels. We would love to see families who are struggling with heavily researched medical issues be supported.</li>\r\n	<li>We will not support organizations which participate heavily in political donations, activity, or lobbying. If there is a cause that needs representation at state and federal levels then let us know and we will work together on how to address that.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe bottom line: we want our donations to get to people who need it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Here are some numbers on how we can impact our communities:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>First off let\'s assume our app is awesome, and it gains great market acceptance and we grow like crazy. But let\'s just start at that 1% (1.5 million) of the market. Good, now that we have that out of the way.</li>\r\n	<li>We would love to have all of our users donate their entire $15 max, then we match that, which equals $30 total. But to be realistic that group might make up around 10% (150,000) of our total active users, giving us a potential total of $4.5 million a month from these users.</li>\r\n	<li>If the rest of the 1.35 million users donate $1, and we match that, then it equals $2. We get monthly donation funds of... $2.7 million plus the users\' donations from point number 2, then we get <strong>$7.2 million a month.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.ggpht.com/DLDifF6R6ETGoHBPAfEDcwbRnZiTvty074hd0WQuRJug7RbfR7ihrkZXgt5zACKejbL6=h900\"><img class=\"alignright\" src=\"https://lh3.ggpht.com/DLDifF6R6ETGoHBPAfEDcwbRnZiTvty074hd0WQuRJug7RbfR7ihrkZXgt5zACKejbL6=h900\" alt=\"\" width=\"461\" height=\"288\" /></a>Sounds crazy right... Well Candy Crush Saga, yes we just referenced that game, has over 100 million active users!\r\n\r\nIt makes over $600,000 a day, and over $230 million a year <strong>AND</strong> our app has the potential to blow that away!\r\n\r\nIf we can donate $7.2 million a month, here is just a glimpse at some of the things we can do with that:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>@ $200 per child = 36,000 kids <strong>clothing &amp; school supplies</strong> for a year</li>\r\n	<li>@ $3.50 per meal = over 2.0 million <strong>meals</strong></li>\r\n	<li>@ $100 per procedure = 72,000<strong> dental procedures</strong> for underprivileged families</li>\r\n	<li>@ $100 per month = 72,000 <strong>Public Transit passes</strong> for a month to un/under employed</li>\r\n	<li>@$2,000 per month = 3,600 families <strong>sheltered and given job training</strong> per month</li>\r\n	<li>@ $5,000 per semester = 1440 <strong>scholarships</strong> to under-funded college students</li>\r\n	<li>@ $25,000 per child = 288 families <strong>supported during life threatening medical issues</strong></li>\r\n	<li>@ $100,000 per unit = We can deliver a self-sustaining water solution to 72 locations, and <strong>provide clean water</strong> where thousands die every year from unclean water...</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf we donated all but a fraction of our revenues to efforts like this we would find joy and satisfaction in our existence and our app. But we can have both an amazing impact through our donations <strong>and</strong> have a healthy profit margin; this is a \"win/win\" opportunity.\r\n\r\nWe also want to help small businesses by providing them with free help when it comes to learning how to advertise and how to get results.\r\n\r\nWe want to give large brands the reach and impact they are looking for every day.\r\n\r\nWe want to provide an amazing return for our investors so they can go out and invest more in companies that do good.\r\n\r\nWe want to talk to you.\r\n<h3>If you want to become part of our team, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://lscapp.com/contact/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></h3>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-04-30 15:56:38','2014-04-30 15:56:38','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(80,1,'2014-10-04 18:58:23','2014-10-04 18:58:23','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">So many people would love to do more...</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So why don\'t we all actually do more?</strong></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Many believe that unless their donation is large it doesn\'t make a difference, that unless they spend hours or days volunteering anything less is not worth the small impact.\n\nWe are not asking for our users to change their mobile device use, they don\'t even have to open our app, they do not need to take any more time out of their busy days to do good through Adora.\n\nOur app gives our users a choice they have never had before, to choose where their advertising earnings go. We make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Our app is simple: the advertising pays for charity work but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our app will also make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference but if 1 million or 10 million users all donate then those dollars add up!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"421\" height=\"258\" />Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible and oh the good that could be done with that kind of donation every month.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company in the world</strong></p>\n But once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish, we must change the way we look at charitable organizations.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses, be it a hashtag trending on twitter, a viral video, or dumping ice on our heads, we know that there are few better ways to move mountains. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below, better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<strong>If you want help out read more about how you can be more involved, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-04 18:58:23','2014-10-04 18:58:23','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(454,1,'2014-05-30 23:57:36','2014-05-30 23:57:36','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 60px;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 180px;\">So many people would love to do more but...</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So why don\'t we do more?</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Add money to the mix and many believe that unless their donation is large it doesn\'t make a difference.\r\n\r\nOur app solves all of these problems. First we are not asking for our users to change their mobile device use, they don\'t even have to open our app. Second our app gives our users a choice they have never had before, to choose where their advertising earnings go. And Third - we make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"426\" height=\"261\" /></a>Our app is simple: the advertising pays for charity work but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our app will also make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference but if 1 million or 100 million users all donate then those dollars add up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible and oh the good we could do with that kind of donation every month.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company in the world</strong></p>\r\n But once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish, we must change the way we look at charitable organizations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses, be it a moving hashtag spreading via twitter or a viral video, we know that there are a few better ways to move mountains. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below, better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<strong>If you want help out and become part of <a title=\"Team\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/team/\">our team</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-05-30 23:57:36','2014-05-30 23:57:36','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(269,1,'2014-05-09 08:09:42','2014-05-09 08:09:42','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 60px;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 150px;\">So many people would love to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Why do they/we not do more?</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Add money to the mix and many believe that unless their donation is large it doesn\'t make a difference.\r\n\r\nOur app solves both of those problems. First we are not asking for our users to spend any more time than they already do. Second our app gives our users a choice they have never had before, to choose where their advertising earnings go.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Crowd.jpg\" alt=\"Crowd\" width=\"388\" height=\"255\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Our app is simple: the advertising pays for charity work but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For those who would like to donate from their own pockets we hope to help this process be easier. Our app will make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference but if 1 million or 100 million users all donate then those dollars add up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company in the world</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">By creating strategic relationships we can hit our first goal of 1% of the 200 million smartphone user market by the middle of 2015. The math plays that 1% out to equal 2 million users, when compared to the 100 million Candy Crush users we would hope that at least 2% would be willing to support such a charitable cause. If you want to find out more about how we are going to gather these users, about our marketing plan, <a href=\"info@lscapp.com\">email us</a>. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<strong>If you want to become part of our team, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-05-09 08:09:42','2014-05-09 08:09:42','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(89,1,'2014-05-01 23:32:12','2014-05-01 23:32:12','<pre><em>This post is backdated to show some history of our journey.</em></pre>\r\nThe light bulb has always been on.\r\n\r\nThe goal has always been the same.\r\n\r\nDo something that matters!\r\n\r\nOne of the most difficult things we all face is doing something day in and day out that we do not believe in. Most of us have been there, and to those who haven\'t it is a learning experience, trust the rest of us - do something that you can believe in.\r\n\r\nDoesn\'t mean it still won\'t be work and that there wont be days that you just can\'t stand what you\'re working on BUT if your base goal/cause/reason for doing the work still inspires you then the hard stuff is more bearable.\r\n\r\nWe love what we do and the impact we can make -\r\n\r\nAnd while it all really started long ago this specific journey started on February 4th 2014...','The light bulb turns on ','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-v1','','','2014-05-01 23:32:12','2014-05-01 23:32:12','',1,'http://getadora.com/1-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(90,1,'2014-05-01 23:36:04','2014-05-01 23:36:04','','DontStop','','inherit','open','open','','dontstop','','','2014-05-01 23:36:04','2014-05-01 23:36:04','',1,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DontStop.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(91,1,'2014-05-01 23:36:24','2014-05-01 23:36:24','<pre><em>This post is backdated to show some history of our journey.</em></pre>\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DontStop.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-90\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DontStop.jpg\" alt=\"DontStop\" width=\"500\" height=\"207\" /></a>The light bulb has always been on.\r\n\r\nThe goal has always been the same.\r\n\r\nDo something that matters!\r\n\r\nOne of the most difficult things we all face is doing something day in and day out that we do not believe in. Most of us have been there, and to those who haven\'t it is a learning experience, trust the rest of us - do something that you can believe in.\r\n\r\nDoesn\'t mean it still won\'t be work and that there wont be days that you just can\'t stand what you\'re working on BUT if your base goal/cause/reason for doing the work still inspires you then the hard stuff is more bearable.\r\n\r\nWe love what we do and the impact we can make -\r\n\r\nAnd while it all really started long ago this specific journey started on February 4th 2014...','The light bulb turns on ','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-v1','','','2014-05-01 23:36:24','2014-05-01 23:36:24','',1,'http://getadora.com/1-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(93,1,'2014-05-01 23:43:07','2014-05-01 23:43:07','','PresentationLogo','','inherit','open','open','','presentationlogo','','','2014-05-01 23:43:07','2014-05-01 23:43:07','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/PresentationLogo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(96,5,'2014-02-13 06:42:37','2014-02-13 06:42:37','<h2>In the Beginning</h2>\r\nThe idea hit, but we didn\'t actually know what we had.\r\n\r\nSo we knew we needed to do some research.\r\n\r\nThe first thing we did was look for other people trying to do the same thing and we haven\'t found anyone who is or has been successful giving to charity in exchange for eyes on advertising.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ripple.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Ripple.org</a> tried and dried up in 2010</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/28/reddit-donations_n_4876589.html\" target=\"_blank\">Reddit is trying to give 10% of its ad revenue to charity</a> - they\'ve been operating for 9 years and is still in the red</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSeeing others crash and fall short we knew that if this was going to work it had to be done in a way that could rival the largest advertising networks out there - yes we\'re talking about you Google, Facebook, Twitter, Yahoo and a few others.\r\n\r\nThe original idea was based on mobile advertising. and do it in a way that doesn\'t interrupt the use of the phone, does not compete with some other service, application, or content, and can reach a user when other advertisers can\'t.\r\n\r\nWe had found a way to do all of this and amazingly by accident!\r\n<h2>The Market\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://83-136-248-155.uk-lon1.host.upcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-08-at-10-8-9.41.00-PM.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"413\" height=\"352\" /></h2>\r\nWe knew we had our solution but that doesn\'t guarantee you success, we then had to figure out the opportunity and that means establishing the market.\r\n\r\nFor this opportunity we must look at two markets; the smart phone market and the general mobile device market (tablets, wearables, glasses and the like), and the mobile advertising market. When looking at growth we need to look at it in stages, first the US market, moving on to Western Europe &amp; Asia, then to developing markets.\r\n\r\nWhen looking at your market it\'s easy to get excited and look at all the possibility but we need to focus. The US market is by far the most productive and well known market we have in front of us.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MobileUS.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-100\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MobileUS.jpg\" alt=\"MobileUS\" width=\"276\" height=\"256\" /></a>By the end of 2014 we are looking at more than 175 million Smartphone Users in the US. On the mobile advertising side the ad spending is expected to eclipse $11 billion.\r\n\r\nThis gives us a user value of more than $63.\r\n\r\nThe great thing about this market is the expected growth. By the end of 2015 we are looking at a projected 210 million users yet the advertising growth is expected to be over 43% or $16 billion.\r\n\r\n2015 user value grows to $76.\r\n\r\nIf growth holds true or actually if it continues to be adjusted up, as it has been over the last few years, then in 2016 we are looking at a user value of over $93.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-109\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MobileAdShare.jpg\" alt=\"MobileAdShare\" width=\"325\" height=\"254\" />There is one other main influence on the mobile advertising spending trends - the players.\r\n\r\nAs it stands there are really only two players in the mobile advertising world; Google and Facebook. Twitter is a distant third.\r\n\r\nIf we can do what we say we can do - Our ads don\'t get in the way, they don\'t have competition (we get the whole screen), and we can get in front of the user before everyone else when we want to and where we want to - then we should not only be able to get into that #3 spot but even make a push for the top spot.\r\n\r\nThe key - delivering a better ad than anyone else.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll talk more about that later...','In the beginning...','','publish','open','open','','in-the-beginning','','','2014-05-08 00:34:55','2014-05-08 00:34:55','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=96',0,'post','',0),(97,1,'2014-05-02 05:33:30','2014-05-02 05:33:30','The idea hit, but we didn\'t actually know what we had.\r\n\r\nSo we knew we needed to do some research.\r\n\r\nThe first thing we did was look for other people trying to do the same thing and we haven\'t found anyone who is or has been successful giving to charity in exchange for eyes on advertising.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ripple.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Ripple.org</a> tried and dried up in 2010</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/28/reddit-donations_n_4876589.html\" target=\"_blank\">Reddit is trying to give 10% of its ad revenue to charity</a> - they\'ve been operating for 9 years and is still in the red</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSeeing others crash and fail we knew that if this was going to work it had to be done in a way that could rival the largest advertising networks out there - yes we\'re talking about you Google, Facebook, Twitter, Yahoo and a few others.\r\n\r\nThe original idea was to focus on mobile advertising. and do it in a way that didn\'t interrupt the use of the phone and at the same time not compete with some other service, application, or content.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','In the beginning there was research...','','inherit','open','open','','96-revision-v1','','','2014-05-02 05:33:30','2014-05-02 05:33:30','',96,'http://getadora.com/96-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(98,1,'2014-05-02 06:42:37','2014-05-02 06:42:37','The idea hit, but we didn\'t actually know what we had.\r\n\r\nSo we knew we needed to do some research.\r\n\r\nThe first thing we did was look for other people trying to do the same thing and we haven\'t found anyone who is or has been successful giving to charity in exchange for eyes on advertising.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ripple.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Ripple.org</a> tried and dried up in 2010</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/28/reddit-donations_n_4876589.html\" target=\"_blank\">Reddit is trying to give 10% of its ad revenue to charity</a> - they\'ve been operating for 9 years and is still in the red</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nS