3% or $16 billion.\n\n2015 user value grows to $76.\n\nIf growth holds true or actually if it continues to be adjusted up, as it has been over the last few years, then in 2016 we are looking at a user value of over $93.\n\n<img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-109\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MobileAdShare.jpg\" alt=\"MobileAdShare\" width=\"325\" height=\"254\" />There is one other main influence on the mobile advertising spending trends - the players.\n\nAs it stands there are really only two players in the mobile advertising world; Google and Facebook. Twitter is a distant third.\n\nIf we can do what we say we can do - Our ads don\'t get in the way, they don\'t have competition (we get the whole screen), and we can get in front of the user before everyone else when we want to and where we want to - then we should not only be able to get into that #3 spot but even make a push for the top spot.','In the beginning there was research...','','inherit','open','open','','96-autosave-v1','','','2014-05-02 09:24:47','2014-05-02 09:24:47','',96,'http://getadora.com/96-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(100,1,'2014-05-02 08:20:47','2014-05-02 08:20:47','','MobileUS','','inherit','open','open','','mobileus','','','2014-05-02 08:20:47','2014-05-02 08:20:47','',96,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MobileUS.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(104,1,'2014-05-02 08:37:36','2014-05-02 08:37:36','The idea hit, but we didn\'t actually know what we had.\r\n\r\nSo we knew we needed to do some research.\r\n\r\nThe first thing we did was look for other people trying to do the same thing and we haven\'t found anyone who is or has been successful giving to charity in exchange for eyes on advertising.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ripple.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Ripple.org</a> tried and dried up in 2010</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/28/reddit-donations_n_4876589.html\" target=\"_blank\">Reddit is trying to g