/></a>By the end of 2014 we are looking at more than 175 million Smartphone Users in the US. On the mobile advertising side the ad spending is expected to eclipse $11 billion.\r\n\r\nThis gives us a user value of more than $63.\r\n\r\nThe great thing about this market is the expected growth. By the end of 2015 we are looking at a projected 210 million users yet the advertising growth is expected to be over 43% or $16 billion.\r\n\r\n2015 user value grows to $76.\r\n\r\nIf growth holds true or actually if it continues to be adjusted up, as it has been over the last few years, then in 2016 we are looking at a user value','In the beginning there was research...','','inherit','open','open','','96-revision-v1','','','2014-05-02 09:09:16','2014-05-02 09:09:16','',96,'http://getadora.com/96-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(108,1,'2014-05-02 09:12:02','2014-05-02 09:12:02','<h2>In the Beginning</h2>\r\nThe idea hit, but we didn\'t actually know what we had.\r\n\r\nSo we knew we needed to do some research.\r\n\r\nThe first thing we did was look for other people trying to do the same thing and we haven\'t found anyone who is or has been successful giving to charity in exchange for eyes on advertising.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.ripple.org/\" target=\"_blank\">Ripple.org</a> tried and dried up in 2010</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/02/28/reddit-donations_n_4876589.html\" target=\"_blank\">Reddit is trying to give 10% of its ad revenue to charity</a> - they\'ve been operating for 9 years and is still in the red</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSeeing others crash and fall short we knew that if this was going to work it had to be done in a way that could rival the largest advertising networks out there - yes we\'re talking about you Google, Facebook, Twitter, Yahoo and a few others.\r\n\r\nThe original idea was based on mobile advertising. and do it in a way that doesn\'t interrupt the use of the phone, does not compete with some other service, application, or content, and can reach a user when other advertisers can\'t.\r\n\r\nWe had found a way to do all of this and amazingly by accident!\r\n<h2>The Market\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://83-136-248-155.uk-lon1.host.upcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-08-at-10-8-9.41.00-PM.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"413\" height=\"352\" /></h2>\r\nWe knew we had our solution but that doesn\'t guarantee you success, we then had to figure out the opportunity and that means establishing the market.\r\n\r\nFor this opportunity we must look at two markets; the smart phone market and the general mobile device market (tablets, wearables, glasses and the like), and the mobile advertising market. When looking at growth we need to look at it in stages, first the US market, moving on to Western Europe &amp; Asia, then to developing markets.\r\n\r\nWhen looking at your market it\'s easy to get excited and look at all the possibility but we need to focus. The US market is by far the most productive and well known market we have in front of us.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MobileUS.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-100\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MobileUS.jpg\" alt=\"MobileUS\" width=\"276\" height=\"256\" /></a>By the end of 2014 we are looking at more than 175 million Smartphone Users in the US. On the mobile advertising side the ad spending is expected to eclipse $11 billion.\r\n\r\nThis gives us a user value of more than $63.\r\n\r\nThe great thing about this market is the expected growth. By the end of 2015 we are looking at a projected 210 million users yet the advertising growth is expected to be over 43% or $16 billion.\r\n\r\n2015 user value grows to $76.\r\n\r\nIf growth holds true or actually if it continues to be adjusted up, as it has been over the last few years, then in 2016 we are looking at a user value of over $93.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','In the beginning there was research...','','in