','','inherit','open','open','','113-autosave-v1','','','2014-05-02 11:26:15','2014-05-02 11:26:15','',113,'http://getadora.com/113-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(117,1,'2014-05-02 11:19:37','2014-05-02 11:19:37','One very important part of our idea was the involvement of charities and with charities.\r\n\r\nThere is a Ted Talk that we really like that brings home some issues with how we run and regulate our charitable organizations.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','113-revision-v1','','','2014-05-02 11:19:37','2014-05-02 11:19:37','',113,'http://getadora.com/113-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(116,1,'2014-05-02 11:19:21','2014-05-02 11:19:21','One very important part of our idea was the involvement of charities and with charities.\r\n\r\nThere is a Ted Talk that we really like that brings home some issues with how we run and regulate our charitable organizations.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','113-revision-v1','','','2014-05-02 11:19:21','2014-05-02 11:19:21','',113,'http://getadora.com/113-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2014-05-02 11:26:37','2014-05-02 11:26:37','One very important part of our idea was the involvement of charities and our support of these charities.\r\n\r\nWhen we talk about Charity+ we mean that we are hoping to do more and donate more to do more good than any other single organization int he world. We aren\'t talking about a billion here or there once a year or so NO we want to get to the point where we can donate over $1 billion every month. A lofty goal but we think it is possible.\r\n\r\nThere is a Ted Talk that we really like that brings home some issues with how we, as a society, run and regulate our charitable organizations.\r\n\r\n<iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nThis really hit home for us. We want to do good but we don\'t want to reward people or get the best people working on doing good. It seems backwards to us.\r\n\r\nWe\'ve batted around a few figures and we\'ve come to the goal of acting like a charity but still working like a for-profit company. By donating up to 60% of our revenue to charity we hope to make a huge impact on charities AND reward people for working with us to do that.\r\n\r\nWe do have a Charity+ page and you can learn more about how we want to do that there!','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','113-revision-v1','','','2014-05-02 11:26:37','2014-05-02 11:26:37','',113,'http://getadora.com/113-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(119,5,'2014-02-27 22:01:28','2014-02-27 22:01:28','We want to more clearly spell out why we feel our ad is going to be the absolute best ad opportunity for brands and the ad agencies that manage them.\r\n<h2>First Point: Reach</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TimeSpentUS.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-120\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TimeSpentUS.jpg\" alt=\"TimeSpentUS\" width=\"324\" height=\"321\" /></a>Mobile advertising is the fastest growing sub-sector in the advertising world, and for good reason.\r\n\r\nIf you look at the \'Share of Time Spent per Day with Major Media by US adults, 2010-2014\' you see a trend. First take a look at the change from TV to Digital from 2010-2014. Then take a look inside the digital breakdown, specifically the mobile and online share. It is clear that mobile is where the eyes are and where more are going.\r\n\r\nThis trend will only continue with greater saturation of smartphones, tablets, wearables and who knows what will come out next, but you can be sure it\'s mobile.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/TimeSpentonMobile.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-126\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/TimeSpentonMobile.jpg\" alt=\"TimeSpentonMobile\" width=\"335\" height=\"310\" /></a>Everyone is trying to figure out how to use mobile to advertise, it is not an easy problem to crack. Think about how you use your phone. First when you pick up your phone you are going to do one of a few things: make or answer a call, search for something or some location, play a game, check a notification, respond to that notification (text, Facebook, tweet, etc)\r\n\r\nSee as an advertiser or an app there is no guarantee that the user is going to interact with your app, utility, or browser based website. There is competition for that time spent.\r\n\r\n<strong>We have found a way to reach our users every time they pick up their phone!</strong>\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/AdoraAdExamples.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright  wp-image-134\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/AdoraAdExamples.jpg\" alt=\"AdoraAdExamples\" width=\"390\" height=\"575\" /></a>Second Point: Real Estate</h2>\r\nThe next problem advertisers find when it comes to mobile, especially on phones, is the amount of space on the screen they get to deliver their message.\r\n\r\nThere are two popular ways of advertising on mobile:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Text Ads</li>\r\n	<li>Banner Ads</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThen you have the Facebook Sponsored Stories, and Twitter Promoted Tweets. Both of these are, in most cases, performing much better than Text and Banner Ads.\r\n\r\nWith the advent of rich media more formats are becoming popular. New applications for traditional advertising are popping up; video, call to actions, slides, and a technique that many brands are trying - subtle advertising - where the brand or product is subtly featured and not featured all at the same time.\r\n\r\nStill with 99% of the advertising opportunities out there the user is using their device to do something other than look at advertising... And those ads have become a turn off. Not only are they a turn off but they often are not maximizing the real estate - not using the entire screen.\r\n<h2>Third Point: A Cause</h2>\r\nOur ads will use the entire screen, we will also make it 100% clear that every time they see an ad they are helping someone in need.\r\n\r\nWe want to make users and brands partners in the effort to get funding to charities.\r\n\r\nBy doing this we put these two parties on the same side, on the same team. This changes the way our users look at the ads we deliver, it encourages brand loyalty, even possibly adoration...','The opportunity for MAD Men (and women!)','','publish','open','open','','the-opportunity-for-mad-men-and-women','','','2014-05-08 00:33:57','2014-05-08 00:33:57','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=119',0,'post','',0),(120,1,'2014-05-02 21:49:57','2014-05-02 21:49:57','','TimeSpentUS','','inherit','open','open','','timespentus','','','2014-05-02 21:49:57','2014-05-02 21:49:57','',119,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TimeSpentUS.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(121,1,'2014-05-02 22:01:28','2014-05-02 22:01:28','We want to more clearly spell out why we feel our ad is going to be the absolute best ad opportunity for brands and the ad agencies that manage them.\r\n<h2>First point: Reach</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TimeSpentUS.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-120\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TimeSpentUS.jpg\" alt=\"TimeSpentUS\" width=\"324\" height=\"321\" /></a>Mobile advertising is the fastest growing sub-sector in the advertising world, and for good reason