ee an ad they are helping someone in need.\n\nWe want to make users and brands partners in the effort to get funding to charities.\n\nBy doing this we put these two parties on the same side, on the same team. This changes the way our users look at the ads we deliver, it encourages brand loyalty, even possi','The opportunity for MAD Men (and women!)','','inherit','open','open','','119-autosave-v1','','','2014-05-05 13:36:41','2014-05-05 13:36:41','',119,'http://getadora.com/119-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(124,1,'2014-05-02 22:16:07','2014-05-02 22:16:07','We want to more clearly spell out why we feel our ad is going to be the absolute best ad opportunity for brands and the ad agencies that manage them.\r\n<h2>First point: Reach</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TimeSpentUS.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-120\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/TimeSpentUS.jpg\" alt=\"TimeSpentUS\" width=\"324\" height=\"321\" /></a>Mobile advertising is the fastest growing sub-sector in the advertising world, and for good reason.\r\n\r\nIf you look at the \'Share of Time Spent per Day with Major Media by US adults, 2010-2014\' you see a trend. First take a look at the change from TV to Digital from 2010-2014. Then take a look inside the digital breakdown, specifically the mobile and online share. It is clear that mobile is where the eyes are and where more are going.\r\n\r\nThis trend will only continue with greater saturation of smartphones, tablets, wearables and who knows what will come out next, but you can be sure it\'s mobile.\r\n\r\nEveryone is trying to figure out how to use mobile to advertise, it is not an easy problem to crack. Think about how you use your phone. First when you pick up your phone you are going to do one of a few things: make or answer a call, search for something or some location, play a game, check a notification, respond to that notification (text, facebook, tweet, etc)','The opport