and subtlety in a youtube video:\r\n<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/2lvRv2mnYLU\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/MobileAdvertisingExamples.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-140\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/MobileAdvertisingExamples.jpg\" alt=\"MobileAdvertisingExamples\" width=\"670\" height=\"3200\" /></a>','Adora Mobile Advertising Report ','','inherit','open','open','','139-revision-v1','','','2014-05-05 14:01:53','2014-05-05 14:01:53','',139,'http://getadora.com/139-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(142,1,'2014-05-05 14:02:48','2014-05-05 14:02:48','&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Adora Mobile Advertising Report: May 2014</h2>\r\nAs we have been preparing and researching the Adora app project we needed to know what the landscape was for mobile advertising.\r\n\r\nOver the last 3 months we\'ve done a great deal of research and while ad rates change constantly we have a fair grasp on current rates and trends.\r\n<h2>Types of Ads</h2>\r\nAs mobile is the fastest growing segment of information use by the public it\'s reasonable that advertisers are following the eyes.\r\n\r\n<strong>Text based ads</strong> like the Google ads you see when you execute a Google search are still a main stay. There are also text based Banner ads.\r\n\r\n<strong>Banner ads</strong> are those nice slim strips of advertising you see at the top and bottom of apps and web pages. They are quickly becoming yesterdays news. The only way they are staying relevant at all is through the innovative use of rich media techniques.\r\n\r\n<strong>Embedded</strong> in app ads like Facebook Sponsored Stories and Twitter Promoted Tweets are examples of this type of ad.\r\n\r\nThen we have the new <strong>Subtlety Techniques</strong> that we are seeing on Instagram and through the use of short videos like Vine. Here is an example of brand subtlety in a youtube video:\r\n<ifram