title=\"Four mobile advertising trends to look out for in 2014\" href=\"http://http://www.theguardian.com/media-network/ebuzzing-partner-zone/mobile-advertising-trends-2014\" target=\"_blank\">\r\nAppFlood - </a><a title=\"10 reasons why your mobile app eCPM is decreasing\" href=\"http://appflood.com/blog/10-ways-app-advertising-ecpm-can-decline\" target=\"_blank\">10 reasons why your mobile app eCPM is decreasing</a></p>','Adora Mobile Advertising Report ','','inherit','open','open','','139-revision-v1','','','2014-05-05 23:24:26','2014-05-05 23:24:26','',139,'http://getadora.com/139-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(147,5,'2014-03-06 00:21:32','2014-03-06 00:21:32','<h2>We needed to stop and think</h2>\r\nAfter the thrill of the idea began to calm we jumped right into research and development of the idea. Then we started to develop the business plan and executive summary and we realized that we needed to stop and think.\r\n\r\nThere is more to a business than just the moving parts, the market, the idea or product.\r\n\r\nStop and think about all the organizations you\'ve been a part of. What made the job fulfilling or taxing?\r\n<h2>The Culture</h2>\r\nNo matter the cause, how good the product is or how much you\'re paid if the culture sucks it will be a short relationship.\r\n\r\nThis is what we needed to think about.\r\n\r\nWhat kind of organization do we want to be? What really is our vision, what is our mission, what kind of culture do we want to have?\r\n<h2>Yes Obviously, But it\'s not so simple</h2>\r\nThinking out loud here (or actually free flow writing but you get it) - The obvious answer is that we want to have a positive culture that fosters improvement, innovation, satisfaction, retention, and all those great buzz words - but isn\'t this what every organization worth its salt wants?\r\n\r\nSo how do we actually create an organization like this?\r\n\r\nOur team is well read on the subject, and even has some experience creating or failing to create the right organizational culture.\r\n\r\nOne of our founders has run into this problem three times before in other organization he was at the head of. The one thing that he kept coming back to, and that he learned the hard way is summed up very simply in this quote -\r\n<blockquote><strong>\"Hire Character, Train Skill\" - Peter Schultz</strong><em>CEO Porsche </em></blockquote>\r\nThe sum an only be any greater than it\'s parts if the parts are great to begin with, true in math, true in life, true in business. If you add, multiply, or in any other way try to make zero (0) any greater than zero you\'ll fail. You have to have something to add it to. The interesting thing is that if you multiply a number by zero you get zero, and as we\'ve seen time and time again if you have someone on your team or in your organization that is a zero or a negative  contributor when you look at your culture they will drag everyone and everything else down with you.\r\n\r\nIf you are a large enough organization you may be able to rehabilitate some of these talented but culturally destructive individuals but even then it\'s hard to teach character. Skills can be improved and amazingly when you find great people they often want to improve, they are humble and driven.\r\n\r\nSo without going into the fluffy words you find in mission &amp; vision statements we\'ll just start with this statement -\r\n<blockquote>\"Here at Adora we want to find great people and those great people will make our desire for an amazing culture possible!\"</blockquote>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://watercoolernewsletter.com/wp-content/files_mf/corporateculturesuccess.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2000\" height=\"864\" />','Stop and Think...','','publish','open','open','','stop-think','','','2014-05-08 00:33:46','2014-05-08 00:33:46','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=147',0,'post','',0),(148,1,'2014-05-06 00:21:32','2014-05-06 00:21:32','<h2>We needed to stop and think</h2>\r\nAfter the thrill of the idea began to calm we jumped right into research and development of the idea. Then we started to develop the business plan and executive summary and we realized that we needed to stop and think.\r\n\r\nThere is more to a business than just the moving parts, the market, the idea or product.\r\n\r\nStop and think about all the organizations you\'ve been a part of. What made the job fulfilling or taxing?\r\n<h2>The Culture</h2>\r\nNo matter the cause, how good the product is or how much you\'re paid if the culture sucks it will be a short relationship.\r\n\r\nThis is what we needed to think about.\r\n\r\nWhat kind of organization do we want to be? What really is our vision, what is our mission, what kind of culture do we want to have?\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://watercoolernewsletter.com/wp-content/files_mf/corporateculturesuccess.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2000\" height=\"864\" />','Stop and Think...','','inherit','open','open','','147-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 00:21:32','2014-05-06 00:21:32','',147,'http://getadora.com/147-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(149,1,'2014-05-06 00:49:38','2014-05-06 00:49:38','<h2>We needed to stop and think</h2>\nAfter the thrill of the idea began to calm we jumped right into research and development of the idea. Then we started to develop the business plan and executive summary and we realized that we needed to stop and think.\n\nThere is more to a business than just the moving parts, the market, the idea or product.\n\nStop and think about all the organizations you\'ve been a part of. What made the job fulfilling or taxing?\n<h2>The Culture</h2>\nNo matter the cause, how good the product is or how much you\'re paid if the culture sucks it will be a short relationship.\n\nThis is what we needed to think about.\n\nWhat kind of organization do we want to be? What really is our vision, what is our mission, what kind of culture do we want to have?\n<h2>Yes Obviously, But it\'s not so simple</h2>\nThinking out loud here (or actually free flow writing but you get it) - The obvious answer is that we want to have a positive culture that fosters improvement, innovation, satisfaction, retention, and all those great buzz words - but isn\'t this what every organization worth its salt wants?\n\nSo how do we actually create an organization like this?\n\nOur team is well read on the subject, and even has some experience creating or failing to create the right organizational culture.\n\nOne of our founders has run into this problem three times before in other organization he was at the head of. The one thing that he kept coming back to, and that he learned the hard way is summed up very simply in this quote -\n<blockquote><strong>\"Hire Character, Train Skill\" - Peter Schultz</strong><em>CEO Porsche </em></blockquote>\nThe sum an only be any greater than it\'s parts if the parts are great to begin with, true in math, true in life, true in business. If you add, multiply, or in any other way try to make zero (0) any greater than zero you\'ll fail. You have to have something to add it to. The interesting thing is that if you multiply a number by zero you get zero, and as we\'ve seen time and time again if you have someone on your team or in your organization that is a zero or a negative  contributor when you look at your culture they will drag everyone and everything else down with you.\n\nIf you are a large enough organization you may be able to rehabilitate some of these talented but culturally destructive individuals but even then it\'s hard to teach character. Skills can be improved and amazingly when you find great people they often want to improve, they are humble and driven.\n\nSo without going into the fluffy words you find in mission &amp; vision statements we\'ll just start with this statement -\n<blockquote>Here at Adora we want to find great people and those great people will make our desire for an amazing culture possible!</blockquote>\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://watercoolernewsletter.com/wp-content/files_mf/corporateculturesuccess.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2000\" height=\"864\" />','Stop and Think...','','inherit','open','open','','147-autosave-v1','','','2014-05-06 00:49:38','2014-05-06 00:49:38','',147,'http://getadora.com/147-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(150,1,'2014-05-06 00:37:01','2014-05-06 00:37:01','<h2>We needed to stop and think</h2>\r\nAfter the thrill of the idea began to calm we jumped right into research and development of the idea. Then we started to develop the business plan and executive summary and we realized that we needed to stop and think.\r\n\r\nThere is more to a business than just the moving parts, the market, the idea or product.\r\n\r\nStop and think about all the organizations you\'ve been a part of. What made the job fulfilling or taxing?\r\n<h2>The Culture</h2>\r\nNo matter the cause, how good the product is or how much you\'re paid if the culture sucks it will be a short relationship.\r\n\r\nThis is what we needed to think about.\r\n\r\nWhat kind of organization do we want to be? What really is our vision, what is our mission, what kind of culture do we want to have?\r\n<h2>Yes Obviously, But it\'s not so simple</h2>\r\nThinking out loud here (or actually free flow writing but you get it) - The obvious answer is that we want to have a positive culture that fosters improvement, innovation, satisfaction, retention, and all those great buzz words - but isn\'t this what every organization worth its salt wants?\r\n\r\nSo how do we actually create an organization like this?\r\n\r\nOur team is well read on the subject, and even has some experience creating or failing to create the right organizational culture.\r\n\r\nOne of our founders has run into this problem three times before in other organization he was at the head of. The one thing that he kept coming back to, and that he learned the hard way is summed up very simply in this quote -\r\n<blockquote><strong>\"Hire Character, Train Skill\" - Peter Schultz</strong> <em>CEO Porsche </em></blockquote>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://watercoolernewsletter.com/wp-content/files_mf/corporateculturesuccess.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2000\" height=\"864\" />','Stop and Think...','','inherit','open','open','','147-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 00:37:01','2014-05-06 00:37:01','',147,'http://getadora.com/147-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(151,1,'2014-05-06 00:49:50','2014-05-06 00:49:50','<h2>We needed to stop and think</h2>\r\nAfter the thrill of the idea began to calm we jumped right into research and development of the idea. Then we started to develop the business plan and executive summary and we realized that we needed to stop and think.\r\n\r\nThere is more to a business than just the moving parts, the market, the idea or product.\r\n\r\nStop and think about all the organizations you\'ve been a part of. What made the job fulfilling or taxing?\r\n<h2>The Culture</h2>\r\nNo matter the cause, how good the product is or how much you\'re paid if the culture sucks it will be a short relationship.\r\n\r\nThis is what we needed to think about.\r\n\r\nWhat kind of organization do we want to be? What really is our vision, what is our mission, what kind of culture do we want to have?\r\n<h2>Yes Obviously, But it\'s not so simple</h2>\r\nThinking out loud here (or actually free flow writing but you get it) - The obvious answer is that we want to have a positive culture that fosters improvement, innovation, satisfaction, retention, and all those great buzz words - but isn\'t this what every organization worth its salt wants?\r\n\r\nSo how do we actually create an organization like this?\r\n\r\nOur team is well read on the subject, and even has some experience creating or failing to create the right organizational culture.\r\n\r\nOne of our founders has run into this problem three times before in other organization he was at the head of. The one thing that he kept coming back to, and that he learned the hard way is summed up very simply in this quote -\r\n<blockquote><strong>\"Hire Character, Train Skill\" - Peter Schultz</strong><em>CEO Porsche </em></blockquote>\r\nThe sum an only be any greater than it\'s parts if the parts are great to begin with, true in math, true in life, true in business. If you add, multiply, or in any other way try to make zero (0) any greater than zero you\'ll fail. You have to have something to add it to. The interesting thing is that if you multiply a number by zero you get zero, and as we\'ve seen time and time again if you have someone on your team or in your organization that is a zero or a negative  contributor when you look at your culture they will drag everyone and everything else down with you.\r\n\r\nIf you are a large enough organization you may be able to rehabilitate some of these talented but culturally destructive individuals but even then it\'s hard to teach character. Skills can be improved and amazingly when you find great people they often want to improve, they are humble and driven.\r\n\r\nSo without going into the fluffy words you find in mission &amp; vision statements we\'ll just start with this statement -\r\n<blockquote>\"Here at Adora we want to find great people and those great people will make our desire for an amazing culture possible!\"</blockquote>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://watercoolernewsletter.com/wp-content/files_mf/corporateculturesuccess.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2000\" height=\"864\" />','Stop and Think...','','inherit','open','open','','147-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 00:49:50','2014-05-06 00:49:50','',147,'http://getadora.com/147-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(152,5,'2014-03-10 01:24:04','2014-03-10 01:24:04','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-153\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins-300x208.jpg\" alt=\"JimCollins\" width=\"300\" height=\"208\" /></a>Ok we have a confession to make - we have a little crush on Jim. If you don\'t know who he his then you need to buy <a title=\"Purchase Good to Great on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Good-Great-Some-Companies-Others/dp/0066620996/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338240&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+-+good+to+great\" target=\"_blank\">Good to Great</a>, and <a title=\"Purchase Built to Last on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Built-Last-Successful-Visionary-Essentials/dp/0060516402/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338302&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+built+to+last\" target=\"_blank\">Built to Last</a>, and even <a title=\"Purchase Great by Choice on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Great-Choice-Uncertainty-Luck--Why-Despite/dp/0062120999/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338319&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+great+by+choice\" target=\"_blank\">Great by Choice</a> and get to know his work.\r\n\r\nOne of the things we love about him is the fact that he is fact driven, data driven, research driven. He might have an opinion or not like the direction research takes him but he still lets the research and data teach him. he also builds teams to get more done in less time and in all reality that is all a business is - a team trying to get more done than one person can by his or her self.\r\n\r\nHe talks about things like the bus, BHAGS, discipline, hedgehogs, brutal facts, tyranny of the word \'or\', home grown management, clock building/time telling, and a host of other great facts that he has uncovered through research into some of the best companies.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be posting a bunch of little stories about us within the framework of some of the revelations from Jim\'s research.\r\n\r\nThings like:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"The Bus\" href=\"http://getadora.com/bus/\">Our Bus</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"The meaning of being a hedgehog\" href=\"http://getadora.com/hedgehog-concept/\">How we\'re going to be like a hedgehog</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"BHAG\" href=\"http://getadora.com/bhag/\">Our BHAG</a></p>\r\n We have many other influences and we\'ll write about them too. People like Randy Pausch, Micheal Gerber, Malcolm Gladwell, Peter Drucker, Stephen Covey and we could go on and on. As we go we\'ll talk ab out each one, what we\'ve learned and what we want to make part of what we are building here at Adora.','A love for Jim Collins','','publish','open','open','','love-jim-collins','','http://getadora.com/bus/\nhttp://getadora.com/bhag/\nhttp://getadora.com/hedgehog-concept/','2014-05-08 01:42:41','2014-05-08 01:42:41','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=152',0,'post','',0),(153,1,'2014-05-06 01:23:53','2014-05-06 01:23:53','','JimCollins','','inherit','open','open','','jimcollins','','','2014-05-06 01:23:53','2014-05-06 01:23:53','',152,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(154,1,'2014-05-06 01:24:04','2014-05-06 01:24:04','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-153\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins-300x208.jpg\" alt=\"JimCollins\" width=\"300\" height=\"208\" /></a>Ok we have a confession to make - we have a little crush on Jim. If you don\'t know who he his then you need to buy <a title=\"Purchase Good to Great on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Good-Great-Some-Companies-Others/dp/0066620996/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338240&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+-+good+to+great\" target=\"_blank\">Good to Great</a>, and <a title=\"Purchase Built to Last on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Built-Last-Successful-Visionary-Essentials/dp/0060516402/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338302&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+built+to+last\" target=\"_blank\">Built to Last</a>, and even <a title=\"Purchase Great by Choice on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Great-Choice-Uncertainty-Luck--Why-Despite/dp/0062120999/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338319&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+great+by+choice\" target=\"_blank\">Great by Choice</a> and get to know him.\r\n\r\nOne of the things we love about him is the fact that he is fact driven, data driven, research driven. He might have an opinion or not like the direction research takes him but he still lets the research and data teach him. he also builds teams to get more done in less time and in all reality that is all a business is - a team trying to get more done than one person can by his or her self.\r\n\r\nHe talks about things like the bus, BHAGS, discipline, hedgehogs, brutal facts, tyranny of the word \'or\', home grown management, clock building/time telling, and a host of other great facts that he has uncovered through research into some of the best companies.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be posting a bunch of little stories about us within the framework of some of the revelations from Jim\'s research.\r\n\r\nThings like:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Our BHAG</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Our Bus</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">How we\'re going to be like a hedgehog</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','A love for Jim Collins','','inherit','open','open','','152-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 01:24:04','2014-05-06 01:24:04','',152,'http://getadora.com/152-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(155,1,'2014-05-06 01:24:58','2014-05-06 01:24:58','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-153\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins-300x208.jpg\" alt=\"JimCollins\" width=\"300\" height=\"208\" /></a>Ok we have a confession to make - we have a little crush on Jim. If you don\'t know who he his then you need to buy <a title=\"Purchase Good to Great on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Good-Great-Some-Companies-Others/dp/0066620996/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338240&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+-+good+to+g