nt, clock building/time telling, and a host of other great facts that he has uncovered through research into some of the best companies.</p>\r\n<p>We\'ll be posting a bunch of little stories about us within the framework of some of the revelations from Jim\'s research.</p>\r\n<p>Things like:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"The Bus\" href=\"http://getadora.com/bus/\">Our Bus</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Our BHAG</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">How we\'re going to be like a hedgehog</p>\r\n<p> We have many other influences and we\'ll write about them too. People like Randy Pausch, Micheal Gerber, Malcolm Gladwell, Peter Drucker, Stephen Covey and we could go on and on. As we go we\'ll talk ab out each one, what we\'ve learned and what we want to make part of what we are building here at Adora.</p>\r\n','A love for Jim Collins','','inherit','open','open','','152-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 01:59:36','2014-05-06 01:59:36','',152,'http://getadora.com/152-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(171,1,'2014-05-06 08:28:49','2014-05-06 08:28:49','<h2><img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://www.jubelirerresultsgroup.com/wp-content/themes/striking/cache/images/285_bhag-628x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"628\" height=\"250\" />What in the world is a BHAG?</h2>\r\nA Big Hairy Audacious Goal\r\n\r\nWhy is it important?\r\n\r\nWell we all know how important goals are but just how important is it to have a defining, driving, motivating, all encompassing goal?\r\n\r\nSounds pretty clear when you talk it out.\r\n\r\nWhen you can, as an organization, identify a goal that helps guide all the actions and motivations of every individual you touch you transcend the fluff.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','BHAG','','inherit','open','open','','170-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 08:28:49','2014-05-06 08:28:49','',170,'http://getadora.com/170-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(172,1,'2014-05-06 08:29:10','2014-05-06 08:29:10','<h2><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.jubelirerresultsgroup.com/wp-content/themes/striking/cache/images/285_bhag-628x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"628\" height=\"250\" />What in the world is a BHAG?</h2>\r\nA Big Hairy Audacious Goal\r\n\r\nWhy is it important?\r\n\r\nWell we all know how important goals are but just how important is it to have a defining, driving, motivating, all encompassing goal?\r\n\r\nSounds pretty clear when you talk it out.\r\n\r\nWhen you can, as an organization, identify a goal that helps guide all the actions and motivations of every individual you touch you transcend the fluff.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','BHAG','','inherit','open','open','','170-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 08:29:10','2014-05-06 08:29:10','',170,'http://getadora.com/170-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(173,1,'2014-05-08 12:36:06','2014-05-08 12:36:06','<h2><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.jubelirerresultsgroup.com/wp-content/themes/striking/cache/images/285_bhag-628x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"628\" height=\"250\" />What in the world is a BHAG?</h2>\nA Big Hairy Audacious Goal\n\nWhy is it important?\n\nWell we all know how important goals are but just how important is it to have a defining, driving, motivating, all encompassing goal?\n\nSounds pretty clear when you talk it out.\n\nWhen you can, as an organization, identify a goal that helps guide all the actions and motivations of every individual you touch you transcend the fluff.\n\nOur BHAG follows our Vision - To become the most charitable company in the world.','BHAG','','inherit','open','open','','170-autosave-v1','','','2014-05-08 12:36:06','2014-05-08 12:36:06','',170,'http://getadora.com/170-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(174,1,'2014-05-06 08:30:20','2014-05-06 08:30:20','<h2><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.jubelirerresultsgroup.com/wp-content/themes/striking/cache/images/285_bhag-628x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"628\" height=\"250\" />What in the world is a BHAG?</h2>\r\nA Big Hairy Audacious Goal\r\n\r\nWhy is it important?\r\n\r\nWell we all know how important goals are but just how important is it to have a defining, driving, motivating, all encompassing goal?\r\n\r\nSounds pretty clear when you talk it out.\r\n\r\nWhen you can, as an organization, identify a goal that helps guide all the actions and motivations of every individual you touch you transcend the fluff.\r\n\r\nWe need to find ours, we don\'t know how big it is but we know it revolves around doing good.','BHAG','','inherit','open','open','','170-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 08:30:20','2014-05-06 08:30:20','',170,'http://getadora.com/170-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(175,5,'2014-03-13 08:55:17','2014-03-13 08:55:17','<h2><img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://static.squarespace.com/static/50a4135ee4b072e097b39f24/51d74170e4b045cd478c90fb/51d74171e4b045cd478c913d/1330722859000/FoxHedge-Logo.png?format=original\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" />The Hedgehog and the Fox</h2>\r\nIn the book Good to Great Jim talks about the difference between the fox and the hedgehog.\r\n\r\nSee a fox is a very creative creature and that is a really great thing BUT the foxes success rate is very hit or miss as he rarely does the same thing twice to achieve his goal so he doesn\'t become great at any one method of finding or catching food.\r\n\r\nThen we have a hedgehog, he is pretty conservative, not interested in what the fox has in store for him so goes about his day and when the fox decides to jump out of what ever new hiding place or sneak attack he\'s come up with the hedgehog does his thing and he does it well.\r\n\r\nThat little rolled up creature frustrates that fox and he goes back to the drawing board.\r\n\r\nBeing creative is great, but finding greatness is priceless. So the moral of the story?\r\n\r\nFind the focus and let that guide you.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://innovaciondelsur.files.wordpress.com/2012/02/good-to-great-hedgehog1-e1329250539816.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"382\" height=\"359\" />For us we need to find our focus and we can best do that by developing a clear hedgehog concept:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>What we are passionate about?</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>What can we be the best in the world at?</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>What drives our Economic engine?</strong></p>\r\nWhen we talk a bout passion it is easy to go on and on, the trick is to come up with a statement that is clear, broad, and galvanizing. It needs to elicit an emotional response in every individual in the company and if it doesn\'t they might not be a great fit.\r\n\r\nStating that you can be the best in the world at anything boarders on hubris and it can come off as arrogant if we are not careful. This should support not contradict or confuse with regards to our stated passion.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to economic engine this is purely statistical, it is a measurement or metric. Think Profit per something, revenue per something, cost per something. Find this and let that guide your every financial decision.','The meaning of being a hedgehog','','publish','open','open','','hedgehog-concept','','','2014-05-08 01:39:53','2014-05-08 01:39:53','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=175',0,'post','',0),(176,1,'2014-05-06 08:55:17','2014-05-06 08:55:17','<h2><img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://static.squarespace.com/static/50a4135ee4b072e097b39f24/51d74170e4b045cd478c90fb/51d74171e4b045cd478c913d/1330722859000/FoxHedge-Logo.png?format=original\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" />The Hedgehog and the Fox</h2>\r\nIn the book Good to Great Jim talks about the difference between the fox and the hedgehog.\r\n\r\nSee a fox is a very creative creature and that is a really great thing BUT the foxes success rate is very hit or miss as he rarely does the same thing twice to achieve his goal so he doesn\'t become great at any one method of finding or catching food.\r\n\r\nThen we have a hedgehog, he is pretty conservative, not interested in what the fox has in store for him so goes about his day and when the fox decides to jump out of what ever new hiding place or sneak attack he\'s come up with the hedgehog does his thing and he does it well.\r\n\r\nThat little rolled up creature frustrates that fox and he goes back to the drawing board.\r\n\r\nBeing creative is great, but finding greatness is priceless. So the moral of the story?\r\n\r\nFind the focus and let that guide you.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://innovaciondelsur.files.wordpress.com/2012/02/good-to-great-hedgehog1-e1329250539816.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"382\" height=\"359\" />For us we need to find our focus and we can best do that by developing a clear hedgehog concept:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>What we we passionate about?</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>What can we be the best in the world at?</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>What drives our Economic engine?</strong></p>\r\nPassion','The meaning of being a hedgehog','','inherit','open','open','','175-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 08:55:17','2014-05-06 08:55:17','',175,'http://getadora.com/175-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(177,1,'2014-05-06 08:56:38','2014-05-06 08:56:38','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-153\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins-300x208.jpg\" alt=\"JimCollins\" width=\"300\" height=\"208\" /></a>Ok we have a confession to make - we have a little crush on Jim. If you don\'t know who he his then you need to buy <a title=\"Purchase Good to Great on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Good-Great-Some-Companies-Others/dp/0066620996/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338240&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+-+good+to+great\" target=\"_blank\">Good to Great</a>, and <a title=\"Purchase Built to Last on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Built-Last-Successful-Visionary-Essentials/dp/0060516402/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338302&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+built+to+last\" target=\"_blank\">Built to Last</a>, and even <a title=\"Purchase Great by Choice on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Great-Choice-Uncertainty-Luck--Why-Despite/dp/0062120999/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338319&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+great+by+choice\" target=\"_blank\">Great by Choice</a> and get to know his work.\r\n\r\nOne of the things we love about him is the fact that he is fact driven, data driven, research driven. He might have an opinion or not like the direction research takes him but he still lets the research and data teach him. he also builds teams to get more done in less time and in all reality that is all a business is - a team trying to get more done than one person can by his or her self.\r\n\r\nHe talks about things like the bus, BHAGS, discipline, hedgehogs, brutal facts, tyranny of the word \'or\', home grown management, clock building/time telling, and a host of other great facts that he has uncovered through research into some of the best companies.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be posting a bunch of little stories about us within the framework of some of the revelations from Jim\'s research.\r\n\r\nThings like:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"The Bus\" href=\"http://getadora.com/bus/\">Our Bus</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"BHAG\" href=\"http://getadora.com/bhag/\">Our BHAG</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">How we\'re going to be like a hedgehog</p>\r\n We have many other influences and we\'ll write about them too. People like Randy Pausch, Micheal Gerber, Malcolm Gladwell, Peter Drucker, Stephen Covey and we could go on and on. As we go we\'ll talk ab out each one, what we\'ve learned and what we want to make part of what we are building here at Adora.','A love for Jim Collins','','inherit','open','open','','152-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 08:56:38','2014-05-06 08:56:38','',152,'http://getadora.com/152-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(178,1,'2014-05-06 08:56:56','2014-05-06 08:56:56','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-153\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JimCollins-300x208.jpg\" alt=\"JimCollins\" width=\"300\" height=\"208\" /></a>Ok we have a confession to make - we have a little crush on Jim. If you don\'t know who he his then you need to buy <a title=\"Purchase Good to Great on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Good-Great-Some-Companies-Others/dp/0066620996/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338240&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+-+good+to+great\" target=\"_blank\">Good to Great</a>, and <a title=\"Purchase Built to Last on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Built-Last-Successful-Visionary-Essentials/dp/0060516402/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338302&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+built+to+last\" target=\"_blank\">Built to Last</a>, and even <a title=\"Purchase Great by Choice on Amazon\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Great-Choice-Uncertainty-Luck--Why-Despite/dp/0062120999/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1399338319&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=jim+collins+great+by+choice\" target=\"_blank\">Great by Choice</a> and get to know his work.\r\n\r\nOne of the things we love about him is the fact that he is fact driven, data driven, research driven. He might have an opinion or not like the direction research takes him but he still lets the research and data teach him. he also builds teams to get more done in less time and in all reality that is all a business is - a team trying to get more done than one person can by his or her self.\r\n\r\nHe talks about things like the bus, BHAGS, discipline, hedgehogs, brutal facts, tyranny of the word \'or\', home grown management, clock building/time telling, and a host of other great facts that he has uncovered through research into some of the best companies.\r\n\r\nWe\'ll be posting a bunch of little stories about us within the framework of some of the revelations from Jim\'s research.\r\n\r\nThings like:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"The Bus\" href=\"http://getadora.com/bus/\">Our Bus</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"BHAG\" href=\"http://getadora.com/bhag/\">Our BHAG</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a title=\"The meaning of being a hedgehog\" href=\"http://getadora.com/hedgehog-concept/\">How we\'re going to be like a hedgehog</a></p>\r\n We have many other influences and we\'ll write about them too. People like Randy Pausch, Micheal Gerber, Malcolm Gladwell, Peter Drucker, Stephen Covey and we could go on and on. As we go we\'ll talk ab out each one, what we\'ve learned and what we want to make part of what we are building here at Adora.','A love for Jim Collins','','inherit','open','open','','152-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 08:56:56','2014-05-06 08:56:56','',152,'http://getadora.com/152-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(350,1,'2014-05-15 14:06:58','2014-05-15 14:06:58','','WebLogoWhite','','inherit','open','open','','weblogowhite','','','2014-05-15 14:06:58','2014-05-15 14:06:58','',1,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/WebLogoWhite.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(181,1,'2014-05-06 13:40:11','2014-05-06 13:40:11','<h2> Adora Mobile Advertising Report: May 2014</h2>\r\nAs we have been preparing and researching the Adora app project we needed to know what the landscape was for mobile advertising.\r\n\r\nOver the last 3 months we\'ve done a great deal of research and while ad rates change constantly we have a fair grasp on current rates and trends.\r\n<h2>Types of Ads</h2>\r\nAs mobile is the fastest growing segment of information use by the public it\'s reasonable that advertisers are following the eyes.\r\n\r\n<strong>Text based ads</strong> like the Google ads you see when you execute a Google search are still a main stay. There are also text based Banner ads.\r\n\r\n<strong>Banner ads</strong> are those nice slim strips of advertising you see at the top and bottom of apps and web pages. They are quickly becoming yesterdays news, the Yahoo ad network is already phasing them out. The only way they are staying relevant at all is through the innovative use of rich media techniques.\r\n\r\n<strong>Embedded</strong> in app ads like Facebook Sponsored Stories and Twitter Promoted Tweets are examples of this type of ad.\r\n\r\nThen we have the new <strong>Subtlety Techniques</strong> that we are seeing on Instagram and through the use of short videos like Vine. Here is an example of brand subtlety in a youtube video:\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/2lvRv2mnYLU\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n\r\nThen we start to get into larger formats, <strong>full screen ads and full screen video players</strong> with interactive options. These must pop up or be part of a loading screen for apps, sites, or utilities to use these full screen ads. They are great use of real estate but some of the most annoying to users.\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/MobileAdvertisingExamples.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-140\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/MobileAdvertisingExamples.jpg\" alt=\"MobileAdvertisingExamples\" width=\"562\" height=\"2684\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nReferences:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>General Mobile CPM</strong>\r\n<a title=\"Top Performing CPM Zones\" href=\"http://buysellads.com/buy/leaderboard/id/17/soldout/1/ch/-1\" target=\"_blank\">Buy Sell Ads Leaderboard\r\n</a><a title=\"What Are Average CPM Rates in 2014?\" href=\"http://monetizepros.com/blog/2014/average-cpm-rates/\" target=\"_blank\">MonetizePros Average CPM Rates 2014\r\n</a><a title=\"What Is an Average Banner CPM?\" href=\"http://www.ehow.com/info_12200588_average-banner-cpm.html\" target=\"_blank\">eHow - What Is an Average Banner CPM?</a><a title=\"What Are Average CPM Rates in 2014?\" href=\"http://monetizepros.com/blog/2014/average-cpm-rates/\" target=\"_blank\">\r\n</a><a title=\"The Average CPM Rates for Mobile Advertising\" href=\"http://smallbusiness.chron.com/average-cpm-rates-mobile-advertising-72201.html\" target=\"_blank\">Chron Small Business - The Average CPM Rates for Mobile Advertising\r\n</a><a title=\"2014 Forecasts: Global Ad Dollars Surge, Driven By Mobile, Social\" href=\"http://http://www.adexchanger.com/agencies/2014-forecasts-global-ad-dollars-surge-driven-by-mobile-social/\" target=\"_blank\">Ad Exchanger - 2014 Forecasts: Global Ad Dollars Surge, Driven By Mobile, Social\r\n</a><a title=\"The Mobile Ad Network Roundup\" href=\"http://blog.apptopia.com/the-mobile-ad-network-rundown/\" target=\"_blank\">Apptopia - The Mobile Ad Network Roundup</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>Facebook &amp; Twitter CPM Resources\r\n</strong><a title=\"Know Your Facebook Ad Rates: CPM and Cost Per Page Like by Placement\" href=\"http://www.jonloomer.com/2014/04/28/facebook-ad-rates-placement/\" target=\"_blank\">Jon Loomer - Know Your Facebook Ad Rates: CPM and Cost Per Page Like by Placement\r\n</a><a title=\"Facebook Mobile App Install Ads Capture Revenue, Drive Installs\" href=\"http://http://www.adexchanger.com/mobile/facebook-mobile-app-install-ads-capture-revenue-drive-installs/\" target=\"_blank\">Ad Exchanger - Facebook Mobile App Install Ads Capture Revenue, Drive Installs\r\n</a><a title=\"Hey Twitter, Your Ads Are Even Worse Than Facebook\'s — Here\'s The Data\" href=\"http://https://finance.yahoo.com/news/hey-twitter-ads-even-worse-195743153.html\" target=\"_blank\">Yahoo - Hey Twitter, Your Ads Are Even Worse Than Facebook\'s — Here\'s The Data\r\n</a><a title=\"Twitter Investment Thesis\" href=\"http://www.slideshare.net/augustinefou/investment-thesis-twitter-by-augustine-fou-april-2014\" target=\"_blank\">Slideshare - Twitter Investment Thesis</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>Mobile Video CPM Resources</strong>\r\n<a title=\"Online Video Advertising Moves Front and Center\" href=\"http://www.emarketer.com/Article/Online-Video-Advertising-Moves-Front-Center/1009886\" target=\"_blank\">eMarketer - Online Video Advertising Moves Front and Center</a> (Digital Video Ad Spending, 2011-2017)\r\n<a title=\"3 Reasons Brands Shouldn’t be Surprised Online Video Ads Out-Price TV Spots\" href=\"https://smallbusiness.yahoo.com/advisor/3-reasons-brands-shouldn-t-surprised-online-video-154514773.html\" target=\"_blank\">Yahoo - 3 Reasons Brands Shouldn’t be Surprised Online Video Ads Out-Price TV Spots</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>Trends\r\n</strong><a title=\"Four mobile advertising trends to look out for in 2014\" href=\"http://http://www.theguardian.com/media-network/ebuzzing-partner-zone/mobile-advertising-trends-2014\" target=\"_blank\">The Guardian - </a><a title=\"Four mobile advertising trends to look out for in 2014\" href=\"http://http://www.theguardian.com/media-network/ebuzzing-partner-zone/mobile-advertising-trends-2014\" target=\"_blank\">Four mobile advertising trends to look out for in 2014</a><a title=\"Four mobile advertising trends to look out for in 2014\" href=\"http://http://www.theguardian.com/media-network/ebuzzing-partner-zone/mobile-advertising-trends-2014\" target=\"_blank\">\r\nAppFlood - </a><a title=\"10 reasons why your mobile app eCPM is decreasing\" href=\"http://appflood.com/blog/10-ways-app-advertising-ecpm-can-decline\" target=\"_blank\">10 reasons why your mobile app eCPM is decreasing</a></p>','Adora Mobile Advertising Report','','inherit','open','open','','139-revision-v1','','','2014-05-06 13:40:11','2014-05-06 13:40:11','',139,'http://getadora.com/139-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(182,1,'2014-05-07 00:49:06','2014-05-07 00:49:06','','SeaGreenFavconPNG','','inherit','open','open','','seagreenfavconpng','','','2014-05-07 00:49:06','2014-05-07 00:49:06',''