</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mobile Ad Revenue (Billions):\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2012 - $8.76</li>\r\n	<li>2013 - $17.96</li>\r\n	<li>2014 - $<em>31.45 (estimate)</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you could create an app which takes advantage of all of these factors, you could deliver ads to users in a way which creates great value to everyone involved.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur app does just this.\r\n\r\nOur marketing plan will allow us to gain significant user acceptance. By partnering with strategic organizations, charities, carriers, and other large companies we can hit our first goal of 1% of the smartphone users (1.75 million users) by the end of 2014.\r\n\r\nThat would bring in a mind blowing $54 million per month in revenues.\r\n<h4>And this is not even the best part of the app - the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side can work.</a></h4>\r\n<h4>If you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></h4>','Adora app','','inherit','open','open','','60-revision-v1','','','2014-05-08 12:06:38','2014-05-08 12:06:38','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(241,1,'2014-05-08 12:12:30','2014-05-08 12:12:30','<h2><strong>Our app is simple</strong></h2>\r\nRight now many of us are doing one specific thing over and over again, and more than likely you will do this one thing a few times as you read this. We want to take that one action and turn it into a way for businesses, large and small, to reach you and everyone else in the world. The focus of the app is to deliver ads to mobile users, using this unique delivery opportunity.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\"><img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"338\" height=\"166\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhat we do with the advertising revenue is what sets us apart.\r\n\r\n<strong>Our mission</strong> is simple:\r\n\r\n<strong>↑User Engagement → ↑Ad Revenue→ ↑Charitable Giving</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Translation -</strong> Our mission is to dramatically increase user engagement with brands thus increasing our value to advertisers and therefore increasing our ability to contribute to organizations who do good.\r\n\r\nThis is our passion - To do as much good as we possibly can.\r\n\r\nThis brings us to <strong>Our Vision:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>It is our goal to be the most charitable company in the world within then next 5 years.</strong>\r\n\r\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such an outlandish goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of 0.8% of pre-tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%. Walmart has lead the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo taking 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account Pfizer has taken the top spot for the last 4 years.\r\n\r\nWe know that these are very large companies but one of our goals is to get to the point where we are donating more than 50% of our pre-tax profits to good causes. We get to this point and how much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\r\n<h2><strong>Google, Facebook, Twitter and all the rest.</strong></h2>\r\nRight now the top online advertising outlets are all trying to capture their piece of the pie, but they do it by offering something else. That something else comes with a lot of distractions, content, and anywhere from 5-12 or even more advertisements--competition. They want to provide value to increase user engagement, but they also want users to interact with the advertising. It is a difficult balance.\r\n\r\nWe want to help fill a void that has little to no competition, does not have distracting content, and is straightforward. We are going to deliver ads to you, and you are going to love it, use it all the time and soon life won\'t be the same with out us.\r\n\r\nHere are some important stats:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"547\"]<a href=\"http://83-136-248-155.uk-lon1.host.upcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-08-at-10-8-9.41.00-PM.png\"><img src=\"http://83-136-248-155.uk-lon1.host.upcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-08-at-10-8-9.41.00-PM.png\" alt=\"US Smartphone Growth Projections\" width=\"547\" height=\"467\" /></a> Smartphone Growth[/caption]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The US alone will be rapidly approaching 200 million smartphones in use by the 2014 holiday season</li>\r\n	<li>Users wake up their phones over <a title=\"HTC One M8 Review and Research\" href=\"https://www.yahoo.com/tech/heres-why-people-are-so-excited-about-the-new-htc-one-80913367177.html\" target=\"_blank\">150 times a day</a> - We are using our phones for everything now.</li>\r\n	<li>Mobile Advertising revenue is going to continue to grow as more and more time is spent on mobile platforms</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mobile Ad Revenue (Billions):\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2012 - $8.76</li>\r\n	<li>2013 - $17.96</li>\r\n	<li>2014 - $<em>31.45 (estimate)</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you could create an app which takes advantage of all of these factors, you could deliver ads to users in a way which creates great value to everyone involved.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur app does just this.\r\n\r\nOur marketing plan will allow us to gain significant user acceptance. By partnering with strategic organizations, charities, carriers, and other large companies we can hit our first goal of 1% of the smartphone users (1.75 million users) by the end of 2014.\r\n\r\nThat would bring in a mind blowing $54 million per month in revenues.\r\n<h4>And this is not even the best part of the app - the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side can work.</a></h4>\r\n<h4>If you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></h4>','The app','','inherit','open','open','','60-revision-v1','','','2014-05-08 12:12:30','2014-05-08 12:12:30','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(242,1,'2014-05-08 12:12:49','2014-05-08 12:12:49','<h2><strong>It\'s simple</strong></h2>\r\nRight now many of us are doing one specific thing over and over again, and more than likely you will do this one thing a few times as you read this. We want to take that one action and turn it into a way for businesses, large and small, to reach you and everyone else in the world. The focus of the app is to deliver ads to mobile users, using this unique delivery opportunity.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\"><img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"338\" height=\"166\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhat we do with the advertising revenue is what sets us apart.\r\n\r\n<strong>Our mission</strong> is simple:\r\n\r\n<strong>↑User Engagement → ↑Ad Revenue→ ↑Charitable Giving</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Translation -</strong> Our mission is to dramatically increase user engagement with brands thus increasing our value to advertisers and therefore increasing our ability to contribute to organizations who do good.\r\n\r\nThis is our passion - To do as much good as we possibly can.\r\n\r\nThis brings us to <strong>Our Vision:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>It is our goal to be the most charitable company in the world within then next 5 years.</strong>\r\n\r\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such an outlandish goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of 0.8% of pre-tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%. Walmart has lead the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo taking 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account Pfizer has taken the top spot for the last 4 years.\r\n\r\nWe know that these are very large companies but one of our goals is to get to the point where we are donating more than 50% of our pre-tax profits to good causes. We get to this point and how much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\r\n<h2><strong>Google, Facebook, Twitter and all the rest.</strong></h2>\r\nRight now the top online advertising outlets are all trying to capture their piece of the pie, but they do it by offering something else. That something else comes with a lot of distractions, content, and anywhere from 5-12 or even more advertisements--competition. They want to provide value to increase user engagement, but they also want users to interact with the advertising. It is a difficult balance.\r\n\r\nWe want to help fill a void that has little to no competition, does not have distracting content, and is straightforward. We are going to deliver ads to you, and you are going to love it, use it all the time and soon life won\'t be the same with out us.\r\n\r\nHere are some important stats:\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"547\"]<a href=\"http://83-136-248-155.uk-lon1.host.upcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-08-at-10-8-9.41.00-PM.png\"><img src=\"http://83-136-248-155.uk-lon1.host.upcloud.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Screen-Shot-2013-10-08-at-10-8-9.41.00-PM.png\" alt=\"US Smartphone Growth Projections\" width=\"547\" height=\"467\" /></a> Smartphone Growth[/caption]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The US alone will be rapidly approaching 200 million smartphones in use by the 2014 holiday season</li>\r\n	<li>Users wake up their phones over <a title=\"HTC One M8 Review and Research\" href=\"https://www.yahoo.com/tech/heres-why-people-are-so-excited-about-the-new-htc-one-80913367177.html\" target=\"_blank\">150 times a day</a> - We are using our phones for everything now.</li>\r\n	<li>Mobile Advertising revenue is going to continue to grow as more and more time is spent on mobile platforms</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mobile Ad Revenue (Billions):\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2012 - $8.76</li>\r\n	<li>2013 - $17.96</li>\r\n	<li>2014 - $<em>31.45 (estimate)</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you could create an app which takes advantage of all of these factors, you could deliver ads to users in a way which creates great value to everyone involved.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur app does just this.\r\n\r\nOur marketing plan will allow us to gain significant user acceptance. By partnering with strategic organizations, charities, carriers, and other large companies we can hit our first goal of 1% of the smartphone users (1.75 million users) by the end of 2014.\r\n\r\nThat would bring in a mind blowing $54 million per month in revenues.\r\n<h4>And this is not even the best part of the app - the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side can work.</a></h4>\r\n<h4>If you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></h4>','The app','','inherit','open','open','','60-revision-v1','','','2014-05-08 12:12:49','2014-05-08 12:12:49','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(243,1,'2014-05-08 12:37:56','2014-05-08 12:37:56','<h2><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://www.jubelirerresultsgroup.com/wp-content/themes/striking/cache/images/285_bhag-628x250.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"628\" height=\"250\" />What in the world is a BHAG?</h2>\r\nA Big Hairy Audacious Goal\r\n\r\nWhy is it important?\r\n\r\nWell we all know how important goals are but just how important is it to have a defining, driving, motivating, all encompassing goal?\r\n\r\nSounds pretty clear when you talk it out.\r\n\r\nWhen you can, as an organization, identify a goal that helps guide all the actions and motivations of every individual you touch you transcend the fluff.\r\n\r\nOur BHAG follows our Vision - To become the most charitable company in the world.','BHAG','','inherit','open','open','','170-revision-v1','','','2014-05-08 12:37:56','2014-05-08 12:37:56','',170,'http://getadora.com/170-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(349,1,'2014-05-15 14:06:47','2014-05-15 14:06:47','','WebLogoSeaGreen','','inherit','open','open','','weblogoseagreen','','','2014-05-15 14:06:47','2014-05-15 14:06:47','',1,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/WebLogoSeaGreen.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(245,1,'2014-05-08 23:21:16','2014-05-08 23:21:16','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Adora project uses the power of Ad Revenue + User Engagement to = Charitable giving.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our passion is to do as much good as we possibly can.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what drives our every move, what make our hearts burn to work harder, longer, and smarter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We then want our example to start a movement, a change in not just corporate giving but private giving too. Make the point that even a dollar here or $5 there can make a difference, that you don\'t have to be wealthy to give and you don\'t have to</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/RXMnDG3QzxE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"http://lscapp.com/about/lsc-app/\">Read more about our app</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want more info <a href=\"http://lscapp.com/contact/\">contact us</a>.</strong></p>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-05-08 23:21:16','2014-05-08 23:21:16','',2,'http://getadora.com/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(246,1,'2014-05-08 23:21:36','2014-05-08 23:21:36','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Adora project uses the power of Ad Revenue + User Engagement to = Charitable giving.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our passion is to do as much good as we possibly can.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what drives our every move, what make our hearts burn to work harder, longer, and smarter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We then want our example to start a movement, a change in not just corporate giving but private giving too. Make the point that even a dollar here or $5 there can make a difference, that you don\'t have to be wealthy to give and you don\'t have to give money to make an impact.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/RXMnDG3QzxE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"http://lscapp.com/about/lsc-app/\">Read more about our app</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want more info <a href=\"http://lscapp.com/contact/\">contact us</a>.</strong></p>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-05-08 23:21:36','2014-05-08 23:21:36','',2,'http://getadora.com/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(248,1,'2014-05-09 03:01:14','2014-05-09 03:01:14','<h2>Before We Jump In</h2>\r\nIt is always exciting and enlightening when you sit down to put together a plan. Vague ideas become polished, new ones develop, some ideas are tossed for better ones,  and issues come up that need to be overcome. This process helps a team find out if the main idea is even a valid opportunity. We are excited to have gone through this process and come out knowing how truly awesome this idea is.\r\n\r\nThere was a time when we were inexperienced entrepreneurs, working on our first business plan, the horizon was always bright and simple. The numbers we make up, yes we make them up, are best guesses and we think that everything is going to work out just as we\'ve planned. But much to our surprise things just don\'t work out as we thought, the crystal ball doesn\'t work. Sometimes things turn out far better than we thought and sometimes they don\'t.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-56\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\" alt=\"SunsetRoad\" width=\"1000\" height=\"438\" /></a>We <strong>learn</strong>, as we go about the execution of one plan after another, that planning is important but never perfect. We <strong>learn</strong> that while the horizon is always bright we <strong>know</strong> that the shadows below the horizon contain pit falls, challenges, storms, detours and sometimes you must completely turn around and backtrack. This process is hard but necessary, it build teams or breaks them, prefects ideas or exposes them, and businesses bloom or fade.\r\n<h3>We want to create the best plan possible, but at the same time, let all of you who may be reading this know that we understand that any plan will change and more than likely change a lot.</h3>\r\nBecause we know that change is inevitable we are going to focus on the first 18 months, and even then we really only have control of the plan for the rest of 2014 (8+ months or so). Why? Because this app has the ability to explode, and we are only going to try and control growth for the first 3-5 months of the beta period. After that we have no idea how fast we will grow.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://www.quotesvalley.com/images/31/there-are-three-types-of-lies-lies-damn-lies-and-statistics-3.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"203\" /><strong>One thing we are going to do - not lie with numbers, data, and fluffy words.</strong>\r\n\r\nWe take an approach that is extreme and conservative all at the same time. We have taken our growth and projected it as conservatively as we can while at the same time projecting costs in an extreme and scary way. The result, a promise we know we can exceed.\r\n\r\nIf you want to review our protected pages or posts <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">email us through our contact page</a></strong> and we\'ll get back to you asap.','Plan','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2014-05-09 03:01:14','2014-05-09 03:01:14','',51,'http://getadora.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(249,1,'2014-05-09 03:01:43','2014-05-09 03:01:43','<h2>Before We Jump In</h2>\r\nIt is always exciting and enlightening when you sit down to put together a plan. Vague ideas become polished, new ones develop, some ideas are tossed for better ones,  and issues come up that need to be overcome. This process helps a team find out if the main idea is even a valid opportunity. We are excited to have gone through this process and come out knowing how truly awesome this idea is.\r\n\r\nThere was a time when we were inexperienced entrepreneurs, working on our first business plan, the horizon was always bright and simple. The numbers we make up, yes we make them up, are best guesses and we think that everything is going to work out just as we\'ve planned. But much to our surprise things just don\'t work out as we thought, the crystal ball doesn\'t work. Sometimes things turn out far better than we thought and sometimes they don\'t.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-56\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\" alt=\"SunsetRoad\" width=\"1000\" height=\"438\" /></a>We <strong>learn</strong>, as we go about the execution of one plan after another, that planning is important but never perfect. We <strong>learn</strong> that while the horizon is always bright we <strong>know</strong> that the shadows below the horizon contain pit falls, challenges, storms, detours and sometimes you must completely turn around and backtrack. This process is hard but necessary, it build teams or breaks them, prefects ideas or exposes them, and businesses bloom or fade.\r\n\r\n<strong>We want to create the best plan possible, but at the same time, let all of you who may be reading this know that we understand that any plan will change and more than likely change a lot.</strong>\r\n\r\nBecause we know that change is inevitable we are going to focus on the first 18 months, and even then we really only have control of the plan for the rest of 2014 (8+ months or so). Why? Because this app has the ability to explode, and we are only going to try and control growth for the first 3-5 months of the beta period. After that we have no idea how fast we will grow.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://www.quotesvalley.com/images/31/there-are-three-types-of-lies-lies-damn-lies-and-statistics-3.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"203\" /><strong>One thing we are going to do - not lie with numbers, data, and fluffy words.</strong>\r\n\r\nWe take an approach that is extreme and conservative all at the same time. We have taken our growth and projected it as conservatively as we can while at the same time projecting costs in an extreme and scary way. The result, a promise we know we can exceed.\r\n\r\nIf you want to review our protected pages or posts <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">email us through our contact page</a></strong> and we\'ll get back to you asap.','Plan','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2014-05-09 03:01:43','2014-05-09 03:01:43','',51,'http://getadora.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(250,1,'2014-05-09 03:16:17','2014-05-09 03:16:17','<h2>Interested in learning more?</h2>\r\nIf you are an Investor, a Charity, or a potential team member and you want to learn more we can give you access.\r\n\r\nWe are sure you\'ve noticed that our plan pages are protected and that is for obvious good reasons. All you have to do is <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">send us a request</a> and we\'ll contact you about the opportunity.\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Warning</span> - Business Plan Disclaimer!</h2>\r\nIt is always exciting and enlightening when you sit down to put together a plan. Vague ideas become polished, new ones develop, some ideas are tossed for better ones,  and issues come up that need to be overcome. This process helps a team find out if the main idea is even a valid opportunity. We are excited to have gone through this process and come out knowing how truly awesome this idea is.\r\n\r\nThere was a time when we were inexperienced entrepreneurs, working on our first business plan, the horizon was always bright and simple. The numbers we make up, yes we make them up, are best guesses and we think that everything is going to work out just as we\'ve planned. But much to our surprise things just don\'t work out as we thought, the crystal ball doesn\'t work. Sometimes things turn out far better than we thought and sometimes they don\'t.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-56\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\" alt=\"SunsetRoad\" width=\"1000\" height=\"438\" /></a>We <strong>learn</strong>, as we go about the execution of one plan after another, that planning is important but never perfect. We <strong>learn</strong> that while the horizon is always bright we <strong>know</strong> that the shadows below the horizon contain pit falls, challenges, storms, detours and sometimes you must completely turn around and backtrack. This process is hard but necessary, it build teams or breaks them, prefects ideas or exposes them, and businesses bloom or fade.\r\n\r\n<strong>We want to create the best plan possible, but at the same time, let all of you who may be reading this know that we understand that any plan will change and more than likely change a lot.</strong>\r\n\r\nBecause we know that change is inevitable we are going to focus on the first 18 months, and even then we really only have control of the plan for the rest of 2014 (8+ months or so). Why? Because this app has the ability to explode, and we are only going to try and control growth for the first 3-5 months of the beta period. After that we have no idea how fast we will grow.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://www.quotesvalley.com/images/31/there-are-three-types-of-lies-lies-damn-lies-and-statistics-3.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"203\" /><strong>One thing we are going to do - not lie with numbers, data, and fluffy words.</strong>\r\n\r\nWe take an approach that is extreme and conservative all at the same time. We have taken our growth and projected it as conservatively as we can while at the same time projecting costs in an extreme and scary way. The result, a promise we know we can exceed.\r\n\r\nIf you want to review our protected pages or posts <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">email us through our contact page</a></strong> and we\'ll get back to you asap.','Plan','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2014-05-09 03:16:17','2014-05-09 03:16:17','',51,'http://getadora.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(251,1,'2014-05-09 06:58:17','2014-05-09 06:58:17','<h2>Interested in learning more?</h2>\r\nIf you are an Investor, a Charity, or a potential team member and you want to learn more about the details behind our project this is the right place to start..\r\n\r\nWe are sure you\'ve noticed that our plan pages are protected, all you have to do is <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">send us a request</a> and we\'ll contact you about the opportunity.\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Warning</span> - Business Plan Disclaimer!</h2>\r\nIt is always exciting and enlightening when you sit down to put together a plan. Vague ideas become polished, new ones develop, some ideas are tossed for better ones,  and issues come up that need to be overcome. This process helps a team find out if the main idea is even a valid opportunity. We are excited to have gone through this process and come out knowing how truly awesome this idea is.\r\n\r\nThere was a time when we were inexperienced entrepreneurs, working on our first business plan, the horizon was always bright and simple. The numbers we make up, yes we make them up, are best guesses and we think that everything is going to work out just as we\'ve planned. But much to our surprise things just don\'t work out as we thought, the crystal ball doesn\'t work. Sometimes things turn out far better than we thought and sometimes they don\'t.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-56\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\" alt=\"SunsetRoad\" width=\"1000\" height=\"438\" /></a>We <strong>learn</strong>, as we go about the execution of one plan after another, that planning is important but never perfect. We <strong>learn</strong> that while the horizon is always bright we <strong>know</strong> that the shadows below the horizon contain pit falls, challenges, storms, detours and sometimes you must completely turn around and backtrack. This process is hard but necessary, it build teams or breaks them, prefects ideas or exposes them, and businesses bloom or fade.\r\n\r\n<strong>We want to create the best plan possible, but at the same time, let all of you who may be reading this know that we understand that any plan will change and more than likely change a lot.</strong>\r\n\r\nBecause we know that change is inevitable we are going to focus on the first 18 months, and even then we really only have control of the plan for the rest of 2014 (8+ months or so). Why? Because this app has the ability to explode, and we are only going to try and control growth for the first 3-5 months of the beta period. After that we have no idea how fast we will grow.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://www.quotesvalley.com/images/31/there-are-three-types-of-lies-lies-damn-lies-and-statistics-3.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"203\" /><strong>One thing we are going to do - not lie with numbers, data, and fluffy words.</strong>\r\n\r\nWe take an approach that is extreme and conservative all at the same time. We have taken our growth and projected it as conservatively as we can while at the same time projecting costs in an extreme and scary way. The result, a promise we know we can exceed.\r\n\r\nIf you want to review our protected pages or posts <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">email us through our contact page</a></strong> and we\'ll get back to you asap.','Plan','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2014-05-09 06:58:17','2014-05-09 06:58:17','',51,'http://getadora.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(254,1,'2014-05-09 07:29:25','2014-05-09 07:29:25','<img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />There are so many who need help.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">So many people would love to help.</p>\r\nWhy do they/we not do more?\r\n<h2>Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Add money to the mix and many believe that unless their donation is large it doesn\'t make a difference.\r\n\r\nOur app solves both of those problems. First we are not asking for our users to spend any more time than they already do. Second our app gives our users a choice they have never had before, to choose where their advertising earnings go.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Crowd.jpg\" alt=\"Crowd\" width=\"388\" height=\"255\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Our app is simple: the advertising pays for charity work but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">By creating strategic relationships we can hit our first goal of 1% of the 200 million smartphone user market by the middle of 2015. The math plays that 1% out to equal 2 million users, when compared to the 100 million Candy Crush users we would hope that at least 2% would be willing to support such a charitable cause. If you want to find out more about how we are going to gather these users, about our marketing plan, <a href=\"info@lscapp.com\">email us</a>. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Our requirements for the charities before getting money from us will be:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 24px;\">No less than 85% of all funds donated must go directly to the key activities of the cause, now this does not mean that no more than 15% can go to \'overhead\' only that it must be an activity that can benefit the cause. We want to work with these charities and make sure that most of their efforts are productive. Fundraising can be productive, getting great talent can be productive, marketing can be productive, tech investments can be productive yet these are all considered traditionally overhead in the non-profit world.</span></li>\r\n	<li>Legal work using donated funds will be heavily scrutinized. We love the legal system but we would rather feed children than pay lawyers.</li>\r\n	<li>Organizations run by religious groups will be heavily scrutinized. We want to make sure everyone is served; not just individuals who share a faith or ideology.</li>\r\n	<li>Medical research will be vetted heavily to make sure funds are going to research that is making strides not spinning wheels. We would love to see families who are struggling with heavily researched medical issues be supported.</li>\r\n	<li>We will not support organizations which participate heavily in political donations, activity, or lobbying. If there is a cause that needs representation at state and federal levels then let us know and we will work together on how to address that.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThe bottom line: we want our donations to get to people who need it.\r\n\r\n<strong>Here are some numbers on how we can impact our communities:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>First off let\'s assume our app is awesome, and it gains great market acceptance and we grow like crazy. But let\'s just start at that 1% (1.5 million) of the market. Good, now that we have that out of the way.</li>\r\n	<li>We would love to have all of our users donate their entire $15 max, then we match that, which equals $30 total. But to be realistic that group might make up around 10% (150,000) of our total active users, giving us a potential total of $4.5 million a month from these users.</li>\r\n	<li>If the rest of the 1.35 million users donate $1, and we match that, then it equals $2. We get monthly donation funds of... $2.7 million plus the users\' donations from point number 2, then we get <strong>$7.2 million a month.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a href=\"https://lh3.ggpht.com/DLDifF6R6ETGoHBPAfEDcwbRnZiTvty074hd0WQuRJug7RbfR7ihrkZXgt5zACKejbL6=h900\"><img class=\"alignright\" src=\"https://lh3.ggpht.com/DLDifF6R6ETGoHBPAfEDcwbRnZiTvty074hd0WQuRJug7RbfR7ihrkZXgt5zACKejbL6=h900\" alt=\"\" width=\"461\" height=\"288\" /></a>Sounds crazy right... Well Candy Crush Saga, yes we just referenced that game, has over 100 million active users!\r\n\r\nIt makes over $600,000 a day, and over $230 million a year <strong>AND</strong> our app has the potential to blow that away!\r\n\r\nIf we can donate $7.2 million a month, here is just a glimpse at some of the things we can do with that:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>@ $200 per child = 36,000 kids <strong>clothing &amp; school supplies</strong> for a year</li>\r\n	<li>@ $3.50 per meal = over 2.0 million <strong>meals</strong></li>\r\n	<li>@ $100 per procedure = 72,000<strong> dental procedures</strong> for underprivileged families</li>\r\n	<li>@ $100 per month = 72,000 <strong>Public Transit passes</strong> for a month to un/under employed</li>\r\n	<li>@$2,000 per month = 3,600 families <strong>sheltered and given job training</strong> per month</li>\r\n	<li>@ $5,000 per semester = 1440 <strong>scholarships</strong> to under-funded college students</li>\r\n	<li>@ $25,000 per child = 288 families <strong>supported during life threatening medical issues</strong></li>\r\n	<li>@ $100,000 per unit = We can deliver a self-sustaining water solution to 72 locations, and <strong>provide clean water</strong> where thousands die every year from unclean water...</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf we donated all but a fraction of our revenues to efforts like this we would find joy and satisfaction in our existence and our app. But we can have both an amazing impact through our donations <strong>and</strong> have a healthy profit margin; this is a \"win/win\" opportunity.\r\n\r\nWe also want to help small businesses by providing them with free help when it comes to learning how to advertise and how to get results.\r\n\r\nWe want to give large brands the reach and impact they are looking for every day.\r\n\r\nWe want to provide an amazing return for our investors so they can go out and invest more in companies that do good.\r\n\r\nWe want to talk to you.\r\n<h3>If you want to become part of our team, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></h3>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-05-09 07:29:25','2014-05-09 07:29:25','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(256,1,'2014-05-09 07:32:22','2014-05-09 07:32:22','There are so many who need help.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">So many people would love to help.</p>\r\nWhy do they/we not do more?\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Add money to the mix and many believe that unless their donation is large it doesn\'t make a difference.\r\n\r\nOur app solves both of those problems. First we are not asking for our users to spend any more time than they already do. Second our app gives our users a choice they have never had before, to choose where their advertising earnings go.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignleft wp-image-96\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Crowd.jpg\" alt=\"Crowd\" width=\"388\" height=\"255\" />\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">Our app is simple: the advertising pays for charity work but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">By creating strategic relationships we can hit our first goal of 1% of the 200 million smartphone user market by the middle of 2015. The math plays that 1% out to e