donating over $100 million every month! That is possible and oh the good we could do with that kind of donation every month.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company in the world</strong></p>\r\n But even once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish, we must change the way we look at charitable organizations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses, be it a moving hashtag spreading via twitter or a viral video, we know that there are a few better ways to move mountains. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below, better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<strong>If you want help out and become part of <a title=\"Team\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/team/\">our team</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-05-11 05:02:14','2014-05-11 05:02:14','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(342,1,'2014-05-11 05:02:45','2014-05-11 05:02:45','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 60px;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 180px;\">So many people would love to do more but...</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So don\'t we do more?</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Add money to the mix and many believe that unless their donation is large it doesn\'t make a difference.\r\n\r\nOur app solves all of these problems. First we are not asking for our users to spend any more time than they already do. Second our app gives our users a choice they have never had before, to choose where their advertising earnings go. And Third - we make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"426\" height=\"261\" /></a>Our app is simple: the advertising pays for charity work but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For those who would like to donate from their own pockets we hope to help this process be easier. Our app will make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference but if 1 million or 100 million users all donate then those dollars add up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible and oh the good we could do with that kind of donation every month.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company in the world</strong></p>\r\n But even once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish, we must change the way we look at charitable organizations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses, be it a moving hashtag spreading via twitter or a viral video, we know that there are a few better ways to move mountains. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below, better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<strong>If you want help out and become part of <a title=\"Team\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/team/\">our team</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-05-11 05:02:45','2014-05-11 05:02:45','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(343,1,'2014-05-11 05:03:01','2014-05-11 05:03:01','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 60px;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 180px;\">So many people would love to do more but...</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So don\'t we do more?</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Add money to the mix and many believe that unless their donation is large it doesn\'t make a difference.\r\n\r\nOur app solves all of these problems. First we are not asking for our users to spend any more time than they already do. Second our app gives our users a choice they have never had before, to choose where their advertising earnings go. And Third - we make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"426\" height=\"261\" /></a>Our app is simple: the advertising pays for charity work but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For those who would like to donate from their own pockets we hope to help this process be easier. Our app will make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference but if 1 million or 100 million users all donate then those dollars add up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible and oh the good we could do with that kind of donation every month.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company in the world</strong></p>\r\n But even once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish, we must change the way we look at charitable organizations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses, be it a moving hashtag spreading via twitter or a viral video, we know that there are a few better ways to move mountains. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below, better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<strong>If you want help out and become part of <a title=\"Team\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/team/\">our team</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-05-11 05:03:01','2014-05-11 05:03:01','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(354,1,'2014-05-15 15:00:28','2014-05-15 15:00:28','','HomelessChildrenSmall','','inherit','open','open','','homelesschildrensmall','','','2014-05-15 15:00:28','2014-05-15 15:00:28','',353,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/HomelessChildrenSmall.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(352,1,'2014-05-15 14:50:34','2014-05-15 14:50:34','','HomelessChildren','','inherit','open','open','','homelesschildren','','','2014-05-15 14:50:34','2014-05-15 14:50:34','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/HomelessChildren.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(353,5,'2014-05-15 15:00:34','2014-05-15 15:00:34','Are you doing all you can for your fellow man?\r\n\r\nI know I can not say that I am.\r\n\r\nWhen I think about it I am ashamed. That I have a roof over my head when so many do not. That I have food when so many cannot say the same.\r\n\r\nI am embarrassed...\r\n\r\nI can do more.\r\n\r\nWe can do more.\r\n\r\nOver the next couple of months we are going to be posting simple, easy things you can do to make a difference.\r\n\r\nPlaces you can go and people who can direct you to places where your limited time can make the most impact.\r\n\r\nWe will be posting images and video of our efforts and we would love for you to do the same. We need to set examples and bring the needs of our fellow man to the for front of our minds.\r\n\r\njoin our mailing list to get these updates.','We can do more','','publish','open','open','','we-can-do-more','','','2014-05-22 02:37:09','2014-05-22 02:37:09','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=353',0,'post','',0),(355,1,'2014-05-15 15:00:34','2014-05-15 15:00:34','Are you doing all you can for your fellow man?\r\n\r\nI know I can not say that I am.\r\n\r\nWhen I think about it I am ashamed. That I have a roof over my head when so many do not. That I have food, that my children have food when so many cannot say the same.\r\n\r\nI am embarrassed...\r\n\r\nI can do more.\r\n\r\nWe can do more.\r\n\r\nOver the next couple of months we are going to be posting simple, easy things you can do to make a difference.\r\n\r\nPlaces you can go and people who can direct you to places where your limited time can make the most impact.\r\n\r\njoin our mailing list to get these updates.','We can do more','','inherit','open','open','','353-revision-v1','','','2014-05-15 15:00:34','2014-05-15 15:00:34','',353,'http://getadora.com/353-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(356,1,'2014-05-15 15:04:18','2014-05-15 15:04:18','Are you doing all you can for your fellow man?\r\n\r\nI know I can not say that I am.\r\n\r\nWhen I think about it I am ashamed. That I have a roof over my head when so many do not. That I have food, that my children have food when so many cannot say the same.\r\n\r\nI am embarrassed...\r\n\r\nI can do more.\r\n\r\nWe can do more.\r\n\r\nOver the next couple of months we are going to be posting simple, easy things you can do to make a difference.\r\n\r\nWe will be posting images and video of our efforts and we would love for you to do the same. We need to set examples and bring the needs of our fellow man to the for front of our minds.\r\n\r\nPlaces you can go and people who can direct you to places where your limited time can make the most impact.\r\n\r\njoin our mailing list to get these updates.','We can do more','','inherit','open','open','','353-revision-v1','','','2014-05-15 15:04:18','2014-05-15 15:04:18','',353,'http://getadora.com/353-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(357,1,'2014-05-15 15:04:36','2014-05-15 15:04:36','Are you doing all you can for your fellow man?\r\n\r\nI know I can not say that I am.\r\n\r\nWhen I think about it I am ashamed. That I have a roof over my head when so many do not. That I have food, that my children have food when so many cannot say the same.\r\n\r\nI am embarrassed...\r\n\r\nI can do more.\r\n\r\nWe can do more.\r\n\r\nOver the next couple of months we are going to be posting simple, easy things you can do to make a difference.\r\n\r\nPlaces you can go and people who can direct you to places where your limited time can make the most impact.\r\n\r\nWe will be posting images and video of our efforts and we would love for you to do the same. We need to set examples and bring the needs of our fellow man to the for front of our minds.\r\n\r\njoin our mailing list to get these updates.','We can do more','','inherit','open','open','','353-revision-v1','','','2014-05-15 15:04:36','2014-05-15 15:04:36','',353,'http://getadora.com/353-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(359,1,'2014-05-15 16:43:39','2014-05-15 16:43:39','Mark and Kyle have been working together on and off for over ten years and there is no other person Kyle trusts more to give it to him straight.\r\n\r\nMark has a JD and an MBA and that education doesn\'t do his skills justice. Mark is a great problem solver and one of the best people to have in a room when brain storming. His combination of focus on the details and creativity helps keep ideas grounded but innovative at the same time, not an easy thing to do.\r\n\r\nMark grew up in Palo Alto, California, in the heart of Silicon Valley in a family of 8 kids and has been active in competitive athletics throughout his life. He is an avid basketball player and loves to do anything outdoors, including SCUBA diving, a favorite past time.\r\n\r\nMark earned a Bachelor\'s degree in Business from Brigham Young University  in Provo, Utah and served a two year LDS mission in Lima Peru. He speaks Spanish fluently and also picked up a few phrases in the indigenous language of Quechua, the Peruvian dialect among the native peoples in the Andes mountains and descendants of the Inca.\r\n\r\n<span>Mark graduated from the Drucker School, named after the \"father of modern management\", Peter Drucker. He earned a Master\'s degree in Business Administration with concentrations in Finance and Strategy. Previous to the MBA program, Mark earned a JD from Southwestern University School of Law in Los Angeles. During his time in law school Mark studied IT law through a summer abroad program at the University College of London.</span>\r\n\r\nCurrently, Mark works as an EB-5 Investor Liaison for foreign clients seeking eligibility for investment in new development projects to obtain permanent residence status through the US\'s EB-5 Immigrant Investor program. As the vast majority of these clients speak Chinese, Mark is studying to learn this language. Mark writes business plans for new capital investment projects, prepares investment contracts, regional center applications, and investor petitions.\r\n\r\n<span>Mark has many years of experience working in a law firm setting and has gained exposure to many different practice areas. His focus is on transactional law that combines his training in both business and law.</span>\r\n\r\nCheck out <a title=\"Mark Feriante\'s Linkedin profile\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=10423233&amp;locale=en_US&amp;trk=tyah&amp;trkInfo=tarId%3A1396283073101%2Ctas%3Amark%20f%2Cidx%3A1-1-1\" target=\"_blank\">Mark\'s Linkedin Profile</a> for even more info.','Mark Feriante','','publish','closed','closed','','mark-feriante','','','2014-05-15 16:43:39','2014-05-15 16:43:39','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=359',0,'team-member','',0),(360,1,'2014-05-15 16:44:30','2014-05-15 16:44:30','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/BenFaanunuSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-297 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/BenFaanunuSmall.jpg\" alt=\"BenFa\'anunu\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>Ben is a big data junkie and that is only one of the many things we love about him.\r\n\r\nCouple that love of data with an ingrained belief in consistent hard work gives you some awesome productivity. We never have to worry about a deadline or missed detail when it comes to Ben\'s work.\r\n\r\nBen loves to compete and it doesn\'t matter if its physical or mental that fire is going to be there. He was active in several high school sports and he wrestled in college.\r\n\r\nAfter serving a two year mission in the Philippine Islands he married and moved to Brigham Young University - Idaho. It was here he fell in love with the world of economics.\r\n\r\nBen Graduated from BYU - I with a BA in Economics and then moved on to an assistantship at the University of Idaho in the economics program. With grit and determination Ben earned two Masters degrees from the University of Idaho, A Master\'s in Applied Economics and a Master\'s in Statistics. Throughout this educational journey Ben gained a great deal of experience in the world of academic research, a skill set learned from these projects has helped him at every stage of his professional career.\r\n\r\nBen currently works as an Economist for the State of Arizona. He produces employment and unemployment reports for the stat and substate regions. He also works on employment and occupational projections and works with other state agencies to make data driven decisions.\r\n\r\nUnderstanding relationships and creating metrics to help us understand how things correlate is his passion. He is very excited to work on ways that we can help small and medium sized enterprises improve their understanding and use of digital marketing tools. He\'s also excited to help our Philanthropic partners do the same.\r\n\r\nRead more about Ben on his <a title=\"Ben Faanunu\'s Linkedin Profile\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=184397599&amp;locale=en_US&amp;trk=tyah&amp;trkInfo=tarId%3A1396284744850%2Ctas%3Abenj%2Cidx%3A1-1-1\" target=\"_blank\">Linkedin profile</a>.','Benjamin Fa\'anunu','','publish','closed','closed','','benjamin-faanunu','','','2014-05-15 17:36:47','2014-05-15 17:36:47','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=360',0,'team-member','',0),(361,1,'2014-05-15 16:57:41','2014-05-15 16:57:41','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JoeMichelsSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-298 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JoeMichelsSmall.jpg\" alt=\"JoeMichels\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>As President and CEO of <a title=\"Software Ops\" href=\"http://softwareops.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Software Ops</a>, Joe has been part of the mobile development community from the very beginning. <span style=\"color: #222222;\">His team at Software Ops is really our secret weapon, they make it possible for us to focus on the charitable and advertising sides of Adora. D</span>uring the early stages of organization Joe will also be serving as our CTO.\r\n\r\nOnce the organization is up and running, Joe and Sebastean will help in the recruiting process for internal IT management.\r\n\r\nLearn more from <a title=\"Joe Michels Linkedin Profile\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=13395916&amp;locale=en_US&amp;trk=tyah2&amp;trkInfo=tarId%3A1396306038415%2Ctas%3AJoe%20Michels%2Cidx%3A1-2-2\" target=\"_blank\">Joe\'s Linkedin profile</a>.','Joe Michels','','publish','closed','closed','','joe-michels','','','2014-05-15 17:35:45','2014-05-15 17:35:45','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=361',0,'team-member','',0),(362,1,'2014-05-15 17:00:02','2014-05-15 17:00:02','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/SebasteanLoschSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-302\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/SebasteanLoschSmall.jpg\" alt=\"SebasteanLoschSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>Sebastean and Joe are key to our success. Sebastean is the Director of Business Development at <a title=\"Software Ops\" href=\"http://softwareops.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Software Ops</a>, our app development partner.\r\n\r\nSebastean comes from a great combination of professional experience, working in both the VC and tech world. His experience over the last ten years has given Sebastean a creative edge when it comes to helping tech startups find success.\r\n\r\nYou can <a title=\"Sebastean Losch Linkedin\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pub/sebastean-losch/16/a03/775\" target=\"_blank\">find out more about Sebastean by visiting his Linkedin profile</a>.','Sebastean Losch','','publish','closed','closed','','sebastean-losch','','','2014-05-15 17:35:08','2014-05-15 17:35:08','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=362',0,'team-member','',0),(364,1,'2014-05-15 17:15:13','2014-05-15 17:15:13','<span style=\"color: #222222;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/WayneCarrollSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-296 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/WayneCarrollSmall.jpg\" alt=\"WayneCarroll\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>Wayne is an engineer turned legal guru with experience in business law and an expertise in IP law. Kyle has worked with Wayne for over 4 years. The chemistry that exists between Wayne and Kyle helps them get more work done in less time and when dealing with legal issues--this is a very good thing!</span>','Wayne Carroll','','publish','closed','closed','','wayne-carroll','','','2014-05-15 17:33:40','2014-05-15 17:33:40','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=364',0,'team-member','',0),(365,1,'2014-05-15 17:18:13','2014-05-15 17:18:13','<span style=\"color: #222222;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ChristianSampsonSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-366 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ChristianSampsonSmall.jpg\" alt=\"ChristianSampson\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>Christian is an up and coming commercial director working on the very media that we hope to distribute through our network. He will continue to work in the commercial world while at the same time help us mold and shape our message, feel and imagery we want to inspire people through.</span>','Christian Sampson','','publish','closed','closed','','christian-sampson','','','2014-05-15 17:30:37','2014-05-15 17:30:37','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=365',0,'team-member','',0),(366,1,'2014-05-15 17:30:07','2014-05-15 17:30:07','','ChristianSampsonSmall','Christian Sampson - Creative DIrector','inherit','open','open','','christiansampsonsmall','','','2014-05-15 17:30:07','2014-05-15 17:30:07','',365,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ChristianSampsonSmall.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(368,1,'2014-05-16 07:24:13','2014-05-16 07:24:13','<h2>Simple Mission</h2>\r\n<strong>Our mission</strong> is simple:\r\n\r\n<strong>↑User Engagement → ↑Ad Revenue→ ↑Charitable Giving</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Translation -</strong> Our mission is to dramatically increase user engagement with brands thus increasing our value to advertisers and therefore increasing our ability to contribute to organizations who do good.\r\n\r\nThis is our passion - To do as much good as we possibly can.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Adora app\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/adora-app/\">Read more about what we are building.</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Our Mission','','inherit','open','open','','218-revision-v1','','','2014-05-16 07:24:13','2014-05-16 07:24:13','',218,'http://getadora.com/218-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(369,4,'2014-03-21 07:24:52','2014-03-21 07:24:52','This brings us to <strong>Our Vision:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>It is our goal to be the most charitable company in the world within then next 5 years.</strong>','Our Vision','','publish','open','open','','vision','','','2014-05-16 07:48:46','2014-05-16 07:48:46','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=369',0,'post','',0),(370,1,'2014-05-16 07:24:52','2014-05-16 07:24:52','This brings us to <strong>Our Vision:</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>It is our goal to be the most charitable company in the world within then next 5 years.</strong>','Our Vision','','inherit','open','open','','369-revision-v1','','','2014-05-16 07:24:52','2014-05-16 07:24:52','',369,'http://getadora.com/369-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(371,1,'2014-05-16 07:41:09','2014-05-16 07:41:09','','Mission-Vision','','inherit','open','open','','mission-vision','','','2014-05-16 07:41:09','2014-05-16 07:41:09','',369,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Mission-Vision.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(372,4,'2014-04-30 08:28:26','2014-04-30 08:28:26','Just to be clear there is no fight here, no decision here, not at Adora.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"A love for Jim Collins\" href=\"http://getadora.com/love-jim-collins/\">Jim Collins</a> is famous for the book ‘Good to Great’ but in an earlier book, ‘Built to Last’ he spoke of a decision making paradigm that we like to follow:\r\n<blockquote>\"The genius of the AND vs. the tyranny of the OR\"</blockquote>\r\nWe refuse to believe that we have to sacrifice privacy in order to use data to make a great product. We will never use any data in a way that compromises anyones privacy.\r\n\r\n<strong>Data</strong>\r\n\r\nPrivacy concerns are no longer in the background for those who use sites like Facebook and Twitter or tools provided by Google.\r\n\r\nThe problem with so many of these sites, tools and utilities lies with the fact that they do not work well, if at all, without a great deal of data. It has become the price we pay for cheap or free services.\r\n\r\nWe here at Adora are no different in the need for data. Information about who you are helps us direct useful and even desired offers and ads to you. Our app is designed to engage users. With each engagement, we will get better at choosing and presenting those ads which are most relevant to you. Not only will this provide more value to you, the user, but it will also add value to our charity partners. Every improvement will translate into additional dollars going to charities who serve the causes you care most about. If we cannot do this we, and you, are not valuable to the advertisers who we need to fund our good works.\r\n\r\nThe main difference between our motivations and those of others like those we’ve mentioned above - we aim to do as much good as we can.\r\n\r\n<strong>Privacy</strong>\r\n\r\nGoogle’s unofficial motto - “Don’t Be Evil”\r\n\r\nThis isn’t a very inspiring motto, in it there leaves a great deal of grey area left to interpretation. Where is the evil line?\r\n\r\nIn the age of big data, we need more than a vague commitment of not being evil. Companies need to take significant steps to protect your information and remain vigilant in its defence.\r\n\r\nEven when we can count on companies to protect our information, we can’t always count on them not to sell that information to third parties. We all hate it when our information gets sold and we start getting spammed by third parties.\r\n\r\nSo here is our commitment to all of you - We are committed to safeguarding your data and promise to never share your contact information with third parties - period.','Privacy vs Data','','publish','open','open','','privacy-vs-data','','\nhttp://getadora.com/love-jim-collins/','2014-05-16 09:14:09','2014-05-16 09:14:09','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=372',0,'post','',0),(373,1,'2014-05-16 08:28:26','2014-05-16 08:28:26','Just to be clear there is no fight here, no decision here, not at Adora.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"A love for Jim Collins\" href=\"http://getadora.com/love-jim-collins/\">Jim Collins</a> is famous for the book ‘Good to Great’ but in an earlier book, ‘Built to Last’ he spoke of a decision making paradigm that we like to follow:\r\n<blockquote>\"The genius of the AND vs. the tyranny of the OR\"</blockquote>\r\nWe refuse to believe that we have to sacrifice privacy in order to use data to make a great product. We will never use any data in a way that compromises anyones privacy.\r\n\r\nData\r\n\r\nPrivacy concerns are no longer in the background for those who use sites like Facebook and Twitter or tools provided by Google.\r\n\r\nThe problem with so many of these sites, tools and utilities lies with the fact that they do not work well, if at all, without a great deal of data. It has become the price we pay for cheap or free services.\r\n\r\nWe here at Adora are no different in the need for data. Information about who you are helps us direct useful and even desired offers and ads to you. Our app is designed to engage users. With each engagement, we will get better at choosing and presenting those ads which are most relevant to you. Not only will this provide more value to you, the user, but it will also add value to our charity partners. Every improvement will translate into additional dollars going to charities who serve the causes you care most about. If we cannot do this we, and you, are not valuable to the advertisers who we need to fund our good works.\r\n\r\nThe main difference between our motivations and those of others like those we’ve mentioned above - we aim to do as much good as we can.\r\n\r\nPrivacy\r\n\r\nGoogle’s unofficial motto - “Don’t Be Evil”\r\n\r\nThis isn’t a very inspiring motto, in it there leaves a great deal of grey area left to interpretation. Where is the evil line?\r\n\r\nIn the age of big data, we need more than a vague commitment of not being evil. Companies need to take significant steps to protect your information and remain vigilant in its defence.\r\n\r\nEven when we can count on companies to protect our information, we can’t always count on them not to sell that information to third parties. We all hate it when our information gets sold and we start getting spammed by third parties.\r\n\r\nWe are committed to safeguarding your data and promise to never share your contact information with third parties.','Privacy vs Data','','inherit','open','open','','372-revision-v1','','','2014-05-16 08:28:26','2014-05-16 08:28:26','',372,'http://getadora.com/372-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(374,1,'2014-05-16 08:57:51','2014-05-16 08:57:51','Just to be clear there is no fight here,