enter\" style=\"height: 27px; width: 657px;\" width=\"569\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Digital Advertising Guru</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Mobile Software Engineer</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Charity Relationship Manager</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">If you think you would not just fit in but flourish and could see yourself in a leadership position as we grow then by all means <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">send us an email</a>.</p>\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/zrHlkHdPF4U\" width=\"932\" height=\"524\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>','Team','','inherit','open','open','','64-revision-v1','','','2014-05-30 16:00:38','2014-05-30 16:00:38','',64,'http://getadora.com/64-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(425,1,'2014-05-30 16:02:42','2014-05-30 16:02:42','','DevinThorpeSmall','Devin Thorpe - Forbes Writer, Financial, Charity, & Strategy Adviser','inherit','open','open','','devinthorpesmall','','','2014-05-30 16:02:42','2014-05-30 16:02:42','',64,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/DevinThorpeSmall.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(426,1,'2014-05-30 16:03:07','2014-05-30 16:03:07','','WayneCarrollSmall','Wayne Carroll - Legal & IP Strategy Adviser','inherit','open','open','','waynecarrollsmall-2','','','2014-05-30 16:03:07','2014-05-30 16:03:07','',64,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/WayneCarrollSmall.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(427,1,'2014-05-30 16:03:29','2014-05-30 16:03:29','','JoshShapiroSmall','Josh Shapiro - Advertising & Marketing Strategy Adviser','inherit','open','open','','joshshapirosmall','','','2014-05-30 16:03:29','2014-05-30 16:03:29','',64,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/JoshShapiroSmall.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(428,1,'2014-05-30 16:03:44','2014-05-30 16:03:44','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the start-up world we have what would be considered a Dream Team. Click on any of us to learn more.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/BenFaanunuSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-299 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/KyleThomasSmall.jpg\" alt=\"KyleThomasSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-297 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/BenFaanunuSmall.jpg\" alt=\"BenFa\'anunuSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/MarkFeriante2Small.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-300 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/MarkFeriante2Small.jpg\" alt=\"MarkFeriante2Small\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JoeMichelsSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-298 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JoeMichelsSmall.jpg\" alt=\"JoeMichelsSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/SebasteanLoschSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-302 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/SebasteanLoschSmall.jpg\" alt=\"SebasteanLoschSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ChristianSampsonSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-366 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ChristianSampsonSmall.jpg\" alt=\"ChristianSampsonSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/DevinThorpeSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-425\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/DevinThorpeSmall.jpg\" alt=\"DevinThorpeSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/WayneCarrollSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-426\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/WayneCarrollSmall.jpg\" alt=\"WayneCarrollSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/JoshShapiroSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-427\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/JoshShapiroSmall.jpg\" alt=\"JoshShapiroSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Man-WomanAvatar.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-304 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Man-WomanAvatar.jpg\" alt=\"Man-WomanAvatar\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We are looking for a few good men and women. Are you interested in a challenging, exciting, fulfilling daily struggle? Hard work, humility, creativity, and passion are part of the culture here at Adora.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We are looking for the following individuals:</p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\" aligncenter\" style=\"height: 27px; width: 657px;\" width=\"569\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Digital Advertising Guru</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Mobile Software Engineer</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Charity Relationship Manager</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">If you think you would not just fit in but flourish and could see yourself in a leadership position as we grow then by all means <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">send us an email</a>.</p>\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/zrHlkHdPF4U\" width=\"932\" height=\"524\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>','Team','','inherit','open','open','','64-revision-v1','','','2014-05-30 16:03:44','2014-05-30 16:03:44','',64,'http://getadora.com/64-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(450,1,'2014-05-30 23:52:23','2014-05-30 23:52:23','&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong><img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"424\" height=\"208\" /></strong></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>Our mission</strong> is simple</h2>\r\n<strong>↑User Engagement → ↑Ad Revenue→ ↑Charitable Giving</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Translation -</strong> Our mission is to dramatically <strong>increase user engagement</strong> with the messages brands present through our unique ad delivery methods thus <strong>increasing our value to advertisers &amp; brands</strong> and therefore<strong> increasing our ability to</strong> <strong>contribute to organizations who do good</strong>.\r\n\r\nThis is our passion - To do as much good as we possibly can.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>Our Vision</strong></h2>\r\n<strong>It is our vision to be the most charitable company in the world within the next 5 years.</strong>\r\n\r\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such an outlandish goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Walmart has lead the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo taking 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account Pfizer has taken the top spot for the last 4 years.\r\n\r\nWe know that these are very large companies but one of our goals is to get to the point where we are <strong>donating more than 50% of our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to this point but how fast and much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart-300x248.jpg\" alt=\"StandingApart\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" /></a>What sets us apart</h2>\r\nThere is more than just our charitable focus that set us apart. Over then next few months we will present a mystery to the world. The mystery of how we can create the most attractive and productive ad for advertisers and for users alike.\r\n\r\nWe have solved this problem and we will share <strong>how we solve it</strong> with all of you soon...\r\n\r\nNo matter how amazing the performance of our ads the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue spent in any other way, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side can work.</a>\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a>','The app','','inherit','open','open','','60-revision-v1','','','2014-05-30 23:52:23','2014-05-30 23:52:23','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(451,1,'2014-05-30 23:53:32','2014-05-30 23:53:32','&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong><img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"424\" height=\"208\" /></strong></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>Our mission</strong> is simple</h2>\r\n<strong>↑User Engagement → ↑Ad Revenue→ ↑Charitable Giving</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Translation -</strong> Our mission is to dramatically <strong>increase user engagement</strong> with the messages brands present through our unique ad delivery methods thus <strong>increasing our value to advertisers &amp; brands</strong> and therefore<strong> increasing our ability to</strong> <strong>contribute to organizations who do good</strong>.\r\n\r\nThis is our passion - To do as much good as we possibly can.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>Our Vision</strong></h2>\r\n<strong>It is our vision to lead a change in corporate social activity by becoming the most charitable company in the world by 2020.</strong>\r\n\r\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such an outlandish goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Walmart has lead the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo taking 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account Pfizer has taken the top spot for the last 4 years.\r\n\r\nWe know that these are very large companies but one of our goals is to get to the point where we are <strong>donating more than 50% of our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to this point but how fast and much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart-300x248.jpg\" alt=\"StandingApart\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" /></a>What sets us apart</h2>\r\nThere is more than just our charitable focus that set us apart. Over then next few months we will present a mystery to the world. The mystery of how we can create the most attractive and productive ad for advertisers and for users alike.\r\n\r\nWe have solved this problem and we will share <strong>how we solve it</strong> with all of you soon...\r\n\r\nNo matter how amazing the performance of our ads the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue spent in any other way, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side can work.</a>\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a>','The app','','inherit','open','open','','60-revision-v1','','','2014-05-30 23:53:32','2014-05-30 23:53:32','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(452,1,'2014-05-30 23:54:27','2014-05-30 23:54:27','&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong><img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"424\" height=\"208\" /></strong></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>Our mission</strong> is simple</h2>\r\n<strong>↑User Engagement → ↑Ad Revenue→ ↑Charitable Giving</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Translation -</strong> Our mission is to dramatically <strong>increase user engagement</strong> with the messages brands present through our unique ad delivery methods thus <strong>increasing our value to advertisers &amp; brands</strong> and therefore<strong> increasing our ability to</strong> <strong>contribute to organizations who do good</strong>.\r\n\r\nThis is our passion - To do as much good as we possibly can.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>Our Vision</strong></h2>\r\n<strong>It is our vision to lead a change in corporate social activity by becoming the most charitable company in the world by 2020.</strong>\r\n\r\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such an outlandish goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Walmart has lead the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo taking 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account Pfizer has taken the top spot for the last 4 years.\r\n\r\nWe know that these are very large companies but one of our goals is to get to the point where we are <strong>donating more than 50% of our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to this point but how fast and much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart-300x248.jpg\" alt=\"StandingApart\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" /></a>What sets us apart</h2>\r\nThere is more than just our charitable focus that set us apart. Over then next few months <strong>we will present a mystery to the world</strong>. The mystery of how we can create the most attractive and productive ad for advertisers and for users alike.\r\n\r\nWe have solved this problem and we will share <strong>how we solve it</strong> with all of you soon...\r\n\r\nNo matter how amazing the performance of our ads the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue spent in any other way, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side can work.</a>\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a>','The app','','inherit','open','open','','60-revision-v1','','','2014-05-30 23:54:27','2014-05-30 23:54:27','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(453,1,'2014-05-30 23:55:24','2014-05-30 23:55:24','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 60px;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; padding-left: 180px;\">So many people would love to do more but...</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So why don\'t we do more?</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Add money to the mix and many believe that unless their donation is large it doesn\'t make a difference.\r\n\r\nOur app solves all of these problems. First we are not asking for our users to spend any more time than they already do. Second our app gives our users a choice they have never had before, to choose where their advertising earnings go. And Third - we make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"426\" height=\"261\" /></a>Our app is simple: the advertising pays for charity work but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Our app will also make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference but if 1 million or 100 million users all donate then those dollars add up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible and oh the good we could do with that kind of donation every month.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company in the world</strong></p>\r\n But even once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish, we must change the way we look at charitable organizations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses, be it a moving hashtag spreading via twitter or a viral video, we know that there are a few better ways to move mountains. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below, better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"http://embed.ted.com/talks/dan_pallotta_the_way_we_think_about_charity_is_dead_wrong.html\" width=\"728\" height=\"409\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<strong>If you want help out and become part of <a title=\"Team\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/team/\">our team</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-05-30 23:55:24','2014-05-30 23:55:24','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(455,1,'2014-05-30 23:58:44','2014-05-30 23:58:44','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Adora project uses the power of Ad Revenue + User Engagement to = Charitable giving.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our passion is to do as much good as we possibly can.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what drives our every move, what makes our hearts burn to work harder, longer, and smarter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We then want our example to start a movement, a change in not just corporate giving but private giving too. Make the point that even a dollar here or $5 there can make a difference, that you don\'t have to be wealthy to give and you don\'t have to give money to make an impact.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/RXMnDG3QzxE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a title=\"The app\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/adora-app/\">Read more about our app</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want more info <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">contact us</a>.</strong></p>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-05-30 23:58:44','2014-05-30 23:58:44','',2,'http://getadora.com/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(456,1,'2014-05-31 00:00:31','2014-05-31 00:00:31','<h2>Interested in learning more?</h2>\r\nIf you are an Investor, a Charity, or a potential team member and you want to learn more about the details behind our project this is the right place to start..\r\n\r\nWe are sure you\'ve noticed that our plan pages are protected, all you have to do is <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">send us a request</a> and we\'ll contact you about the opportunity.\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Warning</span> - Business Plan Disclaimer!</h2>\r\nIt is always exciting and enlightening when you sit down to put together a plan. Vague ideas become polished, new ones develop, some ideas are tossed for better ones,  and issues come up that need to be overcome. This process helps a team find out if the main idea is even a valid opportunity. We are excited to have gone through this process and come out knowing how truly awesome this idea is.\r\n\r\nThere was a time when we were inexperienced entrepreneurs, working on our first business plan, the horizon was always bright and simple. The numbers we make up, yes we make them up, are best guesses and we think that everything is going to work out just as we\'ve planned. But much to our surprise things just don\'t work out as we thought, the crystal ball doesn\'t work. Sometimes things turn out far better than we thought and sometimes they don\'t.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-56\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/SunsetRoad.jpg\" alt=\"SunsetRoad\" width=\"1000\" height=\"438\" /></a>We <strong>learn</strong>, as we go about the execution of one plan after another, that planning is important but never perfect. We <strong>learn</strong> that while the horizon is always bright we <strong>know</strong> that the shadows below the horizon contain pit falls, challenges, storms, detours and sometimes you must completely turn around and backtrack. This process is hard but necessary, it build teams or breaks them, prefects ideas or exposes them, and businesses bloom or fade.\r\n\r\n<strong>We want to create the best plan possible, but at the same time, let everyone know we understand that any plan will change and more than likely change a lot.</strong>\r\n\r\nBecause we know that change is inevitable we are going to focus on the first 18 months, and even then we really only have control of the plan for the rest of 2014 (8+ months or so). Why? Because this app has the ability to explode, and we are only going to try and control growth for the first 3-5 months of the beta period. After that we have no idea how fast we will grow.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignright\" src=\"http://www.quotesvalley.com/images/31/there-are-three-types-of-lies-lies-damn-lies-and-statistics-3.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"475\" height=\"203\" /><strong>One thing we are going to do - not lie with numbers, data, and fluffy words.</strong>\r\n\r\nWe take an approach that is extreme and conservative all at the same time. We have taken our growth and projected it as conservatively as we can while at the same time projecting costs in an extreme and scary way. The result, a promise we know we can exceed.\r\n\r\nIf you want to review our protected pages or posts <strong><a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">email us through our contact page</a></strong> and we\'ll get back to you asap.','Plan','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2014-05-31 00:00:31','2014-05-31 00:00:31','',51,'http://getadora.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(458,1,'2014-05-31 00:10:28','2014-05-31 00:10:28','','Universe','','inherit','open','open','','universe','','','2014-05-31 00:10:28','2014-05-31 00:10:28','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Universe.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(459,5,'2014-05-31 00:19:29','2014-05-31 00:19:29','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Universe.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-458 size-medium\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Universe-300x243.jpg\" alt=\"Universe\" width=\"300\" height=\"243\" /></a>We cannot believe how things have unfolded over the last week.\r\n\r\nOur last post was about finding talent. We have been looking for talent, for people, for amazing people and we have been touched by the universe.\r\n\r\nWe believe in what we are doing, we really do, we love the opportunity but to have the universe agree and act is humbling.\r\n\r\nWe have been blessed to have some amazing people come on board over the last week. Over the next few weeks we will be introducing our entire team, so you can get to know them, and you too will see why we are so blown away.\r\n\r\nStay tuned and look to get to know the hearts working on Adora.','The Universe is Listening','','publish','open','open','','universe-listening','','','2014-06-25 03:02:31','2014-06-25 03:02:31','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=459',0,'post','',0),(460,1,'2014-05-31 00:19:29','2014-05-31 00:19:29','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Universe.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-458 size-medium\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Universe-300x243.jpg\" alt=\"Universe\" width=\"300\" height=\"243\" /></a>We cannot believe how things have unfolded over the last week.\r\n\r\nOur last post was about finding talent. We have been looking for talent, for people, for amazing people and we have been touched by the universe.\r\n\r\nWe believe in what we are doing, we really do, we love the opportunity but to have the universe agree and act is humbling.\r\n\r\nWe have been blessed to have some amazing people come on board over the last week. Over the next few weeks we will be introducing our entire team, so you can get to know them, and you too will see why we are so blown away.\r\n\r\nStay tuned and look to get to know the hearts working on Adora.','The Universe is Listening','','inherit','open','open','','459-revision-v1','','','2014-05-31 00:19:29','2014-05-31 00:19:29','',459,'http://getadora.com/459-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(464,1,'2014-05-31 01:25:03','2014-05-31 01:25:03','','ComingSoonbanner','','inherit','open','open','','websitebanner','','','2014-05-31 01:25:03','2014-05-31 01:25:03','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Websitebanner.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(467,3,'2014-06-03 17:04:36','2014-06-03 17:04:36','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Adora project uses the power of Ad Revenue + User Engagement to = Charitable giving.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our passion is to do as much good as we possibly can.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what drives our every move, what makes our hearts burn to work harder, longer, and smarter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We then will use our example to start a movement, a change in not just corporate giving but in private giving too. We stand for the principle that even a dollar here or $5 there can make a difference--that you don\'t have to be wealthy to give and you don\'t have to give money to make an impact.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/RXMnDG3QzxE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a title=\"The app\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/adora-app/\">Read more about our app</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want more info <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">contact us</a>.</strong></p>','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-06-03 17:04:36','2014-06-03 17:04:36','',2,'http://getadora.com/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(468,3,'2014-06-03 17:09:26','2014-06-03 17:09:26','&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"424\" height=\"208\" /></strong></h2>\n<h2><strong>Our mission</strong> is simple</h2>\n<strong>↑User Engagement → ↑Ad Revenue→ ↑Charitable Giving</strong>\n\n<strong>Translation -</strong> Our mission is to dramatically <strong>increase user engagement</strong> with the messages brands present through our unique ad delivery methods thus <strong>increasing our value to advertisers &amp; brands</strong> and therefore<strong> increasing our ability to</strong> <strong>contribute to organizations who do good</strong>.\n\nThis is our passion - To do as much good as we possibly can.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>Our Vision</strong></h2>\n<strong>It is our vision to lead a change in corporate social activity by becoming the most charitable company in the world by 2020.</strong>\n\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such an outlandish goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Walmart has lead the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo taking 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account Pfizer has taken the top spot for the last 4 years.\n\nWe know that these are very large companies but one of our goals is to get to the point where we are <strong>donating more than 50% of our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to this point but how fast and much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart-300x248.jpg\" alt=\"StandingApart\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" /></a>What sets us apart</h2>\nThere is more than just our charitable focus that sets us apart. Over the next few months <strong>we will present this mystery to the world</strong>. The mystery of how we can create the most attractive and productive ad for advertisers and for users alike.\n\nWe have solved this problem and we will share <strong>how we solve it</strong> with all of you soon...\n\nNo matter how amazing the performance of our ads the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue spent in any other way, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side can work.</a>\n\nIf you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a>','The app','','inherit','open','open','','60-autosave-v1','','','2014-06-03 17:09:26','2014-06-03 17:09:26','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(469,3,'2014-06-03 17:09:58','2014-06-03 17:09:58','&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong><img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"424\" height=\"208\" /></strong></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>Our mission</strong> is simple</h2>\r\n<strong>↑User Engagement → ↑Ad Revenue→ ↑Charitable Giving</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Translation -</strong> Our mission is to dramatically <strong>increase user engagement</strong> with the messages brands present through our unique ad delivery methods thus <strong>increasing our value to advertisers &amp; brands</strong> and therefore<strong> increasing our ability to</strong> <strong>contribute to organizations who do good</strong>.\r\n\r\nThis is our passion - To do as much good as we possibly can.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>Our Vision</strong></h2>\r\n<strong>It is our vision to lead a change in corporate social activity by becoming the most charitable company in the world by 2020.</strong>\r\n\r\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such an outlandish goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Walmart has lead the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo taking 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account Pfizer has taken the top spot for the last 4 years.\r\n\r\nWe know that these are very large companies but one of our goals is to get to the point where we are <strong>donating more than 50% of our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to this point but how fast and much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart-300x248.jpg\" alt=\"StandingApart\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" /></a>What sets us apart</h2>\r\nThere is more than just our charitable focus that sets us apart. Over the next few months <strong>we will present this mystery to the world</strong>. The mystery of how we can create the most attractive and productive ad for advertisers and for users alike.\r\n\r\nWe have solved this problem and we will share <strong>how we solve it</strong> with all of you soon...\r\n\r\nNo matter how amazing the performance of our ads the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue spent in any other way, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side will work.</a>\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a>','The app','','inherit','open','open','','60-revision-v1','','','2014-06-03 17:09:58','2014-06-03 17:09:58','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(471,3,'2014-06-18 09:12:47','2014-06-18 09:12:47','In the beginning, we worked without a real name, just an acronym, so when we finally turned to try and find a name for our venture, we struggled as nothing quite seemed to fit.\n\nIn late April we took the few ideas we did have and put them to our friends and family in the form of a survey, but even then many stated that the right name did not seem to be on the list.\n\nThe name “Adora” came about during a conversation with my brother when we discussed the app idea and I asked him if he had any name suggestions. We started brainstorming and he began throwing out ideas, such as “Ad-ittude”, which is one of the names I remember he mentioned. From that thought I said “Ad-ora”. We recognized this had some similarity  to the name “Pandora” and it made sense, as our concept seemed to be like an “ad” version of Pandora, the automated music recommendation service. Our app will be an ad recommendation service with the single mission of delivering ads you’ll love. Rather than enjoy music, in return we all get to enjoy the great feeling of doing good because of the money generated for charities by using the app.\n\nAs we\'ve done with every other name idea, we looked at it from all directions. I speak fluent Spanish, so Latin-based words feel at home with me. Because of this I knew that Adora was a feminine name. This made sense as we all know the gentler sex is more giving, loving and full of charity.\n\nLater, as we researched the name, we found that \'adora\' means “gift”; “beloved”; “adored” and is of Greek, Old German, and Latin origin. The name is also associated with the root word to “love” which is “adorare” in Latin. For example, “adora” in Portuguese (a latin-based language) means “love.”\n\nThis meaning fits not only perfectly with the charity focus of the app, which can be described as providing “gifts” to charity motivated by “love”, but also the fact that our mission is to deliver only ads that you will “love” based on the app’s ability to learn over time from user activity which ads are relevant and desirable.\n\nThere is not much more to tell about the discovery of our name, but as we have shared it with others, everyone has fallen in love with both the name and the meaning. We invite you to do the same. Join us in our passion to love our fellow man.','The Story Behind a Name','','inherit','open','open','','381-autosave-v1','','','2014-06-18 09:12:47','2014-06-18 09:12:47','',381,'http://getadora.com/381-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(472,3,'2014-06-18 09:12:58','2014-06-18 09:12:58','In the beginning, we worked without a real name, just an acronym, so when we finally turned to try and find a name for our venture, we struggled as nothing quite seemed to fit.\r\n\r\nIn late April we took the few ideas we did have and put them to our friends and family in the form of a survey, but even then many stated that the right name did not seem to be on the list.\r\n\r\nThe name “Adora” came about during a conversation with my brother when we discussed the app idea and I asked him if he had any name suggestions. We started brainstorming and he began throwing out ideas, such as “Ad-ittude”, which is one of the names I remember he mentioned. From that thought I said “Ad-ora”. We recognized this had some similarity  to the name “Pandora” and it made sense, as our concept seemed to be like an “ad” version of Pandora, the automated music recommendation service. Our app will be an ad recommendation service with the single mission of delivering ads you’ll love. Rather than enjoy music, in return we all get to enjoy the great feeling of doing good because of the money generated for charities by using the app.\r\n\r\nAs we\'ve done with every other name idea, we looked at it from all directions. I speak fluent Spanish, so Latin-based words feel at home with me. Because of this I knew that Adora was a feminine name. This made sense as we all know the gentler sex is more giving, loving and full of charity.\r\n\r\nLater, as we researched the name, we found that \'adora\' means “gift”; “beloved”; “adored” and is of Greek, Old German, and Latin origin. The name is also associated with the root word to “love” which is “adorare” in Latin. For example, “adora” in Portuguese (a latin-based language) means “love.”\r\n\r\nThis meaning fits not only perfectly with the charity focus of the app, which can be described as providing “gifts” to charity motivated by “love”, but also the fact that our mission is to deliver only ads that you will “love” based on the app’s ability to learn over time from user activity which ads are relevant and desirable.\r\n\r\nThere is not much more to tell about the discovery of our name, but as we have shared it with others, everyone has fallen in love with both the name and the meaning. We invite you to do the same. Join us in our passion to love our fellow man.','The Story Behind a Name','','inherit','open','open','','381-revision-v1','','','2014-06-18 09:12:58','2014-06-18 09:12:58','',381,'http://getadora.com/381-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(474,5,'2014-06-25 03:01:54','2014-06-25 03:01:54','We know we\'ve been lax in our documentation of our progress but things have been flying around here.\r\n\r\nWe had no idea what the <a title=\"The Universe is Listening\" href=\"http://getadora.com/universe-listening/\">universe</a> had in store for us when we made our <a title=\"A plea for TALENT!\" href=\"http://getadora.com/plea-talent/\">plea for talent</a>! We haven\'t even been able to update our team and while we have only 9 showing on the site right now we have grown to 9 team members and 6 advisers. It has been all we could do to keep up with all we have been doing to get ready for our launch.\r\n\r\nWe have also started bringing charities on board and we will be introducing them as we launch. For those who have already come on board we thank you for leading the pack.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions or would like to learn more feel free to look around or email us - info@getAdora.com','Busy Busy Busy','','publish','open','open','','busy-busy-busy','','http://getadora.com/universe-listening/\nhttp://getadora.com/plea-talent/','2014-06-25 03:10:17','2014-06-25 03:10:17','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=474',0,'post','',0),(475,1,'2014-06-25 02:51:29','2014-06-25 02:51:29','','BusyBees','','inherit','open','open','','busybees','','','2014-06-25 02:51:29','2014-06-25 02:51:29','',474,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/BusyBees.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(476,1,'2014-06-25 03:01:54','2014-06-25 03:01:54','We know we\'ve been lax in our documentation of our progress but things have been flying around here.\r\n\r\nWe haven\'t even been able to update our team and while we have only 9 showing on the site right now we have grown to 9 team members and 6 advisers. It has been all we could do to keep up with all we have been doing to get ready for our launch.\r\n\r\nWe have also started bringing charities on board and we will be introducing them as we launch. For those who have already come on board we thank you for leading the pack.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions or would like to learn more feel free to look around or email us - info@getAdora.com','Busy Busy Busy','','inherit','open','open','','474-revision-v1','','','2014-06-25 03:01:54','2014-06-25 03:01:54','',474,'http://getadora.com/474-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(477,1,'2014-06-25 03:03:44','2014-06-25 03:03:44','We know we\'ve been lax in our documentation of our progress but things have been flying around here.\r\n\r\nWe had no idea what the <a title=\"The Universe is Listening\" href=\"http://getadora.com/universe-listening/\">universe</a> had in store for us when we made our <a title=\"A plea for TALENT!\" href=\"http://getadora.com/plea-talent/\">plea for talent</a>! We haven\'t even been able to update our team and while we have only 9 showing on the site right now we have grown to 9 team members and 6 advisers. It has been all we could do to keep up with all we have been doing to get ready for our launch.\r\n\r\nWe have also started bringing charities on board and we will be introducing them as we launch. For those who have already come on board we thank you for leading the pack.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions or would like to learn more feel free to look around or email us - info@getAdora.com','Busy Busy Busy','','inherit','open','open','','474-revision-v1','','','2014-06-25 03:03:44','2014-06-25 03:03:44','',474,'http://getadora.com/474-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(482,6,'2014-09-04 00:14:09','2014-09-04 00:14:09','','David Brinkerhoff','','publish','closed','closed','','david-brinkerhoff','','','2014-09-04 00:31:34','2014-09-04 00:31:34','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=team-member&#038;p=482',0,'team-member','',0),(484,6,'2014-09-04 00:26:39','2014-09-04 00:26:39','The data is in and philanthropy is back in style.  In his <a title=\"Annual Philanthropy Numbers On The Rise: U.S. Giving Nears Pre-Recession Levels\" href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/tomwatson/2014/06/17/annual-philanthropy-numbers-on-the-rise-u-s-giving-nears-pre-recession-levels/\" target=\"_blank\">article</a> for Forbes, Tom Watson points out that annual giving is on the rise and that individuals rather than corporations are driving the numbers.\r\n\r\nWhile Charitable giving was down after the housing bubble and subsequent derivatives crash, many things have stabilized enough that ordinary Americans are right back at it doing good and almost at the rate they were before the financial downturn.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"416\"]<img src=\"http://blogs-images.forbes.com/tomwatson/files/2014/06/Screen-Shot-2014-06-16-at-8.08.37-PM.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"416\" height=\"259\" /> Total US Giving is on the rise and almost back to per-recession levels. (Source: Giving USA Foundation)[/caption]\r\n\r\nAnother inspiring <a title=\"World\'s most big-hearted nation: the United States\" href=\"http://www.cnbc.com/id/101240935#.\" target=\"_blank\">article</a> from CNBC’s Ansuya Harjani at the end of 2013 highlighted this trend noting America’s rise from 5th to 1st place on the 2013 World Giving Index which measures both financial giving and volunteerism.\r\n\r\nThe most exciting thing about these articles is that they demonstrate a rising trend in charitable giving and volunteerism.  This rise in charitable giving at a grassroots, individual initiative level has created a great opportunity and social momentum.  <a title=\"Adora\'s Website\" href=\"http://getadora.com\" target=\"_blank\">Adora </a>with its Adora Charity App (a mobile device advertising application) hopes to use this momentum to take charitable giving to the next level.\r\n\r\nWith giving back to almost 2% of GDP last year Adora is working to push it over the 2% mark by the end of 2015 and intends to measure its positive social impact primarily by its impact on society.\r\n<blockquote>“Through Adora users will know how much of an impact they are making individually and the overall impact they are making collectively. They will learn about individuals, and causes and hopefully be inspired to go out and make their own impact up and above what they do through Adora. Our motto ‘Let’s Do Some Good’ really is an invitation for everyone to get involved.”\r\n\r\n~CEO of Adora, Kyle Thomas</blockquote>\r\nIt is hard to measure what the impact on a daily basis that advertisements for charities will have not only on a charity\'s current loyal supporters, but it can’t help but change the culture once the user base reaches a certain threshold.  When people who already feel like giving, take additional steps to support their causes and share the good they are doing with their friends, the hope is that what is now a trend in charitable giving can be taken viral.\r\n\r\nThe act of doing something and sharing it with one’s friends has real power in today’s social media driven world.  Consider for a moment the positive impact that the viral videos of people dumping buckets of icy water over their heads is doing for ASL as far as driving exposure and donations to that cause.  How easy would it be for each of those video makers to recommend installing a mobile app that will fund the ALS Association every month on their behalf.  Who knows but that Adora may change society and in the not too distant future, the US may be giving at 3% of GDP.\r\n\r\nIf your charity has not already signed up to be featured as a charity choice for users to fund, there is still a little time to get included when the app launches in late September. Development professionals should contact <a href=\"mailto:info@getadora.com\">info@getadora.com</a> to learn more or <a title=\"Fundraising  Professionals-Sign up Here\" href=\"http://goo.gl/bOIutf\" target=\"_blank\">click here to sign up for funding</a>.\r\n\r\nIf individuals wish to recommend a charity and pledge to support that charity through installing the Adora Charity App,  they may submit those <a title=\"Nominate and pledge support for your charity\" href=\"http://goo.gl/60LSzX\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.','Philanthropy in Vogue - Charitable Giving Approaches Pre Recession Levels','','draft','open','open','','philanthropy-vogue-charitable-giving-approaches-pre-recession-levels','','','2014-09-09 22:04:14','2014-09-09 22:04:14','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=484',0,'post','',0),(485,6,'2014-09-04 00:25:20','2014-09-04 00:25:20','The data is in and philanthropy is back in style.  In his <a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/tomwatson/2014/06/17/annual-philanthropy-numbers-on-the-rise-u-s-giving-nears-pre-recession-levels/\">article</a> for Forbes, Tom Watson points out that annual giving is on the rise and that individuals rather than corporations are driving the numbers.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWhile Charitable giving was down after the housing bubble and subsequent derivatives crash, many things have stabilized enough that ordinary Americans are right back at it doing good and almost at the rate they were before the financial downturn.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnother inspiring <a href=\"http://www.cnbc.com/id/101240935#.\">article</a> from CNBC’s Ansuya Harjani at the end of 2013 highlighted this trend noting America’s rise from 5th to 1st place on the 2013 World Giving Index which measures both financial giving and volunteerism.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe most exciting thing about these articles is that they demonstrate a rising trend in charitable giving and volunteerism.  This rise in charitable giving at a grassroots, individual initiative level has created a great opportunity and social momentum.  <a href=\"http://getadora.com\">Adora</a> with its Charity App (a mobile device advertising application) hopes to use this momentum to take charitable giving to the next level.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith giving back to almost 2% of GDP last year Adora is working to push it over the 2% mark by the end of 2015 and intends to measure its positive social impact primarily by its impact on society.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n“Through Adora users will know how much of an impact they are making individually and the overall impact they are making collectively. They will learn about individuals, and causes and hopefully be inspired to go out and make their own impact up and above what they do through Adora. Our motto ‘Let’s Do Some Good’ really is an invitation for everyone to get involved.”\r\n\r\n~CEO of Adora, Kyle Thomas\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt is hard to measure what the impact on a daily basis that advertisements for charities will have not only on a charity\'s current loyal supporters, but it can’t help but change the culture once the user base reaches a certain threshold.  When people who already feel like giving, take additional steps to support their causes and share the good they are doing with their friends, the hope is that what is now a trend in charitable giving can be taken viral.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe act of doing something and sharing it with one’s friends has real power in today’s social media driven world.  Consider for a moment the positive impact that the viral videos of people dumping buckets of icy water over their heads is doing for ASL as far as driving exposure and donations to that cause.  How easy would it be for each of those video makers to recommend installing a mobile app that will fund the ALS Association every month on their behalf.  Who knows but that Adora may change society and in the not too distant future, the US may be giving at 3% of GDP.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf your charity has not already signed up to be featured as charity choice for users to fund, there is still a little time to get included when the app launches in mid September. Development professionals should contact <a href=\"mailto:info@getadora.com\">info@getadora.com</a> to learn more or <a href=\"http://goo.gl/bOIutf\">click here to sign up for funding</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf individuals wish to recommend a charity and pledge to support that charity through installing the Adora Charity App,  they may submit those <a href=\"http://goo.gl/60LSzX\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCitations: <a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/tomwatson/2014/06/17/annual-philanthropy-numbers-on-the-rise-u-s-giving-nears-pre-recession-levels/\">http://www.forbes.com/sites/tomwatson/2014/06/17/annual-philanthropy-numbers-on-the-rise-u-s-giving-nears-pre-recession-levels/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.cnbc.com/id/101240935\">http://www.cnbc.com/id/101240935</a>','Philanthropy in Vogue - Charitable Giving Approaches Pre Recession Levels','','inherit','open','open','','484-revision-v1','','','2014-09-04 00:25:20','2014-09-04 00:25:20','',484,'http://getadora.com/484-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(486,1,'2014-09-04 00:26:23','2014-09-04 00:26:23','The data is in and philanthropy is back in style.  In his <a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/tomwatson/2014/06/17/annual-philanthropy-numbers-on-the-rise-u-s-giving-nears-pre-recession-levels/\">article</a> for Forbes, Tom Watson points out that annual giving is on the rise and that individuals rather than corporations are driving the numbers.\r\n\r\nWhile Charitable giving was down after the housing bubble and subsequent derivatives crash, many things have stabilized enough that ordinary Americans are right back at it doing good and almost at the rate they were before the financial downturn.\r\n\r\nAnother inspiring <a href=\"http://www.cnbc.com/id/101240935#.\">article</a> from CNBC’s Ansuya Harjani at the end of 2013 highlighted this trend noting America’s rise from 5th to 1st place on the 2013 World Giving Index which measures both financial giving and volunteerism.\r\n\r\nThe most exciting thing about these articles is that they demonstrate a rising trend in charitable giving and volunteerism.  This rise in charitable giving at a grassroots, individual initiative level has created a great opportunity and social momentum.  <a href=\"http://getadora.com\">Adora</a> with its Charity App (a mobile device advertising application) hopes to use this momentum to take charitable giving to the next level.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWith giving back to almost 2% of GDP last year Adora is working to push it over the 2% mark by the end of 2015 and intends to measure its positive social impact primarily by its impact on society.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n“Through Adora users will know how much of an impact they are making individually and the overall impact they are making collectively. They will learn about individuals, and causes and hopefully be inspired to go out and make their own impact up and above what they do through Adora. Our motto ‘Let’s Do Some Good’ really is an invitation for everyone to get involved.”\r\n\r\n~CEO of Adora, Kyle Thomas\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt is hard to measure what the impact on a daily basis that advertisements for charities will have not only on a charity\'s current loyal supporters, but it can’t help but change the culture once the user base reaches a certain threshold.  When people who already feel like giving, take additional steps to support their causes and share the good they are doing with their friends, the hope is that what is now a trend in charitable giving can be taken viral.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe act of doing something and sharing it with one’s friends has real power in today’s social media driven world.  Consider for a moment the positive impact that the viral videos of people dumping buckets of icy water over their heads is doing for ASL as far as driving exposure and donations to that cause.  How easy would it be for each of those video makers to recommend installing a mobile app that will fund the ALS Association every month on their behalf.  Who knows but that Adora may change society and in the not too distant future, the US may be giving at 3% of GDP.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf your charity has not already signed up to be featured as charity choice for users to fund, there is still a little time to get included when the app launches in mid September. Development professionals should contact <a href=\"mailto:info@getadora.com\">info@getadora.com</a> to learn more or <a href=\"http://goo.gl/bOIutf\">click here to sign up for funding</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf individuals wish to recommend a charity and pledge to support that charity through installing the Adora Charity App,  they may submit those <a href=\"http://goo.gl/60LSzX\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCitations: <a href=\"http://www.forbes.com/sites/tomwatson/2014/06/17/annual-philanthropy-numbers-on-the-rise-u-s-giving-nears-pre-recession-levels/\">http://www.forbes.com/sites/tomwatson/2014/06/17/annual-philanthropy-numbers-on-the-rise-u-s-giving-nears-pre-recession-levels/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.cnbc.com/id/101240935\">http://www.cnbc.com/id/101240935</a>','Philanthropy in Vogue - Charitable Giving Approaches Pre Recession Levels','','inherit','open','open','','484-revision-v1','','','2014-09-04 00:26:23','2014-09-04 00:26:23','',484,'http://getadora.com/484-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(487,6,'2014-09-04 00:31:08','2014-09-04 00:31:08','','david','','inherit','open','open','','david','','','2014-09-04 00:31:08','2014-09-04 00:31:08','',482,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/david.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(488,1,'2014-09-04 00:34:29','2014-09-04 00:34:29','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The Adora project uses the power of Ad Revenue + User Engagement to = Charitable giving.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our passion is to do as much good as we possibly can.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what drives our every move, what makes our hearts burn to work harder, longer, and smarter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We then will use our example to start a movement, a change in not just corporate giving but in private giving too. We stand for the principle that even a dollar here or $5 there can make a difference--that you don\'t have to be wealthy to give and you don\'t have to give money to make an impact.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/RXMnDG3QzxE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a title=\"The app\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/adora-app/\">Read more about our app</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want more info <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">contact us</a>.</strong></p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-09-04 00:34:29','2014-09-04 00:34:29','',2,'http://getadora.com/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(490,6,'2014-09-05 06:06:33','2014-09-05 06:06:33','The data is in and philanthropy is back in style.  In his <a title=\"Annual Philanthropy Numbers On The Rise: U.S. Giving Near