steps of digital marketing companies like Google, Facebook, Twitter, Yahoo, as well as more traditional industries like Television, Radio, Newspapers, Magazines and even Billboards. Advertising is all around us and it is a multi-billion dollar industry yet what impact are these platforms making?\n\nThere is a very important difference between all of these other advertising methods and Adora. We are <strong>THE FIRST</strong> main stream advertising platform that is focused on <strong>doing good</strong> with our advertising revenue, revenue created by our efforts in partnership with you, our users.\n\nIf you want to learn more about our focus on Charity work, stop reading this page and <strong><a title=\"Charity+\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">PLEASE click here</a>.</strong>  Our message about what drives us is the most important thing we would have you read on our entire site.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>How the Adora App Works</h3>\nTraditional advertising, even newer methods like Facebook and Google ads, are not working anymore. Raise your hand if you ignore most every ad around you... You have your hand up don\'t you?\n\nWe have found an easy way to advertise, a way that is not intrusive, easy to ignore &amp; interact with all at the same time.\n\nHow you might ask? Through the lockscreen on your mobile device! Take a look at an example of our ad (to the right our just below), yes we know that hulk wouldn\'t really need a band-aid but it is a cool ad. It is a beautiful, full screen ad. It is easy to smile at and simply move on OR it is just as easy to give it a thumbs up and go view the ad.\n\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-641 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LearningSmall.jpg\" alt=\"LearningSmall\" width=\"720\" height=\"400\" />If you\'ve ever used Pandora for music you know how the <strong>thumbs up / thumbs down</strong> interaction works. You get to let us know when you like an ad or when you don\'t.\n\nIf an ad is just not interesting <strong>simply ignore it, and unlock your device</strong> and we\'ll get that message too.\n\nBUT what if you <strong><em>do</em></strong> like the ad but don\'t have time to check it out right now? Simply <strong>Save it for later</strong> (see the folders icon) and unlock the device. You can have this option send you and email or it will just be waiting for you when you open the Adora app.\n\nWhether you are of aren\'t interested in an ad you may know someone else who might be interested, so we let you <strong>share an ad</strong> with an individual or with all your social media buddies.\n\nSoon you\'ll be able to do even more right from the lockscreen, you\'ll love what we have coming!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Adora is More Than Just Ads</h3>\n<img class=\" wp-image-654 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/MoreThanAdsSmall.jpg\" alt=\"MoreThanAdsSmall\" width=\"400\" height=\"193\" />Adora is still in Beta testing and we are going to be delivering more than just ads to your lockscreen.\n\nAs we go through testing we\'ll be finding out the best ratio of ads, offers, deals, news, or even personal images. How will we be determining the best ratios? Well that is up to you. How much good do you wan tot do, how many ads do you want to see vs news, personal images or other content? As you use the app you will tell us with every thumbs up or down.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Adora is easy but we want more from all of you...</h3>\nThe Adora app is free to download and use but we want more from everyone. We would love if you would donate out of pocket right now! Don\'t wait to start doing more good. We also want you to go out and find a way to volunteer, when you download Adora you will start seeing volunteer opportunities but we don\'t want you to wait for those either.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Donate Now</h3>\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart-300x248.jpg\" alt=\"StandingApart\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" /></a>What sets us apart</h3>\nNo matter how amazing the performance of our ads the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue spent in any other way, this is what sets us apart, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side will work.</a>\n\nIf you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a>','The App','','inherit','open','open','','60-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-05 04:23:11','2014-10-05 04:23:11','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(670,6,'2014-10-06 11:51:36','2014-10-06 11:51:36','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-595 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\" alt=\"AffiliateProgram\" width=\"470\" height=\"394\" /></a>Hi, welcome to our info page on the Adora Affiliate Program.\r\n\r\nWe want you to promote our app to your customers, lists, blog readers, social networking followers, and anyone else or through any other avenue where you have a voice. In return for this you have two amazing rewards:\r\n\r\nYou\'ll feel great knowing that you\'ve helped do more good through Adora and that is a great feeling but...\r\nWe all know that an Affiliate Program needs to help you out financially so...\r\n\r\nWe have one of, if not the best, affiliate programs around:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get <em>up to*</em> <strong>$2.50</strong>/user/month for up to 12 months - how long depends on how soon you become an affiliate.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before October 23rd will keep their revenue for 12 months</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before November 19th will keep their revenue for 9 months</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before December 17th will keep their revenue for 6 months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour users will need to download the Adora App, it\'s free, and as long as they keep using the app you can earn your referral fee. Our Affiliate Program is expected to change dramatically in 2015, but any affiliate who signs up before the December 17th deadline will be able to continue adding users through 2015.\r\n\r\n<em>*up to $2.50 means that how much you make per user depends on how often your customers user their phone.</em>\r\n\r\nOur app is coming out soon, but our advertising will not begin until <em>late October / early November</em>. We pay our affiliates after we get paid by the advertisers, so you can expect your first payment from Adora to come around the 15th of December, just in time for the holidays.\r\n\r\nTo get started fill out this form and we\'ll get you into our affiliate program.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRW5XG6L3866\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Affiliate Program','','inherit','open','open','','536-revision-v1','','','2014-10-06 11:51:36','2014-10-06 11:51:36','',536,'http://getadora.com/536-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(671,6,'2014-10-06 12:02:28','2014-10-06 12:02:28','No matter who you are you can do good through Adora.\r\n\r\nOur apps will be launching soon, and as an individual you can download the app and do good by installing it and sharing the app with your friends.  You may have a few hundred friends between your email contacts and social networks who would help you support the cause you feel most passionately about - <a title=\"The app\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/adora-app/\">Learn more about how our app works</a>.\r\n\r\nIf you are a charity you are already doing good and <strong>we thank you so much</strong> for being ready to do even more through Adora! <a title=\"Adora Charity Funding Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Learn more about our Charity Program</a>.\r\n\r\nIf you are a business, blogger, artist, or anyone with a following you can promote Adora and <a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">take part in one of the best Affiliate Programs around</a>.\r\n\r\nIf you advertise, even if you have a small budget, who would you rather advertise with? Facebook, Google, Twitter, even TV &amp; Radio are great advertising outlets BUT what if you could get the same results AND do good with each ad dollar you spend. This is what you do when you advertise through Adora. <a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Learn more about how to start advertising with Adora</a>.\r\n\r\nWe want to give everyone a way to make an impact, we know that the only way we can really change the world, to really do good on a scale that makes noise, is to get everyone involved. Come join us here at Adora, and do as much good as you can.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/GoodTogether.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-614\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/GoodTogether.jpg\" alt=\"GoodTogether\" width=\"884\" height=\"363\" /></a>','How You Can Help','','inherit','open','open','','611-revision-v1','','','2014-10-06 12:02:28','2014-10-06 12:02:28','',611,'http://getadora.com/611-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(672,6,'2014-10-06 12:14:31','2014-10-06 12:14:31','Adora exists to help you do more good.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Charity.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-208 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Charity.jpg\" alt=\"Charity\" width=\"401\" height=\"244\" /></a>Through Adora we hope to help all of our charitable partners do more good through better exposure, more consistent funding, and increased volunteer involvement.\r\n\r\nHere is how it works:\r\n\r\nThe Adora Charity Funding Program requires a very simple formal agreement, Adora doesn\'t even need your donor list to engage your supporters, we trust you to do that. When you become a Charity Partner you will be part of our <a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\" target=\"_blank\">Affiliate Program</a> but with some amazing advantages.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your users will bring you funding for as long as they use the app, no 12-6 month expiration.</li>\r\n	<li>You will receive free advertising on the network that grows with your Adora user base (Ask us about this)</li>\r\n	<li>Free ad design consulting</li>\r\n	<li>Access to a Charity specific reporting profile - Track ad performance and donations in real time</li>\r\n	<li>Donations will be made Monthly &amp; Quarterly (75/25 ask us), we pay for transaction fees</li>\r\n	<li>Earn a guaranteed referral fee every month for every user you bring to us</li>\r\n	<li>Donations will not be limited, users will be able to donate as much as they want to your charity</li>\r\n	<li>Listed on the Featured Charity List (users will choose one regardless of referral source)</li>\r\n	<li>Your Charity will eligible for Adora Grant Funding (Ask us)</li>\r\n	<li>You may be invited to be part of the beta Social Network focused on doing good, volunteer work, spontaneous good works, and of course, charitable giving (coming in 2016).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe key to your funding and the scope of all of these benefits will be based on your effort in promoting your Charity on the Adora App.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-652 size-medium\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Choice\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>Special Crowdfunding Opportunity</strong>\r\n\r\nHere in October, in the next few weeks, we will be lunching a crowdfuning campaign. In this campaign we will be giving 30-50% of our total raised to charities that help us promote the campaign. We\'ll tell you more once you are on board.\r\n\r\nWe’re planning a very aggressive PR campaign that will lead up through the holiday season. During this period we will be visiting some of our partner charities to record and document the use of funds we’ve donated. These professionally produced videos will be available for your charity to use as well as Adora’s use. This exposure will encourage others to go out and do more good.\r\n\r\nBy partnering with us we will be able to work together to do more good.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to receive more information, please fill out and return the ‘Letter of Interest’ section below and we will contact you to talk about how to become an Adora partner\r\n\r\n<i>*Note: This offer is subject to change at any time, and may no longer be available after October 23rd.</i>\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRWR8S5X4Z7N\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Charity Funding Program','','inherit','open','open','','68-revision-v1','','','2014-10-06 12:14:31','2014-10-06 12:14:31','',68,'http://getadora.com/68-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(673,6,'2014-10-06 12:26:48','2014-10-06 12:26:48','','Changing The Way We All Think About Funding Charity','','publish','closed','closed','','dan_pallotta-change','','','2014-10-06 12:26:48','2014-10-06 12:26:48','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=surl&#038;p=673',0,'surl','',0),(675,3,'2014-10-08 02:08:14','2014-10-08 02:08:14','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our passion at Adora is to do as much good as we possibly can.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what drives our every action and what makes our hearts burn to work harder, longer, and smarter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adora will ignite this passion in others to start a movement that is contagious, which will lead to a change in not just corporate giving but also in private giving too. Adora stands for the principle that even a dollar here or $5 there can make a difference--that you don\'t have to be wealthy to give and you don\'t have to give money to make an impact.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/RXMnDG3QzxE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Read more <a title=\"Charity+\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">about Adora</a> or find out more <a title=\"The app\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/adora-app/\">about the Adora app</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you would like to talk more or for additional info please feel free to <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">contact us</a>.</strong></p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-10-08 02:08:14','2014-10-08 02:08:14','',2,'http://getadora.com/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(676,3,'2014-10-08 02:29:28','2014-10-08 02:29:28','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many people would love to do more...</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So why isn\'t more getting done?</strong></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Many of us believe that unless our donation is large, it doesn\'t make a difference. Or that unless we spend hours or days volunteering, then anything less is not worth the small impact.\n\nAt Adora we are not asking our users to change their mobile device use. Our users don\'t even have to open our app or take any more time out of their busy days to do good through Adora.\n\nOur app gives our users a choice they have never had before--to choose where their advertising earnings go. We make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\n\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-652\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\" alt=\"Choice\" width=\"884\" height=\"498\" /></a>\n\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">The Adora app is simple--the advertising pays for charity work, but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The Adora app will also make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference, but if 1 million or 10 million users all donate, then those dollars add up!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"421\" height=\"258\" /> Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see  us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible. And oh the good that could be done with that  kind  of donation every month!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company  in the world.</strong></p>\n But once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish. We must change the way we look at charitable  organizations.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"> Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses. Be it a hashtag trending on twitter, a viral video, or dumping ice water on our heads. We know there are few better ways to move mountains than through the power of numbers. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below. Better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/bfAzi6D5FpM\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n\n<h3>Our Vision</h3>\nWe see a world where <strong>everyone is doing good every day. </strong>\n<h3><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></strong></h3>\n<strong> It is our vision to lead a change in private &amp; corporate social activity by becoming the most charitable company in  the world by 2020.</strong>\n\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such a lofty goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-  tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Even the most charitable companies never donate more  than 15% of their pre-tax profits. Walmart has been at the top of the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years  with Wells Fargo leading the way in 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account, Pfizer has taken the top spot for the  last 4 years.\n\nWe know these are very large companies, but one of our goals is to reach the point where we are <strong>donating more than 51% of  our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to that point, but how fast  and how much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want help out read more about <a title=\"How You Can Help\" href=\"http://getadora.com/can-help/\">how you can be more involved</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong></p>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-08 02:29:28','2014-10-08 02:29:28','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(677,3,'2014-10-08 02:29:51','2014-10-08 02:29:51','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many people would love to do more...</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So why isn\'t more getting done?</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Many of us believe that unless our donation is large, it doesn\'t make a difference. Or that unless we spend hours or days volunteering, then anything less is not worth the small impact.\r\n\r\nAt Adora we are not asking our users to change their mobile device use. Our users don\'t even have to open our app or take any more time out of their busy days to do good through Adora.\r\n\r\nOur app gives our users a choice they have never had before--to choose where their advertising earnings go. We make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-652\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\" alt=\"Choice\" width=\"884\" height=\"498\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">The Adora app is simple--the advertising pays for charity work, but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The Adora app will also make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference, but if 1 million or 10 million users all donate, then those dollars add up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"421\" height=\"258\" /> Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see  us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible. And oh the good that could be done with that  kind  of donation every month!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company  in the world.</strong></p>\r\n But once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish. We must change the way we look at charitable  organizations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"> Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses. Be it a hashtag trending on twitter, a viral video, or dumping ice water on our heads. We know there are few better ways to move mountains than through the power of numbers. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below. Better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/bfAzi6D5FpM\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Our Vision</h3>\r\nWe see a world where <strong>everyone is doing good every day. </strong>\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></strong></h3>\r\n<strong> It is our vision to lead a change in private &amp; corporate social activity by becoming the most charitable company in  the world by 2020.</strong>\r\n\r\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such a lofty goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-  tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Even the most charitable companies never donate more  than 15% of their pre-tax profits. Walmart has been at the top of the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years  with Wells Fargo leading the way in 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account, Pfizer has taken the top spot for the  last 4 years.\r\n\r\nWe know these are very large companies, but one of our goals is to reach the point where we are <strong>donating more than 51% of  our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to that point, but how fast  and how much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want help out, read more about <a title=\"How You Can Help\" href=\"http://getadora.com/can-help/\">how you can be more involved</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong></p>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-10-08 02:29:51','2014-10-08 02:29:51','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(678,3,'2014-10-08 02:31:07','2014-10-08 02:31:07','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">In the start-up world we have what would be considered a Dream Team. Click on any of us to learn more.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/BenFaanunuSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-299 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/KyleThomasSmall.jpg\" alt=\"KyleThomasSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-297 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/BenFaanunuSmall.jpg\" alt=\"BenFa\'anunuSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/MarkFeriante2Small.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-300 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/MarkFeriante2Small.jpg\" alt=\"MarkFeriante2Small\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JoeMichelsSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-298 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/JoeMichelsSmall.jpg\" alt=\"JoeMichelsSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/SebasteanLoschSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-302 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/SebasteanLoschSmall.jpg\" alt=\"SebasteanLoschSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ChristianSampsonSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-366 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/ChristianSampsonSmall.jpg\" alt=\"ChristianSampsonSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/DevinThorpeSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-425\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/DevinThorpeSmall.jpg\" alt=\"DevinThorpeSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/WayneCarrollSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-426\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/WayneCarrollSmall.jpg\" alt=\"WayneCarrollSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/JoshShapiroSmall.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-427\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/JoshShapiroSmall.jpg\" alt=\"JoshShapiroSmall\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Man-WomanAvatar.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-304 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Man-WomanAvatar.jpg\" alt=\"Man-WomanAvatar\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We are looking for a few good men and women. Are you interested in a challenging, exciting, fulfilling daily struggle? Hard work, humility, creativity, and passion are part of the culture here at Adora.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">We are looking for the following individuals:</p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\" aligncenter\" style=\"height: 27px; width: 657px;\" width=\"569\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Digital Advertising Guru</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Mobile Software Engineer</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Charity Relationship Manager</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">If you think you would not just fit in, but flourish and you could see yourself in a leadership position as we grow, then by all means <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">send us an email</a>.</p>\r\n<iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/zrHlkHdPF4U\" width=\"932\" height=\"524\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>','Team','','inherit','open','open','','64-revision-v1','','','2014-10-08 02:31:07','2014-10-08 02:31:07','',64,'http://getadora.com/64-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(679,3,'2014-10-08 02:36:54','2014-10-08 02:36:54','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-595 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\" alt=\"AffiliateProgram\" width=\"470\" height=\"394\" /></a>Hi, welcome to our info page on the Adora Affiliate Program.\n\nWe want you to promote our app to your customers, lists, blog readers, social networking followers, and anyone else or through any other avenue where you have a voice. In return for this you have two amazing rewards:\n\nYou\'ll feel great knowing you\'ve helped do more good through Adora and that is a great feeling, but...\nWe all know that an Affiliate Program needs to help you in return financially so...\n\nWe have one of, if not the best, affiliate programs available:\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get <em>up to*</em> <strong>$2.50 </strong>per user per month for up to 12 months--how long depends on how soon you become an affiliate.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before October 23rd will keep their reward bonuses for 12 months</li>\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before November 19th will keep their reward bonuses for 9 months</li>\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before December 17th will keep their reward bonuses for 6 months</li>\n</ul>\nYour users will need to download the Adora App. It\'s free. And as long as they keep using the app, you can earn your reward bonuses. Our Affiliate Program is expected to change dramatically in 2015, but any affiliate who signs up before the December 17th deadline will be able to continue adding users through 2015.\n\n<em>*up to $2.50 means that how much you make per user depends on how often your customers use their phone.</em>\n\nOur app is coming out soon, but our advertising will not begin until <em>late October / early November</em>. We pay our affiliates after we get paid by the advertisers, so you can expect your first payment from Adora to come around the 15th of December, just in time for the holidays.\n\nTo get started fill out this form and we\'ll register you into our affiliate program.\n\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRW5XG6L3866\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Affiliate Program','','inherit','open','open','','536-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-08 02:36:54','2014-10-08 02:36:54','',536,'http://getadora.com/536-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(680,3,'2014-10-08 02:37:04','2014-10-08 02:37:04','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-595 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\" alt=\"AffiliateProgram\" width=\"470\" height=\"394\" /></a>Hi, welcome to our info page on the Adora Affiliate Program.\r\n\r\nWe want you to promote our app to your customers, lists, blog readers, social networking followers, and anyone else or through any other avenue where you have a voice. In return for this you have two amazing rewards:\r\n\r\nYou\'ll feel great knowing you\'ve helped do more good through Adora and that is a great feeling, but...\r\nWe all know that an Affiliate Program needs to help you in return financially so...\r\n\r\nWe have one of, if not the best, affiliate programs available:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get <em>up to*</em> <strong>$2.50 </strong>per user per month for up to 12 months--how long depends on how soon you become an affiliate.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before October 23rd will keep their reward bonuses for 12 months</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before November 19th will keep their reward bonuses for 9 months</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before December 17th will keep their reward bonuses for 6 months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour users will need to download the Adora App. It\'s free. And as long as they keep using the app, you can earn your reward bonuses. Our Affiliate Program is expected to change dramatically in 2015, but any affiliate who signs up before the December 17th deadline will be able to continue adding users through 2015.\r\n\r\n<em>*up to $2.50 means that how much you make per user depends on how often your customers use their phone.</em>\r\n\r\nOur app is coming out soon, but our advertising will not begin until <em>late October / early November</em>. We pay our affiliates after we get paid by the advertisers, so you can expect your first payment from Adora to come around the 15th of December, just in time for the holidays.\r\n\r\nTo get started fill out this form and we\'ll register you into our affiliate program.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRW5XG6L3866\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Affiliate Program','','inherit','open','open','','536-revision-v1','','','2014-10-08 02:37:04','2014-10-08 02:37:04','',536,'http://getadora.com/536-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(681,3,'2014-10-08 02:48:16','2014-10-08 02:48:16','Adora Helps Charities Do More\n\nAt Adora we love the good our partner charities are doing. Our goal is to help them execute their charitable missions through providing access to additional funding and outreach to volunteers in the communities they serve.\n\nPhilanthropy 2.0\n\nAdora was created as a way to allow everyone to become a philanthropist.  Through the Adora Charity App,  everyone can participate in charitable giving, even those with no money to give. In this new paradigm of giving, all forms of support for a charitable cause are of worth and the cost of developing support from the lowest tier of the funding pyramid goes away.\n\nAdora Provides the Platform &amp; Technology\n\nAdora creates a consistent and dependable revenue stream for charities to augment the current streams or replace other more costly streams.  Advertisers provide the money and Adora turns anyone with a mobile device who supports your cause into a donor. The same social media, newsletter, mail, radio, and TV development efforts attract a new bottom tier to your funding pyramid with no extra costs or efforts.\n\nGood Works Beget More Good Works\n\nFor those who already donate and volunteer, Adora is an easy way to give more and evangelize for your cause with Adora\'s sharing features. For the new donors that give only through the ad-view funding they generate, it is the first step to engagement and involvement with your charity.  Doing good feels good - each individual will give up as much time and money as they are willing to invest to be a part of your mission and to experience the joy of doing good and helping others.  Adora lowers the bar for giving and opens the door to charity involvement and active volunteer participation.\n\nMoving Forward Together\n\nThe impact we can make together can change the face of charitable giving forever. This is no small promise or opportunity, nor is this a one time event. Every day you can add users and grow your funding and volunteer engagement.  Your social support network can now all be donors and as they recruit others for your cause, they will expand that base to achieve the goals for funding and serving others.\n\nHow it works\n\nThe Adora Charity Funding Program requires a very simple formal agreement. Adora doesn\'t even need your donor list to engage your supporters.  As far as funding programs go, it is more of a fundraising tool than a formal program.  We like to think of it as a partnership where Adora takes all the economic risks, bears all the overhead, pays all the transaction costs, generates the revenue and leaves our partner charities free to focus on their organizational missions.\n\nAll a charity needs to do is to indicate an interest in participating by completing the <a title=\"Adora Charity Funding Program Sign-up\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram\">sign-up form</a>.  Adora will provide an affiliate code and link to share with social media followers and place on the charities direct donation page or other media that reaches their supporters.  Charities benefit proportionally to the degree with which they promote participation.\n\nCharities Gives Much More Than Just Funding\n\nThe funds generated by supporters through their ad view revenue and direct donation is only part 1 of a package intended to change the world, one charity and one mobile user at a time.  With exposure and through the time and resources of Adora  k with us on the launch and continual promotion of the app we can have a closer relationship with you. General features of the joint venture:\n<ul>\n	<li>Free advertising on the network (Ask us about this)</li>\n	<li>Free ad design consulting</li>\n	<li>Access to a Charity specific reporting profile - Track ad performance and donations in real time</li>\n	<li>Donations will be made Monthly &amp; Quarterly (75/25 ask us), we pay for transaction fees</li>\n	<li>Earn a guaranteed referral fee every month for every user you bring to us</li>\n	<li>Donations will not be limited, users will be able to donate as much as they want to your charity</li>\n	<li>Listed on the Featured Charity List (users will choose one regardless of referral source)</li>\n	<li>Your Charity will eligible for Adora Grant Funding (Ask us)</li>\n	<li>You will be invited to be part of the beta Social Network focused on doing good, volunteer work, spontaneous good works, and of course, charitable giving</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\nWe’re planning a very aggressive PR campaign that will lead up to and through the holiday season. During this period we will visit some of our partner charities to record and document the use of funds donated through Adora. These professionally produced videos will be available for your charity to use as well as for Adora’s use. This will encourage others to do more good.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe will choose a select few to be in on our secret regarding how we will be delivering our ads. We want you to be able to tell others, including those you promote our app to, that we really do have a top secret, cutting edge way to deliver ads that will make this program revolutionary.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nBy partnering with us we will be able to work together to do more good.\nIf you would like to receive more information, please fill out and return the ‘Letter of Interest’ section below and we will contact you to talk about how to become an Adora partner','Adora Helps Charities Do More Good','','inherit','open','open','','560-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-08 02:48:16','2014-10-08 02:48:16','',560,'http://getadora.com/560-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(682,3,'2014-10-08 02:48:40','2014-10-08 02:48:40','Adora Helps Charities Do More\r\n\r\nAt Adora we love the good our partner charities are doing. Our goal is to help them execute their charitable missions through providing access to additional funding and outreach to volunteers in the communities they serve.\r\n\r\nPhilanthropy 2.0\r\n\r\nAdora was created as a way to allow everyone to become a philanthropist.  Through the Adora Charity 