. Using an external hypertext link means that you are leaving the Site and Adora is therefore not responsible for and gives no warranties, guarantees or representations in respect to the content of any off-site pages or any other sites linked to the Site. Your linking to the Site, off-site pages or other sites is at your own risk and without the permission of Adora.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>JURISDICTION</b>\r\n\r\nThe software and technical data on this web site is subject to the laws, regulations, orders or other restrictions regarding import to, and export and re-export from, various countries, including export and re-export restrictions that may be imposed by applicable laws of the United States. By downloading or accessing software or technical data, you are agreeing not to import, export or re-export, either directly or indirectly (including transmission and shipment) except in accordance with all applicable laws, and you are accepting responsibility to determine what is necessary to assure such compliance. In particular, but without limitation, you agree not to export, re-export or provide the software or technical data:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>to, or to a national or resident of Cuba, Iraq , Iran, Sudan, Libya, Syria, North Korea, or to any other country embargoed or restricted by the U.S. (This list of countries is current as of July 2002 but is subject to change)</li>\r\n	<li>to anyone on the U.S. Commerce Department\'s Table of Denial Orders or the U.S. Department of Treasury\'s Specially Designated Nationals Lists, or</li>\r\n	<li>to any person or entity who has been prohibited from participating in U.S. export transactions by any agency of the U.S. Government.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nYou are also agreeing not to download, transfer, export or re-export Adora products, technology or software to your customers or any intermediate entity in the chain of supply if our products will be used in the design, development, production, stockpiling or use of missiles, chemical or biological weapons or for nuclear end uses, without obtaining prior authorization from the U.S. Government.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n\r\n\r\n</strong>','Terms','','inherit','open','open','','692-revision-v1','','','2014-10-16 23:25:47','2014-10-16 23:25:47','',692,'http://getadora.com/692-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(694,1,'2014-10-16 23:51:41','2014-10-16 23:51:41','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Updated: October 16, 2014</b></p>\r\nThank you for using the Adora app and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\r\n\r\n1. User Content. By submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our website or App; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\r\n\r\n2. Users Outside of the United States. Your Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the website or the App shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\r\n\r\n3. Collection of Personal and Non-Personal Information. Adora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access Facebook to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to share and interact via Facebook, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts.\r\n\r\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other App and website use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our website or App that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n4. Use of Personal and Non-Personal Information. Adora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your User, Charity, Advertiser, or Affiliate account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending e-mails or text messages to your smartphone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been made anonymous and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to Users in particular cities or regions, determining the donation amounts generated by Users by using the Service, or identifying a segment of Users which Advertisers, Charities, or Affiliates have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers, Charities, or Affiliates will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\r\n\r\n5. Disclosure of Personal and Non-Personal (“Anonymous”) Information. If you are a User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, anonymous, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, Charities, Non-Profits, Affiliates or other sponsored partners, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our website, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, charities, affiliates, sponsors, partners, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking share feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the website or App and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n6. Accessing and Updating Personal Information. When you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, App or website. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\r\n\r\n7. Cookies and Automatic Information Gathering Technologies. We and our Advertisers or other authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our website or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our website, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our website. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, and maintaining your accumulated donations generated account). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our website, App or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our website and App, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our website. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the website or App. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the website, you may be served an advertisement from or about the website for the same or a similar product when you visit a website other than the Adora website. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the website, the App or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our website or App which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our website or App or complete certain actions on our website, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our website or App. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\r\n\r\n8. Our Policy on Minors. We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the App and website). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\r\n\r\n9. Information Security. We utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\r\n\r\n10. Your California Privacy Rights. A California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our website. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our website. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are a User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\r\n\r\n11. Public Message Boards and Other Online Forums. Please note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our website or App, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our website or App and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\r\n\r\n12. Changes to this Policy. Adora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the website or App. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the top of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our website, App or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR WEBSITE AND APP AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the website, App and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\r\n\r\nHow to contact us. To ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\r\n\r\nAdora, Inc.\r\nAttn: Privacy Matters\r\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:support@getAdora.com\">support@getAdora.com</a>','Privacy Policy','','publish','open','closed','','privacy','','','2014-10-17 20:27:20','2014-10-17 20:27:20','',0,'http://getadora.com/?page_id=694',9,'page','',0),(695,1,'2014-10-16 23:51:41','2014-10-16 23:51:41','Privacy Policy','Privacy','','inherit','open','open','','694-revision-v1','','','2014-10-16 23:51:41','2014-10-16 23:51:41','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(696,1,'2014-10-17 00:15:51','2014-10-17 00:15:51','Privacy Policy','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 00:15:51','2014-10-17 00:15:51','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(697,1,'2014-10-17 05:12:50','2014-10-17 05:12:50','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Adora Inc. Privacy Policy</b></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Revised: October 16, 2014</b></p>\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\n\nThank you for using Adora Inc. and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\n\n1. USER CONTENT.\n\nBy submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our Site or Application; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\n\n2. USERS OUTSIDE OF THE UNITED STATES.\n\nYour Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the Site or the Application shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Types of Data We Collect. “Personal Information” means information that allows someone to identify or contact you, including, for example, your name, address, telephone number, e-mail address, as well as any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. “Anonymous Information” means data that is not associated with or linked to your Personal Information. Anonymous Information does not, by itself, permit the identification of individual persons. We collect Personal Information and Anonymous Information, as described below through the Services.</p>\n3. COLLECTION OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION.\n\nAdora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access \"Facebook Connect\" to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to use the Facebook Connect feature, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook Connect. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook Connect service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts\n\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other Application and Site use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our Site or Application that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\n\n4. USE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\n\nAdora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your End User or Advertiser account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending text messages to your cell phone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been de-identified and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to End Users in particular cities or regions, determining the number of Reward Points to offer End Users, or identifying a segment of End Users which Advertisers have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\n\n5. DISCLOSURE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\n\nIf you are an End User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, de-identified, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our Site, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking function to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the Site or Application and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\n\n6. ACCESSING AND UPDATING PERSONAL INFORMATION\n\nWhen you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, Application or Site. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\n\n7. COOKIES AND AUTOMATIC INFORMATION GATHERING TECHNOLOGIES\n\nWe and our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our Site or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our Site, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our Site. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, maintaining and redeeming your Rewards Points). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our Site, Application or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our Site and Application, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our Site. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the Site or Application. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the Site, you may be served an advertisement from or about the Site for the same or a similar product when you visit a site other than the Adora Site. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the Site, the Application or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our Site or Application which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our Site or Application or complete certain actions on our site, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our Site or Application. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\n\n8. OUR POLICY ON MINORS\n\nWe do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the Application and Site). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\n\n9. INFORMATION SECURITY\n\nWe utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\n\n10. YOUR CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS\n\nA California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our Site. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our Site. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are an End User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\n\n11. PUBLIC MESSAGE BOARDS AND OTHER ONLINE FORUMS\n\nPlease note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our Site or Application, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our Site or Application and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\n\n12. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY\n\nAdora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the Site or Application. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the bottom of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our Site, Application or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR SITE AND APPLICATION AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the Site, Application and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nHOW TO CONTACT US\n\nTo ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\n\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\n\nAdora, Inc.\nAttn: Privacy Matters\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\nScottsdale, Arizona\n\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:support@getAdora.com\">support@getAdora.com</a>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-17 05:12:50','2014-10-17 05:12:50','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(705,3,'2014-10-17 06:33:23','2014-10-17 06:33:23','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Updated: October 16, 2014</b></p>\r\nThank you for using the Adora app and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\r\n\r\n1. User Content. By submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our website or App; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\r\n\r\n2. Users Outside of the United States. Your Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the website or the App shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\r\n\r\n3. Collection of Personal and Non-Personal Information. Adora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access Facebook to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to share and interact via Facebook, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts.\r\n\r\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other App and website use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our website or App that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n4. Use of Personal and Non-Personal Information. Adora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your User, Charity, Advertiser, or Affiliate account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending e-mails or text messages to your smartphone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been made anonymous and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to Users in particular cities or regions, determining the donation amounts generated by Users by using the Service, or identifying a segment of Users which Advertisers, Charities, or Affiliates have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers, Charities, or Affiliates will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\r\n\r\n5. Disclosure of Personal and Non-Personal (“Anonymous”) Information. If you are a User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, anonymous, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, Charities, Non-Profits, Affiliates or other sponsored partners, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our website, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, charities, affiliates, sponsors, partners, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking share feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the website or App and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n6. Accessing and Updating Personal Information. When you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, App or website. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\r\n\r\n7. Cookies and Automatic Information Gathering Technologies. We and our Advertisers or other authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our website or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our website, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our website. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, and maintaining your accumulated donations generated account). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our website, App or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our website and App, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our website. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the website or App. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the website, you may be served an advertisement from or about the website for the same or a similar product when you visit a website other than the Adora website. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the website, the App or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our website or App which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our website or App or complete certain actions on our website, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our website or App. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\r\n\r\n8. Our Policy on Minors. We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the App and website). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\r\n\r\n9. Information Security. We utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\r\n\r\n10. Your California Privacy Rights. A California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our website. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our website. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are a User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\r\n\r\n11. Public Message Boards and Other Online Forums. Please note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our website or App, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our website or App and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\r\n\r\n12. Changes to this Policy. Adora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the website or App. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the top of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our website, App or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR WEBSITE AND APP AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the website, App and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\r\n\r\nHow to contact us. To ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\r\n\r\nAdora, Inc.\r\nAttn: Privacy Matters\r\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:support@getAdora.com\">support@getAdora.com</a>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 06:33:23','2014-10-17 06:33:23','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(704,3,'2014-10-17 06:29:20','2014-10-17 06:29:20','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Adora Inc. Privacy Policy</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Revised: October 16, 2014</b></p>\r\nThank you for using the Adora app and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\r\n\r\n1. User Content. By submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our website or App; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\r\n\r\n2. Users Outside of the United States. Your Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the website or the App shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\r\n\r\n3. Collection of Personal and Non-Personal Information. Adora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access Facebook to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to share and interact via Facebook, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts.\r\n\r\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other App and website use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our website or App that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n4. Use of Personal and Non-Personal Information. Adora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your User, Charity, Advertiser, or Affiliate account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending e-mails or text messages to your smartphone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been made anonymous and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to Users in particular cities or regions, determining the donation amounts generated by Users by using the Service, or identifying a segment of Users which Advertisers, Charities, or Affiliates have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers, Charities, or Affiliates will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\r\n\r\n5. Disclosure of Personal and Non-Personal (“Anonymous”) Information. If you are a User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, anonymous, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, Charities, Non-Profits, Affiliates or other sponsored partners, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our website, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, charities, affiliates, sponsors, partners, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking share feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the website or App and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n6. Accessing and Updating Personal Information. When you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, App or website. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\r\n\r\n7. Cookies and Automatic Information Gathering Technologies. We and our Advertisers or other authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our website or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our website, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our website. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, and maintaining your accumulated donations generated account). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our website, App or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our website and App, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our website. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the website or App. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the website, you may be served an advertisement from or about the website for the same or a similar product when you visit a website other than the Adora website. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the website, the App or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our website or App which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our website or App or complete certain actions on our website, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our website or App. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\r\n\r\n8. Our Policy on Minors. We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the App and website). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\r\n\r\n9. Information Security. We utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\r\n\r\n10. Your California Privacy Rights. A California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our website. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our website. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are a User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\r\n\r\n11. Public Message Boards and Other Online Forums. Please note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our website or App, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our website or App and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\r\n\r\n12. Changes to this Policy. Adora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the website or App. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the top of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our website, App or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR WEBSITE AND APP AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the website, App and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\r\n\r\nHow to contact us. To ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\r\n\r\nAdora, Inc.\r\nAttn: Privacy Matters\r\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:support@getAdora.com\">support@getAdora.com</a>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 06:29:20','2014-10-17 06:29:20','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(698,1,'2014-10-17 01:03:18','2014-10-17 01:03:18','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Adora Inc. Privacy Policy</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Revised: October 16, 2014</b></p>\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nThank you for using Adora Inc. and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\r\n\r\n1. USER CONTENT.\r\n\r\nBy submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our Site or Application; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\r\n\r\n2. USERS OUTSIDE OF THE UNITED STATES.\r\n\r\nYour Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the Site or the Application shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Types of Data We Collect. “Personal Information” means information that allows someone to identify or contact you, including, for example, your name, address, telephone number, e-mail address, as well as any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. “Anonymous Information” means data that is not associated with or linked to your Personal Information. Anonymous Information does not, by itself, permit the identification of individual persons. We collect Personal Information and Anonymous Information, as described below through the Services.</p>\r\n3. COLLECTION OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION.\r\n\r\nAdora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access \"Facebook Connect\" to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to use the Facebook Connect feature, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook Connect. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook Connect service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts\r\n\r\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other Application and Site use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our Site or Application that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n4. USE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nAdora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your End User or Advertiser account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending text messages to your cell phone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been de-identified and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to End Users in particular cities or regions, determining the number of Reward Points to offer End Users, or identifying a segment of End Users which Advertisers have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\r\n\r\n5. DISCLOSURE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nIf you are an End User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, de-identified, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our Site, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking function to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the Site or Application and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n6. ACCESSING AND UPDATING PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nWhen you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, Application or Site. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\r\n\r\n7. COOKIES AND AUTOMATIC INFORMATION GATHERING TECHNOLOGIES\r\n\r\nWe and our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our Site or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our Site, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our Site. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, maintaining and redeeming your Rewards Points). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our Site, Application or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our Site and Application, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our Site. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the Site or Application. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the Site, you may be served an advertisement from or about the Site for the same or a similar product when you visit a site other than the Adora Site. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the Site, the Application or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our Site or Application which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our Site or Application or complete certain actions on our site, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our Site or Application. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\r\n\r\n8. OUR POLICY ON MINORS\r\n\r\nWe do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the Application and Site). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\r\n\r\n9. INFORMATION SECURITY\r\n\r\nWe utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\r\n\r\n10. YOUR CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS\r\n\r\nA California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our Site. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our Site. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are an End User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\r\n\r\n11. PUBLIC MESSAGE BOARDS AND OTHER ONLINE FORUMS\r\n\r\nPlease note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our Site or Application, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our Site or Application and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\r\n\r\n12. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY\r\n\r\nAdora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the Site or Application. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the bottom of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our Site, Application or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR SITE AND APPLICATION AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the Site, Application and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\r\n\r\n13. HOW TO CONTACT US\r\n\r\nTo ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nAdora, Inc.\r\n\r\nAttn: Privacy Matters\r\n\r\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\r\n\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\n\r\nEmail: support@getAdora.com','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 01:03:18','2014-10-17 01:03:18','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(699,1,'2014-10-17 01:03:56','2014-10-17 01:03:56','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Adora Inc. Privacy Policy</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Revised: October 16, 2014</b></p>\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nThank you for using Adora Inc. and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\r\n\r\n1. USER CONTENT.\r\n\r\nBy submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our Site or Application; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\r\n\r\n2. USERS OUTSIDE OF THE UNITED STATES.\r\n\r\nYour Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the Site or the Application shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Types of Data We Collect. “Personal Information” means information that allows someone to identify or contact you, including, for example, your name, address, telephone number, e-mail address, as well as any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. “Anonymous Information” means data that is not associated with or linked to your Personal Information. Anonymous Information does not, by itself, permit the identification of individual persons. We collect Personal Information and Anonymous Information, as described below through the Services.</p>\r\n3. COLLECTION OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION.\r\n\r\nAdora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access \"Facebook Connect\" to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to use the Facebook Connect feature, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook Connect. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook Connect service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts\r\n\r\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other Application and Site use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our Site or Application that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n4. USE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nAdora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your End User or Advertiser account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending text messages to your cell phone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been de-identified and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to End Users in particular cities or regions, determining the number of Reward Points to offer End Users, or identifying a segment of End Users which Advertisers have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\r\n\r\n5. DISCLOSURE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nIf you are an End User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, de-identified, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our Site, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking function to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the Site or Application and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n6. ACCESSING AND UPDATING PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nWhen you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, Application or Site. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\r\n\r\n7. COOKIES AND AUTOMATIC INFORMATION GATHERING TECHNOLOGIES\r\n\r\nWe and our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our Site or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our Site, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our Site. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, maintaining and redeeming your Rewards Points). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our Site, Application or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our Site and Application, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our Site. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the Site or Application. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the Site, you may be served an advertisement from or about the Site for the same or a similar product when you visit a site other than the Adora Site. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the Site, the Application or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our Site or Application which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our Site or Application or complete certain actions on our site, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our Site or Application. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\r\n\r\n8. OUR POLICY ON MINORS\r\n\r\nWe do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the Application and Site). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\r\n\r\n9. INFORMATION SECURITY\r\n\r\nWe utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\r\n\r\n10. YOUR CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS\r\n\r\nA California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our Site. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our Site. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are an End User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\r\n\r\n11. PUBLIC MESSAGE BOARDS AND OTHER ONLINE FORUMS\r\n\r\nPlease note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our Site or Application, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our Site or Application and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\r\n\r\n12. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY\r\n\r\nAdora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the Site or Application. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the bottom of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our Site, Application or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR SITE AND APPLICATION AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the Site, Application and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHOW TO CONTACT US\r\n\r\nTo ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nAdora, Inc.\r\n\r\nAttn: Privacy Matters\r\n\r\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\r\n\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\n\r\nEmail: support@getAdora.com','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 01:03:56','2014-10-17 01:03:56','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(701,1,'2014-10-17 05:16:11','2014-10-17 05:16:11','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Adora Inc. Privacy Policy</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Revised: October 16, 2014</b></p>\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nThank you for using Adora Inc. and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\r\n\r\n1. USER CONTENT.\r\n\r\nBy submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our Site or Application; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\r\n\r\n2. USERS OUTSIDE OF THE UNITED STATES.\r\n\r\nYour Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the Site or the Application shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Types of Data We Collect. “Personal Information” means information that allows someone to identify or contact you, including, for example, your name, address, telephone number, e-mail address, as well as any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. “Anonymous Information” means data that is not associated with or linked to your Personal Information. Anonymous Information does not, by itself, permit the identification of individual persons. We collect Personal Information and Anonymous Information, as described below through the Services.</p>\r\n3. COLLECTION OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION.\r\n\r\nAdora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access \"Facebook Connect\" to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to use the Facebook Connect feature, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook Connect. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook Connect service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts\r\n\r\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other Application and Site use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our Site or Application that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n4. USE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nAdora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your End User or Advertiser account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending text messages to your cell phone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been de-identified and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to End Users in particular cities or regions, determining the number of Reward Points to offer End Users, or identifying a segment of End Users which Advertisers have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\r\n\r\n5. DISCLOSURE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nIf you are an End User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, de-identified, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our Site, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking function to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the Site or Application and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n6. ACCESSING AND UPDATING PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nWhen you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, Application or Site. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\r\n\r\n7. COOKIES AND AUTOMATIC INFORMATION GATHERING TECHNOLOGIES\r\n\r\nWe and our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our Site or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our Site, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our Site. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, maintaining and redeeming your Rewards Points). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our Site, Application or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our Site and Application, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our Site. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the Site or Application. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the Site, you may be served an advertisement from or about the Site for the same or a similar product when you visit a site other than the Adora Site. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the Site, the Application or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our Site or Application which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our Site or Application or complete certain actions on our site, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our Site or Application. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\r\n\r\n8. OUR POLICY ON MINORS\r\n\r\nWe do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the Application and Site). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\r\n\r\n9. INFORMATION SECURITY\r\n\r\nWe utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\r\n\r\n10. YOUR CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS\r\n\r\nA California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our Site. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our Site. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are an End User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\r\n\r\n11. PUBLIC MESSAGE BOARDS AND OTHER ONLINE FORUMS\r\n\r\nPlease note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our Site or Application, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our Site or Application and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\r\n\r\n12. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY\r\n\r\nAdora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the Site or Application. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the bottom of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our Site, Application or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR SITE AND APPLICATION AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the Site, Application and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\r\n\r\nHOW TO CONTACT US\r\n\r\nTo ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\r\n\r\nAdora, Inc.\r\nAttn: Privacy Matters\r\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:support@getAdora.com\">support@getAdora.com</a>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 05:16:11','2014-10-17 05:16:11','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(700,1,'2014-10-17 05:13:06','2014-10-17 05:13:06','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Adora Inc. Privacy Policy</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Revised: October 16, 2014</b></p>\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nThank you for using Adora Inc. and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\r\n\r\n1. USER CONTENT.\r\n\r\nBy submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our Site or Application; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\r\n\r\n2. USERS OUTSIDE OF THE UNITED STATES.\r\n\r\nYour Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the Site or the Application shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Types of Data We Collect. “Personal Information” means information that allows someone to identify or contact you, including, for example, your name, address, telephone number, e-mail address, as well as any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. “Anonymous Information” means data that is not associated with or linked to your Personal Information. Anonymous Information does not, by itself, permit the identification of individual persons. We collect Personal Information and Anonymous Information, as described below through the Services.</p>\r\n3. COLLECTION OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION.\r\n\r\nAdora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access \"Facebook Connect\" to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to use the Facebook Connect feature, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook Connect. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook Connect service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts\r\n\r\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other Application and Site use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our Site or Application that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n4. USE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nAdora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your End User or Advertiser account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending text messages to your cell phone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been de-identified and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to End Users in particular cities or regions, determining the number of Reward Points to offer End Users, or identifying a segment of End Users which Advertisers have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\r\n\r\n5. DISCLOSURE OF PERSONAL AND NON-PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nIf you are an End User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, de-identified, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our Site, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking function to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the Site or Application and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n6. ACCESSING AND UPDATING PERSONAL INFORMATION\r\n\r\nWhen you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, Application or Site. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\r\n\r\n7. COOKIES AND AUTOMATIC INFORMATION GATHERING TECHNOLOGIES\r\n\r\nWe and our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our Site or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our Site, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our Site. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, maintaining and redeeming your Rewards Points). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our Site, Application or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our Site and Application, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our Site. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the Site or Application. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the Site, you may be served an advertisement from or about the Site for the same or a similar product when you visit a site other than the Adora Site. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the Site, the Application or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our Site or Application which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our Site or Application or complete certain actions on our site, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our Site or Application. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\r\n\r\n8. OUR POLICY ON MINORS\r\n\r\nWe do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the Application and Site). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\r\n\r\n9. INFORMATION SECURITY\r\n\r\nWe utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\r\n\r\n10. YOUR CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS\r\n\r\nA California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our Site. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our Site. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are an End User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\r\n\r\n11. PUBLIC MESSAGE BOARDS AND OTHER ONLINE FORUMS\r\n\r\nPlease note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our Site or Application, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our Site or Application and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\r\n\r\n12. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY\r\n\r\nAdora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the Site or Application. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the bottom of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our Site, Application or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR SITE AND APPLICATION AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the Site, Application and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\r\n\r\nHOW TO CONTACT US\r\n\r\nTo ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nAdora, Inc.\r\nAttn: Privacy Matters\r\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:support@getAdora.com\">support@getAdora.com</a>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 05:13:06','2014-10-17 05:13:06','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(703,3,'2014-10-17 06:30:13','2014-10-17 06:30:13','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Adora Inc. Privacy Policy</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Version: 1.0</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Last Revised: October 16, 2014</b></p>\r\nThank you for using the Adora app and welcome to <a href=\"http://www.getadora.com\">http://www.getadora.com</a>, a website owned and operated by Adora Inc. (“Adora”, “We”, “Us”, “Our”). Adora provides a mobile application (the “App”, and collectively with the website and all services provided through the website and App, the “Services”) that (i) serves as a content delivery platform that allows Adora and its advertisers, charities, and affiliates to interact with users who have downloaded and installed the App (collectively “Users” or each a “User”) by serving directed content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen and (ii) allows users to view and interact with content through a user’s smartphone lockscreen. Users who interact with content through the Services must do so subject to these terms of use. Certain features of the Services, may be subject to additional guidelines, terms, or rules, which will be posted on the Service in connection with such features. We have prepared this Privacy Policy to describe our practices regarding the Personal Information (as defined below) we collect through the Services.\r\n\r\n1. User Content. By submitting Personal Information through our Services, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy and you expressly consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your Personal Information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through the Services, as well as other information provided to us online or offline by Users, Advertisers, Charities/Non-Profits, or other Affiliates and other customers or users of our website or App; however, it does not apply to information collected from our employees, contractors or vendors.\r\n\r\n2. Users Outside of the United States. Your Personal Information may be processed in the country in which it was collected and in other countries, including the United States, where laws regarding processing of Personal Information may be less stringent than the laws in your country. Information gathered through the Services may be transferred, used, and stored in the United States and in foreign jurisdictions in which we, our agents, service providers, customers and other users of the Services are located. If you access the Services, you consent to the transfer, use and storage of your Personal Information (as defined below) to and in those jurisdictions. The data protection and other laws of the United States and other countries might not be as comprehensive as those in your country. You further agree that all transactions relating to the Services, the website or the App shall be deemed to have occurred in the United States.\r\n\r\n3. Collection of Personal and Non-Personal Information. Adora collects Personal Information in connection with our Services. \"Personal Information\" means information that can be used to identify or contact an individual and may include, for example, your name, by itself or combined with your unique user ID, telephone number, password, gender, date of birth, address, email address, your brand preferences, your Facebook, Twitter or other social media handles, your geographic location if you are accessing the Services from a GPS-enabled mobile device, any other personal profile or account information you choose to submit through our Services, and (if applicable) your company name and business contact information, or any other non-public information about you that is associated with or linked to any of the foregoing data. Adora or its third party payment transactions services provider may also collect credit, debit or other billing account information. You may always choose not to provide Personal Information, but this may prevent you from receiving certain Services. For example, in order to set up a User account, you must provide a valid email address so that you can login and so that we can contact you regarding important account activity. If you do not complete the profile signup process, we will not be able to display Ad Content on your lockscreen and you will not be able to generate ad revenue to be directed to your charity or cause of choice. If you choose to use the share option on the app’s and on our website’s social networking feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking sites, we may collect your user ID and password information for that social networking site as necessary to make it easier for you to log in to the Services or interact with your social networks in other ways (for example, to share Ad Content with your friends on those social networks). Specifically, and without limiting the generality of the foregoing, the Services may allow users to access Facebook to interact with friends and to share on Facebook while using Adora. Should you choose to share and interact via Facebook, Adora may collect certain information about you from your Facebook account, which will be specified at the time you first agree to sign in using Facebook. You can edit privacy settings for posts that appear on Facebook or disconnect the Facebook service by using the privacy tools provided through Facebook. Adora may also collect your telephone number, which we may use to verify users and prevent duplicative accounts.\r\n\r\nAdora may also collect non-Personal or “anonymous” Information (aggregate, non-individually identifiable or demographic information). An example of non-Personal Information is system-related information such as IP addresses, click-through, phone activity and other App and website use information (for example, we typically track each time you click on Ad Content from your mobile device lockscreen), browser and browser speed, bandwidth of your Internet connectivity, general location of your server and the pages of our website or App that were viewed during a visit. We use this information to manage User and Advertise accounts and for internal purposes to help us diagnose problems, monitor traffic patterns and otherwise continually improve our Services. Please note that the Services may provide links to third party sites, such as links to the websites of Advertisers and other third-party organizations, businesses, and merchants that have agreed to make Ad Content and offers available to Users through Adora. We are not responsible for the privacy policies, practices or the content of websites owned by others that you may link to or that may be linked from the Services. Accordingly, we encourage you to review the privacy policies and terms of service of those websites so that you understand how those websites collect, use and share any Personal Information.\r\n\r\n4. Use of Personal and Non-Personal Information. Adora uses Personal Information in marketing products and services to you through the Adora Application; setting up and managing your User, Charity, Advertiser, or Affiliate account; improving online operations; processing transactions (for example, any credit, debit or other billing account information collected from you will only be used to process transactions requested by you); sending e-mails or text messages to your smartphone to inform you about special offers; providing customer service; providing you with newsletters, RSS feeds, and/or other communications or services which you have signed up for or otherwise agreed to receive (for example, messages about special offers); displaying content that is customized to your interests or preferences (for example, we may target you with select custom ads, messages and offers, basing our selections on information, such as brand preferences, that you provided to Adora at the time you registered or at other times); sending account- or transaction-related communications such as welcome letters and transaction confirmations; performing research and analysis aimed at improving our products, services and technologies; and managing our systems. We will only use your Personal Information in the way we specified when it was collected (including as described in this Privacy Policy). We may use your non-Personal Information (including Personal Information that has been made anonymous and/or aggregated) for any reason in Adora’s sole discretion. Any geolocation data will be collected from your mobile device only with your express opt-in consent, and such data will be used for the purpose of delivering customized services, such as displaying Ad Content featuring offers only available to Users in particular cities or regions, determining the donation amounts generated by Users by using the Service, or identifying a segment of Users which Advertisers, Charities, or Affiliates have requested as an audience for viewing of particular Ad Content; however, Advertisers, Charities, or Affiliates will not have direct access to your location and will not be able to view your location on a map.\r\n\r\n5. Disclosure of Personal and Non-Personal (“Anonymous”) Information. If you are a User, in order to effectively manage the Services, your non-Personal Information (including, without limitation, anonymous, aggregated Personal Information) will be disclosed to Advertisers to facilitate such account-related activities and to manage and improve our Services. We may also disclose your Personal Information to Advertisers, Charities, Non-Profits, Affiliates or other sponsored partners, with your express opt-in consent, where such sharing is required to deliver products or services that you have requested (including but not limited to facilitating your receipt or acceptance of offers or fulfillment or redemption of offers). In addition, we may disclose Personal Information and non-Personal Information to companies, agents, contractors, service providers or others engaged to perform functions on our behalf (such as processing of payments, provision of data storage, hosting of our website, marketing of our products and services, conducting audits, and performing web analytics). We may also disclose your Personal Information to third parties when we believe, in good faith and in our sole discretion, that such disclosure is reasonably necessary to (a) enforce or apply the terms and conditions of the Services, including investigation of potential violations thereof, (b) comply with legal or regulatory requirements or an enforceable governmental request, (c) protect the rights, property or safety of us, our users or other third parties, (d) prevent a crime or protect national security, or (e) detect, prevent or otherwise address fraud, security or technical issues. We may also disclose non-Personal Information to our clients, business partners, merchants, advertisers, charities, affiliates, sponsors, partners, investors, potential buyers and other third parties if we deem such disclosure, in our sole discretion, to have sound business reasons or justifications. We do NOT sell, rent, share or trade your Personal Information to third parties for their own marketing purposes unless you have granted us permission to do so. Please note also that if you choose to use our social networking share feature to post information to Facebook, Twitter or another social networking site, anyone who has access to your information through that other site will be able to see your information. Adora reserves the right to sell or transfer information (including your Personal Information and non-Personal Information) to a third party in the event of a sale, merger, or transfer of all or substantially all of the assets of our company, or in the unlikely event of a bankruptcy, liquidation or receivership of our business, and you hereby consent to any such sale or transfer. If any such transfer is required, we will make reasonable efforts to notify you in writing in advance by posting a notice on the website or App and/or emailing you at your contact email address of record, and we will make reasonable efforts to ensure that the transferee will continue to use any Personal Information collected from you prior to the transfer in accordance with the terms of the then-current version of this Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n6. Accessing and Updating Personal Information. When you use our Services, we make good faith efforts to provide you with access to your Personal Information and either to correct this data if it is inaccurate or to delete such data at your request if it is not otherwise required to be retained by law or for legitimate business purposes. We ask individual users to identify themselves and the information requested to be accessed, corrected or removed before processing such requests, and we may decline to process requests that are unreasonably repetitive or systematic, require disproportionate technical effort, jeopardize the privacy of others, or would be extremely impractical (for instance, requests concerning information residing on backups), or for which access is not otherwise required. In any case, where we provide information access and correction, we perform this service free of charge, except if doing so would require a disproportionate effort. Please e-mail us at support@getAdora.com if you need assistance accessing or changing your Personal Information or if you would like to have your Personal Information deleted. Please be aware that if you delete your Personal Information, you may not be able to continue to use the Services, App or website. Also, even if you request that we delete your Personal Information, we may need to retain certain information for a limited period of time to satisfy our legal, audit and/or dispute resolution requirements.\r\n\r\n7. Cookies and Automatic Information Gathering Technologies. We and our Advertisers or other authorized service providers, advertising companies, and ad networks may use various activity tracking technologies, such as cookies, pixels and web beacons, to collect information from any computer or mobile device you use to access the Services about your activities on our website or interaction with our advertisements (see “Information Collected by Third Parties” below). A cookie is a small amount of data stored on the hard drive of your computer that allows your computer\'s browser to store your preferences and allows Adora, our Advertisers, authorized service providers, advertising companies and ad networks to identify you by a unique identifier and associate this with corresponding information in our or their database. Through the use of a cookie, we and these companies may store your non-personally identifiable registration information and user preferences and may also automatically collect information about your online activity on our website, such as the web pages you visit, the links or advertisements you click, or the other actions you conduct while on our website. In addition, Adora may set a cookie on your computer when you view our advertisements delivered on or in connection with a third-party website you are visiting. After a cookie is set, Adora may track how you interact with the Ad Content (for example, registering, purchasing, clicking, browsing, etc.). Most browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies. If you choose to decline cookies, please note that you may not be able to sign in or use some of the interactive features offered on our Services. We do not tie tracking cookies used for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes to any Personal Information you submit while on our site; however, cookies may be tied to your Personal Information solely for purposes of effectuating transactions you have requested and similar purposes related to the operation of our Site (such as managing our relationships with Advertiser and tracking, processing, and maintaining your accumulated donations generated account). They do NOT, however, collect Personal Information. Although we may place or allow third parties to place their cookies when you visit our Site (as described more fully in the subsection below entitled “Targeted or Behavioral Advertising”), we do not have access or control over third party cookies nor does our privacy policy cover the use of cookies by third parties. We may use other standard Internet activity tracking technologies, such as web beacons and similar technologies, to track your use on our website, App or your interactions with Ad Content. A web beacon is a programming code used to display an image on a web page and can also transfer an individual\'s user identification to a database and associate the individual with previously acquired information about the individual. Such information may be used in targeted or behavioral advertising, as well as for the other uses described in this paragraph. We may include web beacons in promotional e-mail messages or newsletters or online advertisements to determine whether messages have been opened or acted upon. We may use the information we obtain in this manner to customize the Services, Ad Content and offers we provide to users via our website and App, to deliver targeted advertisements through such vehicles, and to measure the overall effectiveness of our online advertising, content, programming or other activities. We do not tie web beacons to any Personal Information you submit while on our website. Information Collected by Third Parties: Targeted or Behavioral Advertising. Targeted advertising (also known as behavioral advertising) uses information collected on an individual\'s web browsing or mobile application behavior, such as the pages they have visited or the searches they have made to target advertising to the user based on this behavior. This information is then used to select which Adora advertising should be displayed to a particular individual on websites or mobile applications other than the website or App. For example, if you have shown a preference for a certain product while visiting the website, you may be served an advertisement from or about the website for the same or a similar product when you visit a website other than the Adora website. The information collected is only linked to an anonymous cookie ID (alphanumeric number); it does not include any information that could be linked back to a particular person, such as their name, address or credit card number. The information used for targeted advertising either comes from the website, the App or through third party website publishers. In addition, we may place (or allow third parties to place) cookies and pixels on our website or App which enable our authorized service providers, advertising companies and advertising networks to collect information about our users who view or interact with their or our advertisements on our website or App or complete certain actions on our website, such as submitting an application or registration form. However, we do not tie these cookies and pixels to personal information that you submit on our website or App. The information collected by the cookies and pixels allows us and the companies mentioned above to deliver, and gauge the effectiveness of, targeted advertisements, both on our site and when you are browsing other websites. Some of these third-party advertising companies may be advertising networks that are members of the Network Advertising Initiative (www.networkadvertising.org), which offers a single location to opt out of ad targeting from member companies.\r\n\r\n8. Our Policy on Minors. We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from individuals under 18 years of age. Nor do we authorize users who are less than 18 years old to use the Services (including, without limitation, the App and website). If we learn from the individual or from the individual’s parent or legal guardian that we have collected Personal Information about a person under the age of 18, we will make efforts to delete their Personal Information from our systems within a commercially reasonable period of time.\r\n\r\n9. Information Security. We utilize reasonable information security measures to safeguard your Personal Information. For example, industry-standard encryption (Hyper Text Transfer Protocol Secure a/k/a “https”) is used to protect communications between our servers and our users’ web browsers and mobile devices. Unfortunately, however, no data transmission over the Internet and no method of data storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. Therefore, while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its security.\r\n\r\n10. Your California Privacy Rights. A California resident who has provided personal information to a business with whom he/she has established a business relationship for personal, family, or household purposes (\"California Customer\") is entitled to request information about whether the business has disclosed Personal Information to any third parties for the third parties direct marketing purposes. In general, if the business has made such a disclosure of Personal Information, upon receipt of a request by a California Customer, the business is required to provide a list of all third parties to whom Personal Information was disclosed in the preceding calendar year, as well as a list of the categories of Personal Information that were disclosed. We will not share Personal Information about you with third parties for their own direct marketing purposes unless you affirmatively agree to such disclosure - typically by opting in to receive information from a third party through our website. To prevent disclosure of your Personal Information for use in direct marketing by a third party for its own purposes, do not opt in to or authorize such use when you provide Personal Information on our website. Please note that whenever you choose to share your Personal Information with a third party or allow your Personal Information to be shared with a third party to communicate with you (for example, if you are a User, to facilitate your acceptance and/or receipt of special offers from an Advertiser), your information will be subject to the third party\'s privacy policy. If you later decide that you do not want that third party to use your information, you will need to contact the third party directly, as we have no control over how third parties use information. You should always review the privacy policy of any party that collects your information to determine how that entity will handle your information. California Customers may request further information about our compliance with California\'s privacy law by e-mailing support@getAdora.com. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through this e-mail address.\r\n\r\n11. Public Message Boards and Other Online Forums. Please note that when you choose to post messages and/or profile content on messages boards and other online forums that we may make available on our website or App, such content is viewable by third parties and, in the case of public online forums and any public profiles, is publicly viewable. Accordingly, you should exercise discretion with regard to what Personal Information you post on our website or App and you should not post highly confidential or sensitive information. Adora is not responsible for how third parties who view your Personal Information may use this information (such as to send you unsolicited messages).\r\n\r\n12. Changes to this Policy. Adora may modify or update this Privacy Policy periodically with or without prior notice by posting the updated policy on the website or App. We encourage you to check this Privacy Policy from time to time and to refer to the “Last Updated” date at the top of this document to see when the Privacy Policy was last changed. We may also post a notice of changes to this Privacy Policy by e-mailing you about the changes. Your continued use of our website, App or other Services following the effective date of an updated Privacy Policy constitutes your consent to the contents of such policy. However, we will not apply any material changes retroactively to any information we collected from you before such changes took effect, without your affirmative consent to do so. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO FUTURE CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, YOU MUST STOP USING OUR WEBSITE AND APP AFTER THE EFFECTIVE DATE OF SUCH CHANGES. Please note that upon discontinuing use of the website, App and/or other Services, any Privacy Policy in effect immediately prior to your departure shall continue to be binding on you and applicable to any data or information (including, without limitation, Personal Information) collected from you prior to such departure.\r\n\r\nHow to contact us. To ask questions about our Privacy Policy or to lodge a complaint, please contact us at:\r\n\r\nAdora, Inc.\r\nAttn: Privacy Matters\r\n3260 N. Hayden Rd\r\nScottsdale, Arizona\r\nEmail: <a href=\"mailto:support@getAdora.com\">support@getAdora.com</a>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','open','open','','694-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-17 06:30:13','2014-10-17 06:30:13','',694,'http://getadora.com/694-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(706,1,'2014-10-17 20:27:46','2014-10-17 20:27:46','Adora exists to help you do more good.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Charity.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-208 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Charity.jpg\" alt=\"Charity\" width=\"401\" height=\"244\" /></a>Through Adora we hope to help all of our charitable partners do more good through better exposure, more consistent funding, and increased volunteer involvement.\r\n\r\nHere is how it works:\r\n\r\nThe Adora Charity Funding Program requires a very simple formal agreement, Adora doesn\'t even need your donor list to engage your supporters, we trust you to do that. When you become a Charity Partner you will be part of our <a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\" target=\"_blank\">Affiliate Program</a> but with some amazing advantages:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your users will bring you funding for as long as they use the app, no 12-6 month expiration.</li>\r\n	<li>You will receive free advertising on the network that grows with your Adora user base (Ask us about this)</li>\r\n	<li>Free ad design consulting</li>\r\n	<li>Access to a Charity specific reporting profile - Track ad performance and donations in real time</li>\r\n	<li>Donations will be made Monthly &amp; Quarterly (75/25 ask us), we pay for transaction fees</li>\r\n	<li>Earn a guaranteed referral fee every month for every user you bring to us</li>\r\n	<li>Donations will not be limited, users will be able to donate as much as they want to your charity</li>\r\n	<li>Listed on the Featured Charity List (users will choose one regardless of referral source)</li>\r\n	<li>Your Charity will eligible for Adora Grant Funding (Ask us)</li>\r\n	<li>You may be invited to be part of the beta Social Network focused on doing good, volunteer work, spontaneous good works, and of course, charitable giving (coming in 2016).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe key to your funding and the scope of all of these benefits will be based on your effort in promoting your Charity on the Adora App.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-652 size-medium\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Choice\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>Special Crowdfunding Opportunity</strong>\r\n\r\nNow in October, in the next few weeks, we will be lunching a crowdfunding campaign. In this campaign we will be giving 30-50% of our total raised to charities that help us promote the campaign. We\'ll tell you more once you are on board.\r\n\r\nWe’re planning a very aggressive PR campaign that will lead up through the holiday season. During this period we will be visiting some of our partner charities to record and document the use of funds we’ve donated. These professionally produced videos will be available for your charity to use as well as Adora’s use. This exposure will encourage others to go out and do more good.\r\n\r\nBy partnering with us we will be able to work together to do more good.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to receive more information, please fill out and return the ‘Letter of Interest’ section below and we will contact you to talk about how to become an Adora partner\r\n\r\n<i>*Note: This offer is subject to change at any time, and may no longer be available after October 23rd.</i>\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRWR8S5X4Z7N\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Charity Program','','inherit','open','open','','68-revision-v1','','','2014-10-17 20:27:46','2014-10-17 20:27:46','',68,'http://getadora.com/68-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(711,1,'2014-10-21 15:04:49','2014-10-21 15:04:49','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Mobile App on the Apple App Store\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/adora-charity/id930725815?mt=8\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-707\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/AppStore.png\" alt=\"Adora Mobile App on the Apple App Store\" width=\"270\" height=\"80\" /></a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Mobile App on the Google Play Store\" href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.adoracharity\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-708\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/PlayStore.png\" alt=\"Adora Mobile App on the Google Play Store\" width=\"270\" height=\"80\" /></a></p>','Download Adora','','inherit','open','open','','688-revision-v1','','','2014-10-21 15:04:49','2014-10-21 15:04:49','',688,'http://getadora.com/688-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(709,1,'2014-10-21 15:03:55','2014-10-21 15:03:55','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #666699;\"><strong>Download Adora!</strong></span></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Mobile App on the Apple App Store\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/adora-charity/id930725815?mt=8\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-707\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/AppStore.png\" alt=\"Adora Mobile App on the Apple App Store\" width=\"270\" height=\"80\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Mobile App on the Google Play Store\" href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.adoracharity\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-708\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/PlayStore.png\" alt=\"Adora Mobile App on the Google Play Store\" width=\"270\" height=\"80\" /></a></p>','Download Adora','','inherit','open','open','','688-revision-v1','','','2014-10-21 15:03:55','2014-10-21 15:03:55','',688,'http://getadora.com/688-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(710,1,'2014-10-21 15:04:20','2014-10-21 15:04:20','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #666699;\"><strong>Download Adora!</strong></span></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Mobile App on the Apple App Store\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/adora-charity/id930725815?mt=8\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-707\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/AppStore.png\" alt=\"Adora Mobile App on the Apple App Store\" width=\"270\" height=\"80\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Mobile App on the Google Play Store\" href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.adoracharity\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-708\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/PlayStore.png\" alt=\"Adora Mobile App on the Google Play Store\" width=\"270\" height=\"80\" /></a></p>','Download Adora','','inherit','open','open','','688-revision-v1','','','2014-10-21 15:04:20','2014-10-21 15:04:20','',688,'http://getadora.com/688-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(712,1,'2014-10-21 15:06:33','2014-10-21 15:06:33','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Mobile App on the Apple App Store\" href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/adora-charity/id930725815?mt=8\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-707\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/AppStore.png\" alt=\"Adora Mobile App on the Apple App Store\" width=\"270\" height=\"80\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Mobile App on the Google Play Store\" href=\"https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.adoracharity\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-708\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/PlayStore.png\" alt=\"Adora Mobile App on the Google Play Store\" width=\"270\" height=\"80\" /></a></p>','Download Adora','','inherit','open','open','','688-revision-v1','','','2014-10-21 15:06:33','2014-10-21 15:06:33','',688,'http://getadora.com/688-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(828,6,'2014-12-08 14:52:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','This Christmas and Holiday Season, Adora has joined with our partner charities in <a href=\"http://getadora.com/go/indiegogo/\" target=\"_blank\">Fighting Holiday Hunger</a>.\n\nWinter is a tough time for so many, already with the additional expenses of heating costs and continued increase in the price of basic staple groceries, even our friends and neighbors who get by most of the year have things even harder at time of the year for celebration and thanksgiving.  Some of our neighbors have less and some have none at all.  Some of our neighbors are children, some of them are elderly, some of them are sick, some of them are unemployed, some of them need your help right now.\n\nJoin with Adora right now in providing 1 or several meals for those in need right now.  Your gift to feed a neighbor for the holidays will continue bless your community year round as we complete our Adora Charity App for Android and iOS which will allow every mobile user to fund the charity of their choice each month without having to spend their own money.\n\nPlease<a href=\"http://getadora.com/go/indiegogo/\" target=\"_blank\"> contribute to the campaign</a>, let us know where one of our Food Bank, Pantry, Soup Kitchen, Shelter, or Rescue Mission partners can deliver the meals by commenting on the campaign.  Share the number of meals you have donated through your contribution on social media and inspire your friends and followers to do the same. #dosomegood #Adora','Fight Holiday Hunger','','draft','open','open','','fightholidayhunger','','','2014-12-08 14:52:50','2014-12-08 14:52:50','',0,'http://getadora.com/?page_id=828',0,'page','',0),(717,6,'2014-11-20 23:01:53','2014-11-20 23:01:53','Adora exists to help you do more good.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Charity.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-208 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Charity.jpg\" alt=\"Charity\" width=\"401\" height=\"244\" /></a>Through Adora we hope to help all of our charitable partners do more good through better exposure, more consistent funding, and increased volunteer involvement.\r\n\r\nHere is how it works:\r\n\r\nThe Program is FREE, you will never pay for our services.\r\n\r\nThe Adora Charity Funding Program requires a very simple formal agreement, Adora doesn\'t even need your donor list to engage your supporters, we trust you to do that. When you become a Charity Partner you will be part of our <a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\" target=\"_blank\">Affiliate Program</a> but with some amazing advantages:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your users will bring you funding for as long as they use the app, no 12-6 month expiration.</li>\r\n	<li>You will receive free advertising on the network that grows with your Adora user base (Ask us about this)</li>\r\n	<li>Free ad design consulting</li>\r\n	<li>Access to a Charity specific reporting profile - Track ad performance and donations in real time</li>\r\n	<li>Donations will be made Monthly &amp; Quarterly (75/25 ask us), we pay for transaction fees</li>\r\n	<li>Earn a guaranteed referral fee every month for every user you bring to us</li>\r\n	<li>Direct Donations will not be limited, users will be able to donate to you via our app, and we will pay the transaction fees.</li>\r\n	<li>Listed on the Featured Charity List (users will choose one regardless of referral source)</li>\r\n	<li>Your Charity will eligible for Adora Grant Funding (Ask us)</li>\r\n	<li>You may be invited to be part of the beta Social Network focused on doing good, volunteer work, spontaneous good works, and of course, charitable giving (coming in 2016).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe key to your funding and the scope of all of these benefits will be based on your effort in promoting your Charity on the Adora App.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-652 size-medium\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Choice\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>Special Crowdfunding Opportunity</strong>\r\n\r\nOn November 25th, we will be lunching a crowdfunding campaign. In this campaign we will be giving 30-50% of our total raised to charities that help us promote the campaign. This campaign will focus on fighting holiday hunger and be a great way to acquire users of our app who will fund you monthly once the app begins delivering ads in mid December.  The more users that download our app from your partner link, the less that is spent on non-charity affiliate costs be cause those affiliate fees go to your charity. We\'ll tell you more once you are on board.\r\n\r\nWe’re planning a very aggressive PR campaign that will lead up through the holiday season. During this period we will be visiting some of our partner charities to record and document the use of funds we’ve donated. These professionally produced videos will be free for your charity to use as well as Adora’s use. This exposure will encourage others to go out and do more good.\r\n\r\nBy partnering with us we will be able to work together to do more good.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to receive more information, please fill out and return the ‘Letter of Interest’ section below and we will contact you to talk about how to become an Adora partner.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRWR8S5X4Z7N\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Charity Program','','inherit','open','open','','68-revision-v1','','','2014-11-20 23:01:53','2014-11-20 23:01:53','',68,'http://getadora.com/68-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(718,6,'2014-11-21 01:31:12','2014-11-21 01:31:12','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-595 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\" alt=\"AffiliateProgram\" width=\"470\" height=\"394\" /></a>Hi, welcome to our info page on the Adora Affiliate Program.\r\n\r\nWe want you to promote our app along with causes and charities that are important to you, to your customers, lists, blog readers, social networking followers, and anyone else or through any other avenue where you have a voice. In return for this you have two amazing rewards:\r\n\r\nYou\'ll feel great knowing you\'ve helped do more good through Adora and that is a great feeling, but...\r\nWe all know that an Affiliate Program needs to help you in return financially so...\r\n\r\nWe have one of, if not the best, affiliate programs available:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get <em>up to*</em> <strong>$2.50 </strong>per user per month for up to 12 months--how long depends on how soon you become an affiliate.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up before Dec 1st will keep their reward bonuses for 12 months</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up on December 1st or later will keep their reward bonuses for 6 months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour users will need to download the Adora App. It\'s free. And as long as they keep using the app, you can earn your reward bonuses. Our Affiliate Program is expected to change dramatically in 2015, but any affiliate who signs up before the December 17th deadline will be able to continue adding users through 2015.\r\n\r\n<em>*up to $2.50 means that how much you make per user depends on how often your customers use their phone.</em>\r\n\r\nOur app is coming out soon, but our advertising will not begin until <em>late October / early November</em>. We pay our affiliates after we get paid by the advertisers, so you can expect your first payment from Adora to come around the 15th of January 2015.\r\n\r\nTo get started fill out this form and we\'ll register you into our affiliate program.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRW5XG6L3866\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Affiliate Program','','inherit','open','open','','536-revision-v1','','','2014-11-21 01:31:12','2014-11-21 01:31:12','',536,'http://getadora.com/536-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(719,6,'2014-11-21 01:35:06','2014-11-21 01:35:06','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-591  alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.jpg\" alt=\"LockScreenExample1\" width=\"191\" height=\"400\" /></a> <a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-592  alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.png\" alt=\"LockScreenExample1\" width=\"191\" height=\"400\" /></a>Adora Advertising is different for one HUGE reason... When anyone looks at our ads they KNOW they are doing good.\r\n\r\nWith every other ad platform - Facebook, Google, Twitter, Yahoo, you name it - people are turned off by advertising. They don\'t want it. They didn\'t say \"yes\" to the ads, even if they said \"yes\" to the product or service.\r\n\r\nRight now we are preparing to populate our app with ads. Most large brands and ad agencies need us to have a large user base before they will even consider advertising with us, so like many organizations we have the \"Chicken or the egg\" dilemma.\r\n\r\nThis is where you get the deal...! We are offering small and medium sized B2C startups/businesses the opportunity to secure excellent advertising at a great price.\r\n\r\nRight now, through November 24th<em>,</em> you can test our platform for <strong>FREE</strong>. We are giving away two different ad packages:\r\n\r\nSmall Biz Pack -        10,000 impressions\r\nMedium Biz Pack -   100,000 impressions\r\n\r\n<strong>Fill out the interest form below and we\'ll contact you to start the process.</strong>\r\n\r\nEXTRA: Starting in November we are going to feature a new business every week, and those businesses will receive unlimited* advertising through the end of the year.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRWL6X2G4C68\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Advertising','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2014-11-21 01:35:06','2014-11-21 01:35:06','',51,'http://getadora.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(721,6,'2014-11-24 22:02:27','2014-11-24 22:02:27','','AddCharity','User of the app can add a charity or cause of their choice to fund.','inherit','open','open','','addcharity','','','2014-11-24 22:03:43','2014-11-24 22:03:43','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/AddCharity.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(722,6,'2014-11-24 22:19:21','2014-11-24 22:19:21','','Add a Charity Image','','publish','closed','closed','','add-a-charity_image','','','2014-11-24 22:19:21','2014-11-24 22:19:21','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=surl&#038;p=722',0,'surl','',0),(731,1,'2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=731',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(732,1,'2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=732',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(733,1,'2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=733',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(734,1,'2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=734',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(735,1,'2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-01 16:53:19','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=735',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(827,1,'2014-12-05 18:36:55','2014-12-05 18:36:55','','logo_message','','inherit','open','open','','logo_message','','','2014-12-05 18:36:55','2014-12-05 18:36:55','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/logo_message.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(737,1,'2014-12-01 23:48:59','2014-12-01 23:48:59','','features_adora','','inherit','open','open','','features_adora','','','2014-12-01 23:48:59','2014-12-01 23:48:59','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/features_adora.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(738,1,'2014-12-01 23:49:00','2014-12-01 23:49:00','','first_section_title','','inherit','open','open','','first_section_title','','','2014-12-01 23:49:00','2014-12-01 23:49:00