image_five.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(746,1,'2014-12-02 00:23:25','2014-12-02 00:23:25','','fourth_image_four','','inherit','open','open','','fourth_image_four','','','2014-12-02 00:23:25','2014-12-02 00:23:25','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/fourth_image_four.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(747,1,'2014-12-02 00:23:26','2014-12-02 00:23:26','','fourth_image_one','','inherit','open','open','','fourth_image_one','','','2014-12-02 00:23:26','2014-12-02 00:23:26','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/fourth_image_one.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(748,1,'2014-12-02 00:23:27','2014-12-02 00:23:27','','fourth_image_three','','inherit','open','open','','fourth_image_three','','','2014-12-02 00:23:27','2014-12-02 00:23:27','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/fourth_image_three.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(749,1,'2014-12-02 00:23:28','2014-12-02 00:23:28','','fourth_image_two','','inherit','open','open','','fourth_image_two','','','2014-12-02 00:23:28','2014-12-02 00:23:28','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/fourth_image_two.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(750,1,'2014-12-02 01:00:10','2014-12-02 01:00:10','','fifth_section_bg','','inherit','open','open','','fifth_section_bg','','','2014-12-02 01:00:10','2014-12-02 01:00:10','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/fifth_section_bg.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(751,1,'2014-12-02 01:00:15','2014-12-02 01:00:15','','fifth_section_title','','inherit','open','open','','fifth_section_title','','','2014-12-02 01:00:15','2014-12-02 01:00:15','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/fifth_section_title.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(752,1,'2014-12-02 01:20:18','2014-12-02 01:20:18','','social_icons','','inherit','open','open','','social_icons','','','2014-12-02 01:20:18','2014-12-02 01:20:18','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/social_icons.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(767,1,'2014-12-02 18:10:32','2014-12-02 18:10:32','','home_logo','','inherit','open','open','','home_logo','','','2014-12-02 18:10:32','2014-12-02 18:10:32','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/home_logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(760,1,'2014-12-02 17:21:51','2014-12-02 17:21:51','','user_icon','','inherit','open','open','','user_icon','','','2014-12-02 17:21:51','2014-12-02 17:21:51','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/user_icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(755,1,'2014-12-02 01:36:52','2014-12-02 01:36:52','','footer_bg','','inherit','open','open','','footer_bg','','','2014-12-02 01:36:52','2014-12-02 01:36:52','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/footer_bg.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(763,1,'2014-12-02 17:35:21','2014-12-02 17:35:21','','play_icon','','inherit','open','open','','play_icon','','','2014-12-02 17:35:21','2014-12-02 17:35:21','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/play_icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(757,1,'2014-12-02 17:18:01','2014-12-02 17:18:01','','googleplus_icon','','inherit','open','open','','googleplus_icon','','','2014-12-02 17:18:01','2014-12-02 17:18:01','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/googleplus_icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(758,1,'2014-12-02 17:18:02','2014-12-02 17:18:02','','twitter_icon','','inherit','open','open','','twitter_icon','','','2014-12-02 17:18:02','2014-12-02 17:18:02','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/twitter_icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(759,1,'2014-12-02 17:18:03','2014-12-02 17:18:03','','facebook_icon','','inherit','open','open','','facebook_icon','','','2014-12-02 17:18:03','2014-12-02 17:18:03','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/facebook_icon.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(761,1,'2014-12-02 17:30:47','2014-12-02 17:30:47','<b>1) How did you come up with the idea?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are two parts to the creation of Adora.\r\n\r\nFirst, the lockscreen advertising. This came as a result of consulting with a company that sells cell phone covers and matching lockscreen images. We thought, “Hey that is a great place to put an ad or deal like Groupon, but you don’t have to go digging for it.”\r\n\r\nSecond, the Adora culture. While lockscreen advertising can be convenient to the user, no one wants to see more advertising. Why would anyone voluntarily download an app like that? It was a roadblock until we started to talk about a different part of the company - the culture. We wanted to make it easy for our employees to volunteer, even if that meant giving them time off to do that. Then we talked about giving charities free advertising so they could let people know about volunteer opportunities. Then it finally hit us - we could make the entire company about <i>doing good</i>. Everything changed for us after that.\r\n\r\n<b>2) Why an app?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are very few effective ways to reach a lot of people. Technology has changed the way we communicate and interact. TV, newspapers, radio and even laptops &amp; desktops are all shrinking platforms- the only medium which is really growing is Mobile. Most people have a smartphone.\r\n\r\n<b>3) How will it work?</b>\r\n\r\nThe idea is really simple. We deliver ads, offers, deals, news and sponsored stories to your notification system and lockscreen. In exchange, advertisers pay for the donation a user sends to their charity.\r\n\r\n<b>4) Can advertisers pick where the charitable money goes?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. We give that power to the individual users. The user gets to champion and support their favorite charity. Advertisers will only be able to say that they DON’T want to advertise on the phones of people who support certain causes.\r\n\r\n<b>5) How do I pick my charity?</b>\r\n\r\nUsers can choose a cause and work with any of the great charities already partnered with us, or they can specify their own. We will contact the charity and ask if they want to receive funds from an Adora user.\r\n\r\n<b>6) Where will my personal information go?</b>\r\n\r\nSecurity is very important to us. Personally identifiable information will never be shared with a third party without your express consent. Aggregated user activity may be shared to identify general user characteristics of those who may be most interested in a product, offer, or deal. For example, 13% of men ages 18-34 respond positively to ads for sports related products.\r\n\r\n<b>7) Who will have access to my personal information and how will it be used?</b>\r\n\r\nPersonally identifiable information will never shared with a third party without your expressed consent. From time to time, some of our users may be asked to participate in focus groups to give feedback about ads, products, or services. This will always be at the users discretion.  Aggregated user activity may be shared to identify general user characteristics in the form outlined above.\r\n\r\n<b>8) Can I only donate to one charity at a time?</b>\r\n\r\nCurrently, any money you generate can only be donated to one charity at a time. In the future, we plan to add the ability to give to multiple charities (splitting your donation to them).\r\n\r\n<b>9) How will my charity be paid?</b>\r\n\r\nCharities that are partnered with Adora will receive monthly or quarterly payments directly from Adora by wire transfer or check. The amount donated and frequency of payments will be based on user support. Any charity with less than 100 users will receive quarterly payments. The amount of the donation is based on the information a user gives us and the frequency ads are delivered (how often an app user unlocks their phone or views a notification).\r\n\r\n<b>10) What if the advertiser doesn\'t agree with the cause?</b>\r\n\r\nWhile we don’t anticipate this happening, we want advertisers to experience the same options users do. Advertisers will be given the option to not send advertising to users who support a certain cause.\r\n\r\n<b>11) How often can I change where my money is going?</b>\r\n\r\nEvery Month\r\n\r\n<b>12) How will I know the charity is actually receiving what you say they\'re getting?</b>\r\n\r\nWe are working on allowing users to receive real time updates. This will allow you to track the amount you have earned for your charity during the month and the total amount you have already donated. Charities will also have the ability to track the number of users and the amount they have earned in real time.\r\n\r\nIf you explicitly authorize Adora to share your personal information with your charity of choice, you will be able to request your personal donation information directly from them.\r\n\r\n<b>13) What do you (Adora) get out of doing this?</b>\r\n\r\nWe get the opportunity to change the way charity is done. We are a for-profit company, but we know that when we succeed, the causes we are so passionate about do even better.\r\n\r\n<b>14) How often will more charities be added to the selection?</b>\r\n\r\nWe will add charities as soon as they have been properly vetted. It’s not a long process, but we want to make sure that any charity we partner with will appropriately use funds donated by our users.\r\n\r\n<b>15) How often will I be seeing pop up ads on my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nIn addition to ads, offers, news, and sponsored stories, we want to allow users to add in some of their own content like pictures. We also want users to have the option to decide the frequency of ads. The more ads delivered, the more you generate for your cause.\r\n\r\n<b>16) What if I don\'t want to be associated with a certain advertiser, what can I do to stop getting pop ups from them?</b>\r\n\r\nOur innovative lockscreen will allow users to give direct feedback about ads and advertisers. Simply give it a thumbs down and our learning engine will learn your preferences.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><b>16 a) How does the learning engine work?</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get to rate ads as you see them. This helps us tailor your experience to your preferences. Every time you interact with the lockscreen we learn about the products and brands you love. Over time, you’ll love the deals and offers almost as much as you love the good you are doing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><b>16 b) Why would an advertiser agree to let you thumbs down their ad? </b></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Because feedback (even bad feedback) can be helpful. By letting you rate ads, they get valuable feedback and save money by NOT advertising to people who don’t like them. Maybe they can even adapt and listen to that feedback in a way that could win you over in the future. AND you get to shape your experience; you have more control over what you see with Adora than you do with any other advertising platform.</p>\r\n<b>17) How do I get the ads to stop altogether?</b>\r\n\r\nIn our buildout we will have an option for you to control the frequency of ads you see. You can always delete the app, but in that case, your charity will no longer be funded.\r\n\r\n<b>18) Is there a plan to expand it to gadgets other than my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nAbsolutely! We want to make Adora available on every mobile device (anything that has a touch screen) so that we can do even more for our charities.\r\n\r\n<b>19) Will there be a difference on how the app will work on Droids vs. Apple</b>\r\n\r\nApple has been cautious about letting anyone onto the lockscreen, so initially, Apple users will only get deals and offers through the notification system. We hope that Apple and Apple users will see the tremendous amount of good Adora is doing and allow the full functionality on the lockscreen.\r\n\r\n<b>20) Are there other apps similar to this one?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are a few lockscreens out there, but none with our charity concept or learning engine.\r\n\r\n<b>21) If the app costs me nothing and I am never giving you money, how do the charities get paid?</b>\r\n\r\nAdora gets paid to deliver content. We simply give our users a choice on where some of that ad revenue they generate goes.\r\n\r\n<b>22) What happens to my charitable donation if the charity I am donating to decides they don\'t want to be a part of Adora any more?  Who decides where my donation will go?</b>\r\n\r\nCharities don’t need to partner with Adora to receive funding. If for some reason a charity does not want to receive money from Adora, we will notify you to choose another charity.\r\n\r\n<b>23) What hours of the day will be most popular for ads?</b>\r\n\r\nWe won’t know this until further down the road, but ads delivered around breakfast, lunch, and dinner will most likely be the most popular.\r\n\r\n<b>24) Will I be able to write off my charitable donation on my taxes?</b>\r\n\r\nThe revenue which is generated as a result of the ads will not be eligible for tax reductions. However, other donations made out of pocket by you to a charity through Adora will be.\r\n\r\n<b>25) What is the benefit to your advertisers to participate in this?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are some great advantages to advertising with Adora. One - you know that you get to do some good by advertising with us. That will make the advertisers and audience both happy. Two - amazing targeting capabilities. We can target by demographic, psychographic, geographic, and time. Three - we can also get direct feedback on ads shown. Imagine being able to get real time direct feedback for two different ads of the same product. This would allow companies to find out which ads their audience dislike and which ones they like without having to do more costly focus groups.\r\n\r\n<b>26) How much money will each charity get?</b>\r\n\r\nThe amount of money a charity gets will depend completely on users and the frequency that ads are delivered. The more users a charity attracts, the more they use their phone, the more money they will receive.\r\n\r\n<b>27) How do you determine the percentage? / How much are you actually planning on giving to charity?</b>\r\n\r\nThe amount of money generated by a user depends on their use of their phone. The more they use their phone, the more ads they get delivered, the more money they earn for their charity. Our company goal is to send at least 20 cents out of every dollar to your causes to start. Eventually we plan to give half of every dollar we earn to charities across the world.\r\n\r\n<b>28) What happens to those charities that people don\'t choose to donate to on their own? Do they still get money donated to them?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. Charities will only receive donations from Adora users who have selected that particular charity.\r\n\r\n<b>29) Is the app ever going to hinder me to get to my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. It works the same way your current lockscreen does, except now whenever you unlock your phone you are generating funds for your charity. Doing good doesn’t get any easier.\r\n\r\n<b>30) Will it be every time I access my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. We will allow users to choose the frequency of the ads and offers they receive.\r\n\r\n<b>31) Is having it going to slow down my phone, take too much memory?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. Most advertising content is pretty small. Content will be loaded and stored onto your mobile device when you are connected to wifi. This way it will simply pull a small stored file that takes no time at all.\r\n\r\n<b>32) What does Adora mean?  How did you come up with the name?</b>\r\n\r\nAdora means ‘love’ in portuguese. Mark (one of the founders) and his brother actually came up with it during a discussion about the app.\r\n\r\n<b>33) Who are the people behind Adora?</b>\r\n\r\nWe have had a lot of help in building Adora. There are four founders: Kyle Thomas, Mark Feriante, Ben Faanunu, and David Brinkerhoff. We also have great advisors Devin Thorpe, Brian Critchfield, Wayne Carroll, Bert Martinez, Joe Michels, and Sebastean Losch, Bob Frasure, Christian Sampson, Joyce Sowards, and Heather Faanunu. We wouldn’t be here if not for the loving support and encouragement of all of our family and friends.\r\n\r\n<b>34) How will Adora verify the charity is a legitimate cause?</b>\r\n\r\nWe hope to partner with organizations, like Charity Navigator, who evaluate and score charities based on financial health, accountability, and transparency. We will be staying away from nonprofit organizations that are involved in politics, and instead work with charities that are really making a difference in the lives of people everyday.\r\n\r\n<b>35) Will you provide details on the charity and what they do?</b>\r\n\r\nWe will be featuring and highlighting different charities through the app. We want charities to have the opportunity to get the word out on what they do. We will also be periodically updating you on the good being accomplished because of your donations. This is part of our commitment to you, so that you know that your money is doing good.\r\n\r\n<b>36) Will you accept anyone as one of your advertisers, or will you be selective about who can advertise?</b>\r\n\r\nIt’s important for us to use discretion when advertising products. While we anticipate working with most advertisers, we will not show any imagery which we do not deem as being family- friendly. We know that anyone can pick up your phone, so the ads delivered cannot be suggestive in any way.\r\n\r\n<b>37) Will there be parental controls on the advertisement?</b>\r\n\r\nEach ad will be evaluated on a case by case basis to make sure it is family friendly. We definitely want to make that option available, but we anticipate that the guards we have will be sufficient for most parents.\r\n\r\n<b>38) How will you control whether or not my child may accidentally get an advertisement that may be too adult for them?</b>\r\n\r\nEach ad will be evaluated on a case by case basis to make sure it is family friendly. Ads which may be appropriate for adults but not for the entire family will not be shown on our app. We are sensitive to our charity partners who work in a wide range of causes and must ensure that our ads do not contradict the good work they do.\r\n\r\n<b>39) Would you ever turn down a specific charity? Or are all welcome?</b>\r\n\r\nAny nonprofit organization which does political work will be excluded. Funds from Adora will be limited to charities which address the more immediate need of individuals.\r\n\r\n<b>40) Can you limit your donation to just your local chapter?</b>\r\n\r\nAs we grow, we hope to make this an option.\r\n\r\n<b>41) How will you communicate how much money you\'ve donated to charity?</b>\r\n\r\nThe app will track your monthly donations and the total amount you’ve donated.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','F.A.Q\'s','','publish','open','closed','','f-qs','','','2014-12-04 21:55:27','2014-12-04 21:55:27','',0,'http://getadora.com/?page_id=761',10,'page','',0),(762,1,'2014-12-02 17:30:47','2014-12-02 17:30:47','<b>1) How did you come up with the idea?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are two parts to the creation of Adora.\r\n\r\nFirst, the lockscreen advertising. This came as a result of consulting with a company that sells cell phone covers and matching lockscreen images. We thought, “Hey that is a great place to put an ad or deal like Groupon, but you don’t have to go digging for it.”\r\n\r\nSecond, the Adora culture. While lockscreen advertising can be convenient to the user, no one wants to see more advertising. Why would anyone voluntarily download an app like that? It was a roadblock until we started to talk about a different part of the company - the culture. We wanted to make it easy for our employees to volunteer, even if that meant giving them time off to do that. Then we talked about giving charities free advertising so they could let people know about volunteer opportunities. Then it finally hit us - we could make the entire company about <i>doing good</i>. Everything changed for us after that.\r\n\r\n<b>2) Why an app?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are very few effective ways to reach a lot of people. Technology has changed the way we communicate and interact. TV, newspapers, radio and even laptops &amp; desktops are all shrinking platforms- the only medium which is really growing is Mobile. Most people have a smartphone.\r\n\r\n<b>3) How will it work?</b>\r\n\r\nThe idea is really simple. We deliver ads, offers, deals, news and sponsored stories to your notification system and lockscreen. In exchange, advertisers pay for the donation a user sends to their charity.\r\n\r\n<b>4) Can advertisers pick where the charitable money goes?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. We give that power to the individual users. The user gets to champion and support their favorite charity. Advertisers will only be able to say that they DON’T want to advertise on the phones of people who support certain causes.\r\n\r\n<b>5) How do I pick my charity?</b>\r\n\r\nUsers can choose a cause and work with any of the great charities already partnered with us, or they can specify their own. We will contact the charity and ask if they want to receive funds from an Adora user.\r\n\r\n<b>6) Where will my personal information go?</b>\r\n\r\nSecurity is very important to us. Personally identifiable information will never be shared with a third party without your express consent. Aggregated user activity may be shared to identify general user characteristics of those who may be most interested in a product, offer, or deal. For example, 13% of men ages 18-34 respond positively to ads for sports related products.\r\n\r\n<b>7) Who will have access to my personal information and how will it be used?</b>\r\n\r\nPersonally identifiable information will never shared with a third party without your expressed consent. From time to time, some of our users may be asked to participate in focus groups to give feedback about ads, products, or services. This will always be at the users discretion.  Aggregated user activity may be shared to identify general user characteristics in the form outlined above.\r\n\r\n<b>8) Can I only donate to one charity at a time?</b>\r\n\r\nCurrently, any money you generate can only be donated to one charity at a time. In the future, we plan to add the ability to give to multiple charities (splitting your donation to them).\r\n\r\n<b>9) How will my charity be paid?</b>\r\n\r\nCharities that are partnered with Adora will receive monthly or quarterly payments directly from Adora by wire transfer or check. The amount donated and frequency of payments will be based on user support. Any charity with less than 100 users will receive quarterly payments. The amount of the donation is based on the information a user gives us and the frequency ads are delivered (how often an app user unlocks their phone or views a notification).\r\n\r\n<b>10) What if the advertiser doesn\'t agree with the cause?</b>\r\n\r\nWhile we don’t anticipate this happening, we want advertisers to experience the same options users do. Advertisers will be given the option to not send advertising to users who support a certain cause.\r\n\r\n<b>11) How often can I change where my money is going?</b>\r\n\r\nEvery Month\r\n\r\n<b>12) How will I know the charity is actually receiving what you say they\'re getting?</b>\r\n\r\nWe are working on allowing users to receive real time updates. This will allow you to track the amount you have earned for your charity during the month and the total amount you have already donated. Charities will also have the ability to track the number of users and the amount they have earned in real time.\r\n\r\nIf you explicitly authorize Adora to share your personal information with your charity of choice, you will be able to request your personal donation information directly from them.\r\n\r\n<b>13) What do you (Adora) get out of doing this?</b>\r\n\r\nWe get the opportunity to change the way charity is done. We are a for-profit company, but we know that when we succeed, the causes we are so passionate about do even better.\r\n\r\n<b>14) How often will more charities be added to the selection?</b>\r\n\r\nWe will add charities as soon as they have been properly vetted. It’s not a long process, but we want to make sure that any charity we partner with will appropriately use funds donated by our users.\r\n\r\n<b>15) How often will I be seeing pop up ads on my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nIn addition to ads, offers, news, and sponsored stories, we want to allow users to add in some of their own content like pictures. We also want users to have the option to decide the frequency of ads. The more ads delivered, the more you generate for your cause.\r\n\r\n<b>16) What if I don\'t want to be associated with a certain advertiser, what can I do to stop getting pop ups from them?</b>\r\n\r\nOur innovative lockscreen will allow users to give direct feedback about ads and advertisers. Simply give it a thumbs down and our learning engine will learn your preferences.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><b>16 a) How does the learning engine work?</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get to rate ads as you see them. This helps us tailor your experience to your preferences. Every time you interact with the lockscreen we learn about the products and brands you love. Over time, you’ll love the deals and offers almost as much as you love the good you are doing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><b>16 b) Why would an advertiser agree to let you thumbs down their ad? </b></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Because feedback (even bad feedback) can be helpful. By letting you rate ads, they get valuable feedback and save money by NOT advertising to people who don’t like them. Maybe they can even adapt and listen to that feedback in a way that could win you over in the future. AND you get to shape your experience; you have more control over what you see with Adora than you do with any other advertising platform.</p>\r\n<b>17) How do I get the ads to stop altogether?</b>\r\n\r\nIn our buildout we will have an option for you to control the frequency of ads you see. You can always delete the app, but in that case, your charity will no longer be funded.\r\n\r\n<b>18) Is there a plan to expand it to gadgets other than my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nAbsolutely! We want to make Adora available on every mobile device (anything that has a touch screen) so that we can do even more for our charities.\r\n\r\n<b>19) Will there be a difference on how the app will work on Droids vs. Apple</b>\r\n\r\nApple has been cautious about letting anyone onto the lockscreen, so initially, Apple users will only get deals and offers through the notification system. We hope that Apple and Apple users will see the tremendous amount of good Adora is doing and allow the full functionality on the lockscreen.\r\n\r\n<b>20) Are there other apps similar to this one?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are a few lockscreens out there, but none with our charity concept or learning engine.\r\n\r\n<b>21) If the app costs me nothing and I am never giving you money, how do the charities get paid?</b>\r\n\r\nAdora gets paid to deliver content. We simply give our users a choice on where some of that ad revenue they generate goes.\r\n\r\n<b>22) What happens to my charitable donation if the charity I am donating to decides they don\'t want to be a part of Adora any more?  Who decides where my donation will go?</b>\r\n\r\nCharities don’t need to partner with Adora to receive funding. If for some reason a charity does not want to receive money from Adora, we will notify you to choose another charity.\r\n\r\n<b>23) What hours of the day will be most popular for ads?</b>\r\n\r\nWe won’t know this until further down the road, but ads delivered around breakfast, lunch, and dinner will most likely be the most popular.\r\n\r\n<b>24) Will I be able to write off my charitable donation on my taxes?</b>\r\n\r\nThe revenue which is generated as a result of the ads will not be eligible for tax reductions. However, other donations made out of pocket by you to a charity through Adora will be.\r\n\r\n<b>25) What is the benefit to your advertisers to participate in this?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are some great advantages to advertising with Adora. One - you know that you get to do some good by advertising with us. That will make the advertisers and audience both happy. Two - amazing targeting capabilities. We can target by demographic, psychographic, geographic, and time. Three - we can also get direct feedback on ads shown. Imagine being able to get real time direct feedback for two different ads of the same product. This would allow companies to find out which ads their audience dislike and which ones they like without having to do more costly focus groups.\r\n\r\n<b>26) How much money will each charity get?</b>\r\n\r\nThe amount of money a charity gets will depend completely on users and the frequency that ads are delivered. The more users a charity attracts, the more they use their phone, the more money they will receive.\r\n\r\n<b>27) How do you determine the percentage? / How much are you actually planning on giving to charity?</b>\r\n\r\nThe amount of money generated by a user depends on their use of their phone. The more they use their phone, the more ads they get delivered, the more money they earn for their charity. Our company goal is to send at least 20 cents out of every dollar to your causes to start. Eventually we plan to give half of every dollar we earn to charities across the world.\r\n\r\n<b>28) What happens to those charities that people don\'t choose to donate to on their own? Do they still get money donated to them?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. Charities will only receive donations from Adora users who have selected that particular charity.\r\n\r\n<b>29) Is the app ever going to hinder me to get to my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. It works the same way your current lockscreen does, except now whenever you unlock your phone you are generating funds for your charity. Doing good doesn’t get any easier.\r\n\r\n<b>30) Will it be every time I access my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. We will allow users to choose the frequency of the ads and offers they receive.\r\n\r\n<b>31) Is having it going to slow down my phone, take too much memory?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. Most advertising content is pretty small. Content will be loaded and stored onto your mobile device when you are connected to wifi. This way it will simply pull a small stored file that takes no time at all.\r\n\r\n<b>32) What does Adora mean?  How did you come up with the name?</b>\r\n\r\nAdora means ‘love’ in portuguese. Mark (one of the founders) and his brother actually came up with it during a discussion about the app.\r\n\r\n<b>33) Who are the people behind Adora?</b>\r\n\r\nWe have had a lot of help in building Adora. There are four founders: Kyle Thomas, Mark Feriante, Ben Faanunu, and David Brinkerhoff. We also have great advisors Devin Thorpe, Brian Critchfield, Wayne Carroll, Bert Martinez, Joe Michels, and Sebastean Losch, Bob Frasure, Christian Sampson, Joyce Sowards, and Heather Faanunu. We wouldn’t be here if not for the loving support and encouragement of all of our family and friends.\r\n\r\n<b>34) How will Adora verify the charity is a legitimate cause?</b>\r\n\r\nWe hope to partner with organizations, like Charity Navigator, who evaluate and score charities based on financial health, accountability, and transparency. We will be staying away from nonprofit organizations that are involved in politics, and instead work with charities that are really making a difference in the lives of people everyday.\r\n\r\n<b>35) Will you provide details on the charity and what they do?</b>\r\n\r\nWe will be featuring and highlighting different charities through the app. We want charities to have the opportunity to get the word out on what they do. We will also be periodically updating you on the good being accomplished because of your donations. This is part of our commitment to you, so that you know that your money is doing good.\r\n\r\n<b>36) Will you accept anyone as one of your advertisers, or will you be selective about who can advertise?</b>\r\n\r\nIt’s important for us to use discretion when advertising products. While we anticipate working with most advertisers, we will not show any imagery which we do not deem as being family- friendly. We know that anyone can pick up your phone, so the ads delivered cannot be suggestive in any way.\r\n\r\n<b>37) Will there be parental controls on the advertisement?</b>\r\n\r\nEach ad will be evaluated on a case by case basis to make sure it is family friendly. We definitely want to make that option available, but we anticipate that the guards we have will be sufficient for most parents.\r\n\r\n<b>38) How will you control whether or not my child may accidentally get an advertisement that may be too adult for them?</b>\r\n\r\nEach ad will be evaluated on a case by case basis to make sure it is family friendly. Ads which may be appropriate for adults but not for the entire family will not be shown on our app. We are sensitive to our charity partners who work in a wide range of causes and must ensure that our ads do not contradict the good work they do.\r\n\r\n<b>39) Would you ever turn down a specific charity? Or are all welcome?</b>\r\n\r\nAny nonprofit organization which does political work will be excluded. Funds from Adora will be limited to charities which address the more immediate need of individuals.\r\n\r\n<b>40) Can you limit your donation to just your local chapter?</b>\r\n\r\nAs we grow, we hope to make this an option.\r\n\r\n<b>41) How will you communicate how much money you\'ve donated to charity?</b>\r\n\r\nThe app will track your monthly donations and the total amount you’ve donated.\r\n\r\n<strong>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</strong>','F.A.Q\'s','','inherit','open','open','','761-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 17:30:47','2014-12-02 17:30:47','',761,'http://getadora.com/761-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(766,1,'2014-12-02 18:02:49','2014-12-02 18:02:49','','header_bg_shoes','','inherit','open','open','','header_bg_shoes','','','2014-12-02 18:02:49','2014-12-02 18:02:49','',0,'http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/header_bg_shoes.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(768,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Home','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=768',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(769,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=769',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(770,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=770',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(771,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=771',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(772,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=772',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(773,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=773',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(774,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=774',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(775,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=775',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(776,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=776',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(777,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=777',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(778,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=778',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(779,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','F.A.Q\'s','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=779',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(780,1,'2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 18:29:01','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=780',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(783,6,'2014-12-02 20:20:00','2014-12-02 20:20:00','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">You get to tell Adora the kinds of content you like in your profile and by interacting with the content that is delivered to your lock screen.  When you interact positively with content you will see more offers like that and if there is content that doesn\'t interest you, you will see less of those kinds of offers going forward.  The longer you use the app, the more personalized the expenience.<strong>\n</strong></p>','Adaptive','','inherit','open','open','','506-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-02 20:20:00','2014-12-02 20:20:00','',506,'http://getadora.com/506-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(815,4,'2014-12-02 22:22:38','2014-12-02 22:22:38','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-595 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\" alt=\"AffiliateProgram\" width=\"470\" height=\"394\" /></a>Hi, welcome to our info page on the Adora Affiliate Program.\r\n\r\nWe want you to promote our app along with causes and charities that are important to you, to your customers, lists, blog readers, social networking followers, and anyone else or through any other avenue where you have a voice. In return for this you have two amazing rewards:\r\n\r\nYou\'ll feel great knowing you\'ve helped do more good through Adora and that is a great feeling, but...\r\nWe all know that an Affiliate Program needs to help you in return financially so...\r\n\r\nWe have one of, if not the best, affiliate programs available:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get <em>up to*</em> <strong>$2.50 </strong>per user per month for up to 12 months--how long depends on how soon you become an affiliate.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up on or before December 3rd will keep their reward bonuses for 12 months</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up on December 4th or later will keep their reward bonuses for 6 months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour users will need to download the Adora App. It\'s free. And as long as they keep using the app, you can earn your reward bonuses. Our Affiliate Program is expected to change dramatically in 2015, so partner with us before the December 17th deadline.\r\n\r\n<em>*up to $2.50 means that the amount made per user depends on how often your customers use their phone.</em>\r\n\r\nOur app is coming soon. We will begin advertising through the notifications system which will be paired with full-page, in-app ads. We pay our affiliates after we get paid by the advertisers, so you can expect your first payment from Adora to come around the 15th of January 2015.\r\n\r\nTo get started fill out this form and we\'ll register you into our affiliate program.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRW5XG6L3866\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Affiliate Program','','inherit','open','open','','536-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 22:22:38','2014-12-02 22:22:38','',536,'http://getadora.com/536-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(784,6,'2014-12-02 20:36:36','2014-12-02 20:36:36','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-595 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\" alt=\"AffiliateProgram\" width=\"470\" height=\"394\" /></a>Hi, welcome to our info page on the Adora Affiliate Program.\r\n\r\nWe want you to promote our app along with causes and charities that are important to you, to your customers, lists, blog readers, social networking followers, and anyone else or through any other avenue where you have a voice. In return for this you have two amazing rewards:\r\n\r\nYou\'ll feel great knowing you\'ve helped do more good through Adora and that is a great feeling, but...\r\nWe all know that an Affiliate Program needs to help you in return financially so...\r\n\r\nWe have one of, if not the best, affiliate programs available:\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get <em>up to*</em> <strong>$2.50 </strong>per user per month for up to 12 months--how long depends on how soon you become an affiliate.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up on or before December 3rd will keep their reward bonuses for 12 months</li>\r\n	<li style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Those who sign up on December 4th or later will keep their reward bonuses for 6 months</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour users will need to download the Adora App. It\'s free. And as long as they keep using the app, you can earn your reward bonuses. Our Affiliate Program is expected to change dramatically in 2015, but any affiliate who signs up before the December 17th deadline will be able to continue adding users through 2015.\r\n\r\n<em>*up to $2.50 means that how much you make per user depends on how often your customers use their phone.</em>\r\n\r\nOur app is coming out soon, but our advertising will not begin until <em>late October / early November</em>. We pay our affiliates after we get paid by the advertisers, so you can expect your first payment from Adora to come around the 15th of January 2015.\r\n\r\nTo get started fill out this form and we\'ll register you into our affiliate program.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRW5XG6L3866\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Affiliate Program','','inherit','open','open','','536-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 20:36:36','2014-12-02 20:36:36','',536,'http://getadora.com/536-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(785,6,'2014-12-02 20:47:22','2014-12-02 20:47:22','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-591  alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.jpg\" alt=\"LockScreenExample1\" width=\"191\" height=\"400\" /></a> <a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-592  alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.png\" alt=\"LockScreenExample1\" width=\"191\" height=\"400\" /></a>Adora Advertising is different for one HUGE reason... When anyone looks at our ads they KNOW they are doing good.\r\n\r\nWith every other ad platform - Facebook, Google, Twitter, Yahoo, you name it - people are turned off by advertising. They don\'t want it. They didn\'t say \"yes\" to the ads, even if they said \"yes\" to the product or service.\r\n\r\nRight now we are preparing to populate our app with ads. Most large brands and ad agencies need us to have a large user base before they will even consider advertising with us, so like many organizations we have the \"Chicken or the egg\" dilemma.\r\n\r\nThis is where you get the deal...! We are offering small and medium sized B2C startups/businesses the opportunity to secure excellent advertising at a great price.\r\n\r\nAdvertisers and Businesses can test our platform for <strong>FREE</strong>. We are giving away two different ad packages:\r\n\r\nFree Small / Medium Biz Pack -     10,000 impressions\r\nFree Enterprise Biz Pack -     100,000 impressions\r\n\r\nGreat deals on discounted ad packages will be available for purchase soon through our upcoming indiegogo.com campaign.\r\n\r\n<strong>Fill out the interest form below and we\'ll contact you to start the process.</strong>\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRWL6X2G4C68\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Advertising','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 20:47:22','2014-12-02 20:47:22','',51,'http://getadora.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(786,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Home','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=786',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(787,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=787',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(788,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=788',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(789,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=789',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(790,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=790',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(791,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=791',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(792,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=792',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(793,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=793',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(794,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=794',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(795,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=795',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(796,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=796',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(797,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','F.A.Q\'s','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=797',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(798,6,'2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00',' ','','','draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-02 20:52:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://getadora.com/?p=798',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(802,1,'2014-12-02 21:38:26','2014-12-02 21:38:26','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Charity Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Charities</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Charity Program)</em></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Advertisers</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about Advertising with Adora)</em></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">Affiliates</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Affiliate Program)</em></p>','Partners','','publish','open','open','','partners','','','2014-12-02 21:58:15','2014-12-02 21:58:15','',0,'http://getadora.com/?page_id=802',0,'page','',0),(804,1,'2014-12-02 21:39:03','2014-12-02 21:39:03','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Charity Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Charities</a></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Advertisers</a></h1>\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">Affiliates</a></h1>','Partners','','inherit','open','open','','802-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 21:39:03','2014-12-02 21:39:03','',802,'http://getadora.com/802-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(803,1,'2014-12-02 21:38:26','2014-12-02 21:38:26','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Charity Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Charities</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Advertisers</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">Affiliates</a></h1>','Partners','','inherit','open','open','','802-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 21:38:26','2014-12-02 21:38:26','',802,'http://getadora.com/802-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(805,4,'2014-12-03 09:32:07','2014-12-03 09:32:07','<h3>Adora: A New Option</h3>\n<img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"424\" height=\"208\" />Advertising funds everything we do. We are humbled to follow in the footsteps of digital marketing companies like Google, Facebook, Twitter, Yahoo, as well as more traditional industries like Television, Radio, Newspapers, Magazines and even Billboards. Advertising is all around us and it is a multi-billion dollar industry yet what impact are these platforms making?\n\nThere is a very important difference between all of these other advertising methods and Adora. We are <strong>THE FIRST</strong> main stream advertising platform that is focused on <strong>doing good</strong> with our advertising revenue, revenue created by our efforts in partnership with you, our users.\n\nIf you want to learn more about our focus on Charity work, stop reading this page and <strong><a title=\"Charity+\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">PLEASE click here</a>.</strong>  Our message about what drives us is the most important thing we would have you read on our entire site.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>How the Adora App Works</h3>\nTraditional advertising, even newer methods like Facebook and Google ads, are not working anymore. Raise your hand if you ignore most every ad around you... You have your hand up don\'t you?\n\nWe have found an easy way to advertise, a way that is not intrusive, easy to ignore &amp; interact with all at the same time.\n\nHow you might ask? Through the lockscreen on your mobile device! Take a look at an example of our ad (to the right our just below), yes we know that hulk wouldn\'t really need a band-aid but it is a cool ad. It is a beautiful, full screen ad. It is easy to smile at and simply move on OR it is just as easy to give it a thumbs up and go view the ad.\n\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-641 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LearningSmall.jpg\" alt=\"LearningSmall\" width=\"720\" height=\"400\" />If you\'ve ever used Pandora for music you know how the <strong>thumbs up / thumbs down</strong> interaction works. You get to let us know when you like an ad or when you don\'t.\n\nIf an ad is just not interesting <strong>simply ignore it, and unlock your device</strong> and we\'ll get that message too.\n\nBUT what if you <strong><em>do</em></strong> like the ad but don\'t have time to check it out right now? Simply <strong>Save it for later</strong> (see the folders icon) and unlock the device. You can have this option send you and email or it will just be waiting for you when you open the Adora app.\n\nWhether your interested in an ad or not, you may know someone else who might be. We let you <strong>share that ad</strong> with an individual or with all your social media buddies.\n\nSoon you\'ll be able to do even more right from the lockscreen, you\'ll love what we have coming!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Adora is More Than Just Ads</h3>\n<img class=\" wp-image-654 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/MoreThanAdsSmall.jpg\" alt=\"MoreThanAdsSmall\" width=\"400\" height=\"193\" />Adora is still in Beta testing and we are going to be delivering more than just ads to your lockscreen.\n\nAs we go through testing we\'ll be finding out the best ratio of ads, offers, deals, news, or even personal images. How will we be determining the best ratios? Well that is up to you. How much good do you want tot do, how many ads do you want to see vs news, personal images or other content? As you use the app you will tell us with every thumbs up or down.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Adora is easy but we want more from all of you...</h3>\nThe Adora app is free to download and use but we want more from everyone. We would love if you would donate out of pocket right now! Don\'t wait to start doing more good. When you download Adora you\'ll start seeing volunteer opportunities but don\'t wait, to find those opportunities.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Donate Now</h3>\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart-300x248.jpg\" alt=\"StandingApart\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" /></a>What sets us apart</h3>\nNo matter how amazing the performance of our ads, the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue spent in any other way. This is what sets us apart, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side will work.</a>\n\nIf you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a>','The App','','inherit','open','open','','60-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-03 09:32:07','2014-12-03 09:32:07','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(824,4,'2014-12-03 09:32:38','2014-12-03 09:32:38','<h3>Adora: A New Option</h3>\r\n<img class=\"   alignright\" src=\"http://increasevisibility.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/digital-marketing-banner1.png\" alt=\"Digital Marketing\" width=\"424\" height=\"208\" />Advertising funds everything we do. We are humbled to follow in the footsteps of digital marketing companies like Google, Facebook, Twitter, Yahoo, as well as more traditional industries like Television, Radio, Newspapers, Magazines and even Billboards. Advertising is all around us and it is a multi-billion dollar industry yet what impact are these platforms making?\r\n\r\nThere is a very important difference between all of these other advertising methods and Adora. We are <strong>THE FIRST</strong> main stream advertising platform that is focused on <strong>doing good</strong> with our advertising revenue, revenue created by our efforts in partnership with you, our users.\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn more about our focus on Charity work, stop reading this page and <strong><a title=\"Charity+\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">PLEASE click here</a>.</strong>  Our message about what drives us is the most important thing we would have you read on our entire site.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>How the Adora App Works</h3>\r\nTraditional advertising, even newer methods like Facebook and Google ads, are not working anymore. Raise your hand if you ignore most every ad around you... You have your hand up don\'t you?\r\n\r\nWe have found an easy way to advertise, a way that is not intrusive, easy to ignore &amp; interact with all at the same time.\r\n\r\nHow you might ask? Through the lockscreen on your mobile device! Take a look at an example of our ad (to the right our just below), yes we know that hulk wouldn\'t really need a band-aid but it is a cool ad. It is a beautiful, full screen ad. It is easy to smile at and simply move on OR it is just as easy to give it a thumbs up and go view the ad.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"size-full wp-image-641 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LearningSmall.jpg\" alt=\"LearningSmall\" width=\"720\" height=\"400\" />If you\'ve ever used Pandora for music you know how the <strong>thumbs up / thumbs down</strong> interaction works. You get to let us know when you like an ad or when you don\'t.\r\n\r\nIf an ad is just not interesting <strong>simply ignore it, and unlock your device</strong> and we\'ll get that message too.\r\n\r\nBUT what if you <strong><em>do</em></strong> like the ad but don\'t have time to check it out right now? Simply <strong>Save it for later</strong> (see the folders icon) and unlock the device. You can have this option send you and email or it will just be waiting for you when you open the Adora app.\r\n\r\nWhether your interested in an ad or not, you may know someone else who might be. We let you <strong>share that ad</strong> with an individual or with all your social media buddies.\r\n\r\nSoon you\'ll be able to do even more right from the lockscreen, you\'ll love what we have coming!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Adora is More Than Just Ads</h3>\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-654 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/MoreThanAdsSmall.jpg\" alt=\"MoreThanAdsSmall\" width=\"400\" height=\"193\" />Adora is still in Beta testing and we are going to be delivering more than just ads to your lockscreen.\r\n\r\nAs we go through testing we\'ll be finding out the best ratio of ads, offers, deals, news, or even personal images. How will we be determining the best ratios? Well that is up to you. How much good do you want to do, how many ads do you want to see vs news, personal images or other content? As you use the app you will tell us with every thumbs up or down.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Adora is easy but we want more from all of you...</h3>\r\nThe Adora app is free to download and use but we want more from everyone. We would love if you would donate out of pocket right now! Don\'t wait to start doing more good. When you download Adora you\'ll start seeing volunteer opportunities but don\'t wait, to find those opportunities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Donate Now</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-285\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/StandingApart-300x248.jpg\" alt=\"StandingApart\" width=\"300\" height=\"248\" /></a>What sets us apart</h3>\r\nNo matter how amazing the performance of our ads, the charity work we can do far outweighs the impact of our revenue spent in any other way. This is what sets us apart, so <a href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">read more about how the charity side will work.</a>\r\n\r\nIf you want to learn in more detail how we do this, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a>','The App','','inherit','open','open','','60-revision-v1','','','2014-12-03 09:32:38','2014-12-03 09:32:38','',60,'http://getadora.com/60-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(806,1,'2014-12-02 21:46:45','2014-12-02 21:46:45','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Charity Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Charities</a></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Charity Program)</em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\n\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Advertisers</a></h1>\n<em>(Click here to learn more about our Charity Program)</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">Affiliates</a></h1>\n<em>(Click here to learn more about our Charity Program)</em>','Partners','','inherit','open','open','','802-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-02 21:46:45','2014-12-02 21:46:45','',802,'http://getadora.com/802-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(809,1,'2014-12-02 21:47:21','2014-12-02 21:47:21','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Charity Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Charities</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Charity Program)\r\n\r\n</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Advertisers</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about Advertising with Adora)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">Affiliates</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Affiliate Program)</em></p>','Partners','','inherit','open','open','','802-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 21:47:21','2014-12-02 21:47:21','',802,'http://getadora.com/802-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(808,1,'2014-12-02 21:47:09','2014-12-02 21:47:09','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Charity Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Charities</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Charity Program)</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Advertisers</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about Advertising with Adora)</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">Affiliates</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Affiliate Program)</em></p>','Partners','','inherit','open','open','','802-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 21:47:09','2014-12-02 21:47:09','',802,'http://getadora.com/802-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(810,1,'2014-12-02 21:47:28','2014-12-02 21:47:28','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Charity Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Charities</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Charity Program)</em></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Advertisers</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about Advertising with Adora)\r\n\r\n</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">Affiliates</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Affiliate Program)</em></p>','Partners','','inherit','open','open','','802-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 21:47:28','2014-12-02 21:47:28','',802,'http://getadora.com/802-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(811,1,'2014-12-02 21:47:36','2014-12-02 21:47:36','<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Charity Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/charityprogram/\">Charities</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Charity Program)</em></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Advertising\" href=\"http://getadora.com/ads/\">Advertisers</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about Advertising with Adora)</em></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\"><a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\">Affiliates</a></h1>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>(Click here to learn more about our Affiliate Program)</em></p>','Partners','','inherit','open','open','','802-revision-v1','','','2014-12-02 21:47:36','2014-12-02 21:47:36','',802,'http://getadora.com/802-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(812,4,'2014-12-02 22:36:33','2014-12-02 22:36:33','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-595 size-full\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/AffiliateProgram.jpg\" alt=\"AffiliateProgram\" width=\"470\" height=\"394\" /></a>Hi, welcome to our info page on the Adora Affiliate Program.\n\nWe want you to promote our app along with causes and charities that are important to you, to your customers, lists, blog readers, social networking followers, and anyone else or through any other avenue where you have a voice. In return for this you have two amazing rewards:\n\nYou\'ll feel great knowing you\'ve helped do more good through Adora and that is a great feeling, but...\nWe all know that an Affiliate Program needs to help you in return financially so...\n\nWe have one of, if not the best, affiliate programs available:\n\nYou get <em>up to*</em> <strong>$2.50 </strong>per user per month for up to 12 months--how long depends on how soon you become an affiliate. Those who sign up on or before December 17th will keep their reward bonuses for 12 months.\n\nYour users will need to download the Adora App. It\'s free. And as long as they keep using the app, you can earn your reward bonuses. Our Affiliate Program is expected to change dramatically in 2015, so partner with us before the December 17th deadline.\n\n<em>*up to $2.50 means that the amount made per user depends on how often your customers use their phone.</em>\n\nOur app is coming soon. We will begin advertising through the notifications system paired with full-page, in-app ads. We pay our affiliates after we get paid by the advertisers.\n\nTo get started fill out this form and we\'ll register you into our affiliate program.\n\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRW5XG6L3866\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Affiliate Program','','inherit','open','open','','536-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-02 22:36:33','2014-12-02 22:36:33','',536,'http://getadora.com/536-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(813,4,'2014-12-03 09:06:40','2014-12-03 09:06:40','Adora exists to help you do more good.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Charity.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-208 alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Charity.jpg\" alt=\"Charity\" width=\"401\" height=\"244\" /></a>Through Adora we hope to help all of our charitable partners do more good through better exposure, more consistent funding, and increased volunteer involvement.\r\n\r\nHere is how it works:\r\n\r\nThe Program is FREE, you will never pay for our services.\r\n\r\nThe Adora Charity Funding Program requires a very simple formal agreement, Adora doesn\'t even need your donor list to engage your supporters, we trust you to do that. When you become a Charity Partner you will be part of our <a title=\"Adora Affiliate Program\" href=\"http://getadora.com/affiliate/\" target=\"_blank\">Affiliate Program</a> but with some amazing advantages:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your users will bring you funding for as long as they use the app, no 12-6 month expiration.</li>\r\n	<li>You will receive free advertising on the network that grows with your Adora user base (Ask us about this)</li>\r\n	<li>Free ad design consulting</li>\r\n	<li>Access to a Charity specific reporting profile - Track ad performance and donations in real time</li>\r\n	<li>Donations will be made Monthly &amp; Quarterly (75/25 ask us), we pay for transaction fees</li>\r\n	<li>Earn a guaranteed referral fee every month for every user you bring to us</li>\r\n	<li>Direct Donations will not be limited, users will be able to donate to you via our app, and we will pay the transaction fees.</li>\r\n	<li>Listed on the Featured Charity List (users will choose one regardless of referral source)</li>\r\n	<li>Your Charity will eligible for Adora Grant Funding (Ask us)</li>\r\n	<li>You may be invited to be part of the beta Social Network focused on doing good, volunteer work, spontaneous good works, and of course, charitable giving (coming in 2016).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe key to your funding and the scope of all of these benefits will be based on your effort in promoting your Charity on the Adora App.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-652 size-medium\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Choice\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>Special Crowdfunding Opportunity</strong>\r\n\r\nOn December 4th, we will be lunching a crowdfunding campaign. In this campaign we will raising money to complete the app and feed people and pets. This campaign will focus on fighting holiday hunger and be a great way to acquire users of our app who will fund you monthly once the app begins delivering ads.  The more users that download our app from your partner link, the less that is spent on non-charity affiliate costs be cause those affiliate fees go to your charity. We\'ll tell you more once you are on board.\r\n\r\nWe’re planning a very aggressive PR campaign through the holiday season. During this period we will be visiting some of our partner charities to record and document the use of funds we’ve donated. These professionally produced videos will also be made available for your charity to use as well. This exposure will encourage others to go out and do more good.\r\n\r\nBy partnering with us we will be able to work together to do more good.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to receive more information, please fill out and return the ‘Letter of Interest’ section below and we will contact you to talk about how to become an Adora partner.\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRWR8S5X4Z7N\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Charity Program','','inherit','open','open','','68-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-03 09:06:40','2014-12-03 09:06:40','',68,'http://getadora.com/68-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(818,4,'2014-12-03 07:19:00','2014-12-03 07:19:00','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our passion at Adora is to do as much good as we possibly can.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what drives our every action and what makes our hearts burn to work harder, longer, and smarter.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adora will ignite this passion in others to start a movement which will lead to a change in not just corporate giving but also in private giving too. Adora stands for the principle that even $1 here or $5 there can make a difference--that you don\'t have to be wealthy to give and you don\'t have to give money to make an impact.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/RXMnDG3QzxE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Read more <a title=\"Charity+\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">about Adora</a> or find out more <a title=\"The app\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/adora-app/\">about the Adora app</a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you would like to talk more or for additional info please feel free to <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">contact us</a>.</strong></p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-03 07:19:00','2014-12-03 07:19:00','',2,'http://getadora.com/2-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(819,4,'2014-12-03 07:37:11','2014-12-03 07:37:11','<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Our passion at Adora is to do as much good as we possibly can.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">This is what drives our every action and what makes our hearts burn to work harder, longer, and smarter.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adora will ignite this passion in others to start a movement which will lead to a change in not just corporate giving but also in private giving too. Adora stands for the principle that even $1 here or $5 there can make a difference--that you don\'t have to be wealthy to give and you don\'t have to give money to make an impact.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/RXMnDG3QzxE\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Read more <a title=\"Charity+\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/charity/\">about Adora</a> or find out more <a title=\"The app\" href=\"http://getadora.com/about/adora-app/\">about the Adora app</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you would like to talk more or for additional info please feel free to <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\">contact us</a>.</strong></p>','About','','inherit','open','open','','2-revision-v1','','','2014-12-03 07:37:11','2014-12-03 07:37:11','',2,'http://getadora.com/2-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(820,4,'2014-12-03 08:14:20','2014-12-03 08:14:20','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many people would love to do more...</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So why isn\'t more getting done?</strong></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Many of us believe that unless our donation is large, it doesn\'t make a difference. Or that unless we spend hours or days volunteering, then it\'s not worth the small impact.\n\nAt Adora we are not asking our users to change their mobile device use. Our users don\'t even have to open our app or take any more time out of their busy days to do good through Adora.\n\nOur app gives our users a choice they have never had before--to choose where their advertising earnings go. We make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\n\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-652\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\" alt=\"Choice\" width=\"884\" height=\"498\" /></a>\n\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">The Adora app is simple--the advertising pays for charity work, but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The Adora app will also make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference, but if 1 million or 10 million users all donate, then those dollars add up!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"421\" height=\"258\" /> Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see  us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible. And oh the good that could be done with that  kind  of donation every month!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company  in the world.</strong></p>\n But once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish. We must change the way we look at charitable  organizations.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"> Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses. Be it a hashtag trending on twitter, a viral video, or dumping ice water on our heads. We know there are few better ways to move mountains than through the power of numbers. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below. Better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/bfAzi6D5FpM\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n\n<h3>Our Vision</h3>\nWe see a world where <strong>everyone is doing good every day. </strong>\n<h3><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></strong></h3>\n<strong> It is our vision to lead a change in private &amp; corporate social activity by becoming the most charitable company in  the world by 2020.</strong>\n\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such a lofty goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-  tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Even the most charitable companies never donate more  than 15% of their pre-tax profits. Walmart has been at the top of the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo leading the way in 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account, Pfizer has taken the top spot for the  last 4 years.\n\nWe know these are very large companies, but one of our goals is to reach the point where we are <strong>donating more than 51% of  our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to that point, but how fast  and how much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want help out, read more about <a title=\"How You Can Help\" href=\"http://getadora.com/can-help/\">how you can be more involved</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong></p>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-03 08:14:20','2014-12-03 08:14:20','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(821,4,'2014-12-03 08:17:14','2014-12-03 08:17:14','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">There are so many who need help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many charities are trying to help.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Many people would love to do more...</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>So why isn\'t more getting done?</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><img class=\"alignright wp-image-252\" src=\"http://lscapp.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Charity1.jpg\" alt=\"CharityWordle1\" width=\"478\" height=\"291\" />Time &amp; Money</h2>\r\nThis is what stops most of us from doing more. We have enough trouble balancing our lives as it is. Many of us believe that unless our donation is large, it doesn\'t make a difference. Or that unless we spend hours or days volunteering, then it\'s not worth the small impact.\r\n\r\nAt Adora we are not asking our users to change their mobile device use. Our users don\'t even have to open our app or take any more time out of their busy days to do good through Adora.\r\n\r\nOur app gives our users a choice they have never had before--to choose where their advertising earnings go. We make it clear that no donation is too small to make a difference.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-652\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Choice.jpg\" alt=\"Choice\" width=\"884\" height=\"498\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">The Adora app is simple--the advertising pays for charity work, but the users determine where the funds go.</span></strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The Adora app will also make it easy to donate as little as $1 a month and make that seemingly insignificant sum hold the weight of our entire user base. $1 alone makes little difference, but if 1 million or 10 million users all donate, then those dollars add up!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><img class=\"alignleft  wp-image-340\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/CrowdCellLights-300x184.jpg\" alt=\"CrowdCellLights\" width=\"421\" height=\"258\" /> Imagine if we could be as well supported as a game like Candy Crush and its 100 million users. That would see  us donating over $100 million every month! That is possible. And oh the good that could be done with that  kind  of donation every month!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> Every effort we make is guided by the goal voiced in our vision: <strong>To become the most charitable company  in the world.</strong></p>\r\n But once we reach that lofty goal there is more to accomplish. We must change the way we look at charitable  organizations.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\"> Charity+ = The next evolution of charitable funding</h2>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5em;\">We have seen the strength of the masses. Be it a hashtag trending on twitter, a viral video, or dumping ice water on our heads. We know there are few better ways to move mountains than through the power of numbers. If real good is to be done it must be done by everyone and it must be seen as possible.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For this to be possible we must look at the business of charity work in a much different way. We resonate with Dan in his TED Talk below. Better support for great leadership, management, marketing, and business principals is essential to success in the world of doing good. We cannot expect great performance without great support.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/bfAzi6D5FpM\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Our Vision</h3>\r\nWe see a world where <strong>everyone is doing good every day. </strong>\r\n<h3><strong><a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-281\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/GreenView-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"GreenView\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></strong></h3>\r\n<strong> It is our vision to lead a change in private &amp; corporate social activity by becoming the most charitable company in  the world by 2020.</strong>\r\n\r\nTo be perfectly honest this is not such a lofty goal, unfortunately. In 2012 the average company donated a median of <strong>0.8% of pre-  tax profits, which is less than the normal range of 1% to 1.4%</strong>. Even the most charitable companies never donate more  than 15% of their pre-tax profits. Walmart has been at the top of the list of most charitable companies 7 times over the last 8 years with Wells Fargo leading the way in 2011. When both cash and products are taken into account, Pfizer has taken the top spot for the  last 4 years.\r\n\r\nWe know these are very large companies, but one of our goals is to reach the point where we are <strong>donating more than 51% of  our pre-tax profits</strong> to good causes. We want to be very clear that we know it could take us years to get to that point, but how fast  and how much we donate will really be up to the supportive public and brands who want to reach them.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>If you want help out, read more about <a title=\"How You Can Help\" href=\"http://getadora.com/can-help/\">how you can be more involved</a>, or if you are just interested in learning more, <a title=\"Contact Us\" href=\"http://getadora.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\">contact us.</a></strong></p>','Charity+','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2014-12-03 08:17:14','2014-12-03 08:17:14','',62,'http://getadora.com/62-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(896,1,'2015-02-11 22:36:50','2015-02-11 22:36:50','<a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-591  alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.jpg\" alt=\"LockScreenExample1\" width=\"191\" height=\"400\" /></a> <a href=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-592  alignright\" src=\"http://getadora.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/LockScreenExample1.png\" alt=\"LockScreenExample1\" width=\"191\" height=\"400\" /></a>Adora Advertising is different for one HUGE reason... When anyone looks at our ads they KNOW they are doing good.\r\n\r\nWith every other ad platform - Facebook, Google, Twitter, Yahoo, you name it - people are turned off by advertising. They don\'t want it. They didn\'t say \"yes\" to the ads, even if they said \"yes\" to the product or service.\r\n\r\nRight now we are preparing to populate our app with ads. Most large brands and ad agencies need us to have a large user base before they will even consider advertising with us, so like many organizations we have the \"Chicken or the egg\" dilemma.\r\n\r\nWe are currently offering great discounted ad packages - send us an email - ads (at) getadora.com<strong> to start the process.</strong>\r\n\r\n<script src=\"https://secure.echosign.com/public/embeddedWidget?wid=AEIRWL6X2G4C68\" type=\"text/javascript\" language=\"JavaScript\"></script>','Adora Advertising','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2015-02-11 22:36:50','2015-02-11 22:36:50','',51,'http://getadora.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(825,1,'2014-12-04 21:34:27','2014-12-04 21:34:27','<b>1) How did you come up with the idea?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are two parts to the creation of Adora.\r\n\r\nFirst, the lockscreen advertising. This came as a result of consulting with a company that sells cell phone covers and matching lockscreen images. We thought, “Hey that is a great place to put an ad or deal like Groupon, but you don’t have to go digging for it.”\r\n\r\nSecond, the Adora culture. While lockscreen advertising can be convenient to the user, no one wants to see more advertising. Why would anyone voluntarily download an app like that? It was a roadblock until we started to talk about a different part of the company - the culture. We wanted to make it easy for our employees to volunteer, even if that meant giving them time off to do that. Then we talked about giving charities free advertising so they could let people know about volunteer opportunities. Then it finally hit us - we could make the entire company about <i>doing good</i>. Everything changed for us after that.\r\n\r\n<b>2) Why an app?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are very few effective ways to reach a lot of people. Technology has changed the way we communicate and interact. TV, newspapers, radio and even laptops &amp; desktops are all shrinking platforms- the only medium which is really growing is Mobile. Most people have a smartphone.\r\n\r\n<b>3) How will it work?</b>\r\n\r\nThe idea is really simple. We deliver ads, offers, deals, news and sponsored stories to your notification system and lockscreen. In exchange, advertisers pay for the donation a user sends to their charity.\r\n\r\n<b>4) Can advertisers pick where the charitable money goes?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. We give that power to the individual users. The user gets to champion and support their favorite charity. Advertisers will only be able to say that they DON’T want to advertise on the phones of people who support certain causes.\r\n\r\n<b>5) How do I pick my charity?</b>\r\n\r\nUsers can choose a cause and work with any of the great charities already partnered with us, or they can specify their own. We will contact the charity and ask if they want to receive funds from an Adora user.\r\n\r\n<b>6) Where will my personal information go?</b>\r\n\r\nSecurity is very important to us. Personally identifiable information will never be shared with a third party without your express consent. Aggregated user activity may be shared to identify general user characteristics of those who may be most interested in a product, offer, or deal. For example, 13% of men ages 18-34 respond positively to ads for sports related products.\r\n\r\n<b>7) Who will have access to my personal information and how will it be used?</b>\r\n\r\nPersonally identifiable information will never shared with a third party without your expressed consent. From time to time, some of our users may be asked to participate in focus groups to give feedback about ads, products, or services. This will always be at the users discretion.  Aggregated user activity may be shared to identify general user characteristics in the form outlined above.\r\n\r\n<b>8) Can I only donate to one charity at a time?</b>\r\n\r\nCurrently, any money you generate can only be donated to one charity at a time. In the future, we plan to add the ability to give to multiple charities (splitting your donation to them).\r\n\r\n<b>9) How will my charity be paid?</b>\r\n\r\nCharities that are partnered with Adora will receive monthly or quarterly payments directly from Adora by wire transfer or check. The amount donated and frequency of payments will be based on user support. Any charity with less than 100 users will receive quarterly payments. The amount of the donation is based on the information a user gives us and the frequency ads are delivered (how often an app user unlocks their phone or views a notification).\r\n\r\n<b>10) What if the advertiser doesn\'t agree with the cause?</b>\r\n\r\nWhile we don’t anticipate this happening, we want advertisers to experience the same options users do. Advertisers will be given the option to not send advertising to users who support a certain cause.\r\n\r\n<b>11) How often can I change where my money is going?</b>\r\n\r\nEvery Month\r\n\r\n<b>12) How will I know the charity is actually receiving what you say they\'re getting?</b>\r\n\r\nWe are working on allowing users to receive real time updates. This will allow you to track the amount you have earned for your charity during the month and the total amount you have already donated. Charities will also have the ability to track the number of users and the amount they have earned in real time.\r\n\r\nIf you explicitly authorize Adora to share your personal information with your charity of choice, you will be able to request your personal donation information directly from them.\r\n\r\n<b>13) What do you (Adora) get out of doing this?</b>\r\n\r\nWe get the opportunity to change the way charity is done. We are a for-profit company, but we know that when we succeed, the causes we are so passionate about do even better.\r\n\r\n<b>14) How often will more charities be added to the selection?</b>\r\n\r\nWe will add charities as soon as they have been properly vetted. It’s not a long process, but we want to make sure that any charity we partner with will appropriately use funds donated by our users.\r\n\r\n<b>15) How often will I be seeing pop up ads on my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nIn addition to ads, offers, news, and sponsored stories, we want to allow users to add in some of their own content like pictures. We also want users to have the option to decide the frequency of ads. The more ads delivered, the more you generate for your cause.\r\n\r\n<b>16) What if I don\'t want to be associated with a certain advertiser, what can I do to stop getting pop ups from them?</b>\r\n\r\nOur innovative lockscreen will allow users to give direct feedback about ads and advertisers. Simply give it a thumbs down and our learning engine will learn your preferences.\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><b>16 a) How does the learning engine work?</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You get to rate ads as you see them. This helps us tailor your experience to your preferences. Every time you interact with the lockscreen we learn about the products and brands you love. Over time, you’ll love the deals and offers almost as much as you love the good you are doing.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><b>16 b) Why would an advertiser agree to let you thumbs down their ad? </b></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Because feedback (even bad feedback) can be helpful. By letting you rate ads, they get valuable feedback and save money by NOT advertising to people who don’t like them. Maybe they can even adapt and listen to that feedback in a way that could win you over in the future. AND you get to shape your experience; you have more control over what you see with Adora than you do with any other advertising platform.</p>\r\n<b>17) How do I get the ads to stop altogether?</b>\r\n\r\nIn our buildout we will have an option for you to control the frequency of ads you see. You can always delete the app, but in that case, your charity will no longer be funded.\r\n\r\n<b>18) Is there a plan to expand it to gadgets other than my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nAbsolutely! We want to make Adora available on every mobile device (anything that has a touch screen) so that we can do even more for our charities.\r\n\r\n<b>19) Will there be a difference on how the app will work on Droids vs. Apple</b>\r\n\r\nApple has been cautious about letting anyone onto the lockscreen, so initially, Apple users will only get deals and offers through the notification system. We hope that Apple and Apple users will see the tremendous amount of good Adora is doing and allow the full functionality on the lockscreen.\r\n\r\n<b>20) Are there other apps similar to this one?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are a few lockscreens out there, but none with our charity concept or learning engine.\r\n\r\n<b>21) If the app costs me nothing and I am never giving you money, how do the charities get paid?</b>\r\n\r\nAdora gets paid to deliver content. We simply give our users a choice on where some of that ad revenue they generate goes.\r\n\r\n<b>22) What happens to my charitable donation if the charity I am donating to decides they don\'t want to be a part of Adora any more?  Who decides where my donation will go?</b>\r\n\r\nCharities don’t need to partner with Adora to receive funding. If for some reason a charity does not want to receive money from Adora, we will notify you to choose another charity.\r\n\r\n<b>23) What hours of the day will be most popular for ads?</b>\r\n\r\nWe won’t know this until further down the road, but ads delivered around breakfast, lunch, and dinner will most likely be the most popular.\r\n\r\n<b>24) Will I be able to write off my charitable donation on my taxes?</b>\r\n\r\nThe revenue which is generated as a result of the ads will not be eligible for tax reductions. However, other donations made out of pocket by you to a charity through Adora will be.\r\n\r\n<b>25) What is the benefit to your advertisers to participate in this?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are some great advantages to advertising with Adora. One - you know that you get to do some good by advertising with us. That will make the advertisers and audience both happy. Two - amazing targeting capabilities. We can target by demographic, psychographic, geographic, and time. Three - we can also get direct feedback on ads shown. Imagine being able to get real time direct feedback for two different ads of the same product. This would allow companies to find out which ads their audience dislike and which ones they like without having to do more costly focus groups.\r\n\r\n<b>26) How much money will each charity get?</b>\r\n\r\nThe amount of money a charity gets will depend completely on users and the frequency that ads are delivered. The more users a charity attracts, the more they use their phone, the more money they will receive.\r\n\r\n<b>27) How do you determine the percentage? / How much are you actually planning on giving to charity?</b>\r\n\r\nThe amount of money generated by a user depends on their use of their phone. The more they use their phone, the more ads they get delivered, the more money they earn for their charity. Our company goal is to send at least 20 cents out of every dollar to your causes to start. Eventually we plan to give half of every dollar we earn to charities across the world.\r\n\r\n<b>28) What happens to those charities that people don\'t choose to donate to on their own? Do they still get money donated to them?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. Charities will only receive donations from Adora users who have selected that particular charity.\r\n\r\n<b>29) Is the app ever going to hinder me to get to my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. It works the same way your current lockscreen does, except now whenever you unlock your phone you are generating funds for your charity. Doing good doesn’t get any easier.\r\n\r\n<b>30) Will it be every time I access my phone?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. We will allow users to choose the frequency of the ads and offers they receive.\r\n\r\n<b>31) Is having it going to slow down my phone, take too much memory?</b>\r\n\r\nNo. Most advertising content is pretty small. Content will be loaded and stored onto your mobile device when you are connected to wifi. This way it will simply pull a small stored file that takes no time at all.\r\n\r\n<b>32) What does Adora mean?  How did you come up with the name?</b>\r\n\r\nAdora means ‘love’ in portuguese. Mark (one of the founders) and his brother actually came up with it during a discussion about the app.\r\n\r\n<b>33) Who are the people behind Adora?</b>\r\n\r\nWe have had a lot of help in building Adora. There are four founders: Kyle Thomas, Mark Feriante, Ben Faanunu, and David Brinkerhoff. We also have great advisors Devin Thorpe, Brian Critchfield, Wayne Carroll, Bert Martinez, Joe Michels, and Sebastean Losch, Bob Frasure, Christian Sampson, Joyce Sowards, and Heather Faanunu. We wouldn’t be here if not for the loving support and encouragement of all of our family and friends.\r\n\r\n<b>34) How will Adora verify the charity is a legitimate cause?</b>\r\n\r\nWe hope to partner with organizations, like Charity Navigator, who evaluate and score charities based on financial health, accountability, and transparency. We will be staying away from nonprofit organizations that are involved in politics, and instead work with charities that are really making a difference in the lives of people everyday.\r\n\r\n<b>35) Will you provide details on the charity and what they do?</b>\r\n\r\nWe will be featuring and highlighting different charities through the app. We want charities to have the opportunity to get the word out on what they do. We will also be periodically updating you on the good being accomplished because of your donations. This is part of our commitment to you, so that you know that your money is doing good.\r\n\r\n<b>36) Will you accept anyone as one of your advertisers, or will you be selective about who can advertise?</b>\r\n\r\nIt’s important for us to use discretion when advertising products. While we anticipate working with most advertisers, we will not show any imagery which we do not deem as being family- friendly. We know that anyone can pick up your phone, so the ads delivered cannot be suggestive in any way.\r\n\r\n<b>37) Will there be parental controls on the advertisement?</b>\r\n\r\nEach ad will be evaluated on a case by case basis to make sure it is family friendly. We definitely want to make that option available, but we anticipate that the guards we have will be sufficient for most parents.\r\n\r\n<b>38) How will you control whether or not my child may accidentally get an advertisement that may be too adult for them?</b>\r\n\r\nEach ad will be evaluated on a case by case basis to make sure it is family friendly. Ads which may be appropriate for adults but not for the entire family will not be shown on our app. We are sensitive to our charity partners who work in a wide range of causes and must ensure that our ads do not contradict the good work they do.\r\n\r\n<b>39) Would you ever turn down a specific charity? Or are all welcome?</b>\r\n\r\nAny nonprofit organization which does political work will be excluded. Funds from Adora will be limited to charities which address the more immediate need of individuals.\r\n\r\n<b>40) Can you limit your donation to just your local chapter?</b>\r\n\r\nAs we grow, we hope to make this an option.\r\n\r\n<b>41) How will you communicate how much money you\'ve donated to charity?</b>\r\n\r\nThe app will track your monthly donations and the total amount you’ve donated.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','F.A.Q\'s','','inherit','open','open','','761-revision-v1','','','2014-12-04 21:34:27','2014-12-04 21:34:27','',761,'http://getadora.com/761-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(826,6,'2014-12-05 04:40:04','2014-12-05 04:40:04','','indieGOGO','','publish','closed','closed','','indiegogo','','','2014-12-05 04:40:04','2014-12-05 04:40:04','',0,'http://getadora.com/?post_type=surl&#038;p=826',0,'surl','',0),(829,6,'2014-12-08 14:46:51','2014-12-08 14:46:51','This Christmas and Holiday Season, Adora has joined with our partner charities in <a href=\"https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/adora-the-lockscreen-charity-app/x/9144872\" target=\"_blank\">Fighting Holiday Hunger</a>.\r\n\r\nWinter is a tough time for so many, already with the additional expenses of heating costs and continued increase in the price of basic staple groceries, even our friends and neighbors who get by most of the year have things even harder at time of the year for celebration and thanksgiving.  Some of our neighbors have less and some have none at all.  Some of our neighbors are children, some of them are elderly, some of them are sick, some of them are unemployed , some of them need your help right now.\r\n\r\nJoin with Adora right now in providing 1 or several meals for those in need right now.  Your gift to feed a neighbor for the holidays will continue bless your community year round as we complete our Adora Charity App for Android and iOS which will allow every mobile user to fund the charity of their choice each month without having to spend their own money.\r\n\r\nPlease<a href=\"http://https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/adora-the-lockscreen-charity-app/x/9144872\" target=\"_blank\"> contribute to the campaign</a>, let us know where one of our Food Bank, Pantry, Soup Kitchen, Shelter, or Rescue Mission partners can deliver the meals by commenting on the campaign.  Share the number of meals you have donated through your contribution on social media and inspire your friends and followers to do the same. #dosomegood #Adora','Fight Holiday Hunger','','inherit','open','open','','828-revision-v1','','','2014-12-08 14:46:51','2014-12-08 14:46:51','',828,'http://getadora.com/828-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(863,1,'2015-01-30 00:34:20','2015-01-30 00:34:20','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Adora is popping up all over and really gaining momentum! Check out some of our recent appearances in the news and on different blogs and sites!</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><script src=\"http://KPHO.images.worldnow.com/interface/js/WNVideo.js?rnd=514695;hostDomain=www.kpho.com;playerWidth=640;playerHeight=400;isShowIco